INSERT INTO `dashboard_eventdata` VALUES (436,'1535952475000','ClimbOn Basic Mountaineering Course','254343076','1542124009000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/254343076/','ClimbOn Ashim - 9000567089, ClimbOn Arun - 8328662479','2018-11-17 17:00:00.000000','upcoming','Mahaboob Nagar','Hyderabad','in','Khilla Ghanpur Fort',0,'2018-11-13 15:46:00.000000','<p>Expected total team size is 25.</p> <p>Dates: NOVEMBER 17TH 5pm to NOVEMBER 24TH 5pm</p> <p>Place: Khilla Ghanpur Camp</p> <p>ClimbOn is an adventure club/community based out of Hyderabad that brings adventure enthusiasts together. It facilitates fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor adventure experiences by organizing activities like trekking, outdoor climbing, hiking, bouldering, camping, adventure treks, sports, fitness events etc. Last year ClimbOn adventures club comes up with the BASIC MOUNTAINEERING COURSE providing mountaineering training to 15 people. This is the second edition of the same course.</p> <p>Through this course our plan is to train ClimbOn organizers and some of our active members.</p> <p><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/l45UbTq.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/U4Y1fDj.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/Ey6Qmmg.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/8L1w1fO.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/yIi1cyN.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/oktINVg.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/3fSsfM0.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/Hkpvmv0.jpg\" /><br/><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/xq2Tmr7.jpg\" /></p> <p>Good news for Hyderabad adventure lovers.</p> <p>ClimbOn adventures club gives you the chance of learning basic mountaineering and survival technicques.</p> <p>This training course include</p> <p>1) Climbing<br/>Regular classes on climbing techniques and gears. Learn about side, upper, lower grips and use in regular practice on wall, tree and rock climbing. For wall climbing, we will be using top as well as bottom belays in practice and for rock climbing, we will practice bouldering and climbing using pitons.</p> <p>2) Rappelling<br/>We will practice different types of rappelling - shoulder, abs and Australian Rappelling. Understand the importance of belay and practice providing belay to other participants.</p> <p>3) Forest survival techniques<br/>Ever stayed alone in a forest? Ever cooked alone while backpacking? After this course, you will be an expert in all this. Learn more about camping, cooking in forests, how to be aware of animals in forest environment.</p> <p>4) Compass reading<br/>Learn to read the compass to see the directions, always helpful during hiking and trekking.</p> <p>5) Mountaineering gears<br/>Learn use of ropes, harnesses, pitons, carabiners, belay, figure of 8 in day to day practice of different mountaineering techniques.</p> <p>6) Different types of Knots<br/>ClimbOn will provide you regular classes on different knots to be used in different mountaineering techniques like Rappelling, Tree climbing, Wall Climbing. Make sure you practice this daily even after the course.</p> <p>7) Self Defense<br/>Learn techniques of self defense from animals and human attacks, useful in trekking and day to day life.</p> <p>BASIC RULES OF THIS TRAINING PROGRAM<br/>1) Once you join the training camp, you must follow trainer’s instructions. Don\'t expect any preference as a club organizer.<br/>2) You should not take any step without trainer’s permission.<br/>3) Usage of mobile phones during training time (6 am to 6 pm) is strictly not allowed.<br/>4) During training, you might have to accommodate with whatever food we provide.<br/>5) During training, you will not be allowed to go outside.<br/>6) Trainer instruction is the final word and you are expected to accept.</p> <p>Sign up for the training if you are ready to follow the above mentioned instructions. Go through the rules carefully and contact us.</p> <p>Damages: 4000(non refundable)</p> <p>Please pay the full amount by NOVEMBER 05th to confirm your slot.</p> <p>Account name: Climb on adventures society<br/>AXIS BANK:916010056765291<br/>IFSC CODE: UTIB0002960<br/>Account Type: Current</p> <p>TRAINING WILL BE CONDUCTED AT KHILLAGHANPUR AS PER THE CLEARANCE FROM GOVT OF TELANGANA STATE</p> <p>NOTE: Event Hosts have all the rights to add or remove any member and do necessary changes in route, activity, time, duration depending on the situations and weather conditions. ORGANIZER\'S DECISION IS FINAL (IT IS ALL ABOUT SAFETY, Please Co-operate)</p> '),(437,'1542588081000','ClimbOn Fitness: Ashtanga vinyasa yoga and Power Yoga','256530183','1542599044000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/256530183/','SP Singh (93-90-33-69-92); Jagadeesh (8008-48-9618)','2018-11-25 07:00:00.000000','upcoming','kondapur','Hyderabad','in','Botanical Garden',0,'2018-11-19 03:44:00.000000','<p>Come and join ClimbOn’s lovely morning outdoor yoga sessions. Enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Enjoy the open air, smell of the trees, hear birds’ chirps, connect with yourself, and sweat off toxins by having lovely morning with holistic body and mind uplifting through yoga workouts! Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p>A glimpse from previous yoga event:<br/><a href=\"https://youtu.be/FDsVPKBB-nI\" class=\"embedded\">https://youtu.be/FDsVPKBB-nI</a></p> <p>About the Event Host:</p> <p>Event host is a corporate yoga trainer for past 10 years and has learnt yoga from Mysore, Rishikesh and many other yoga schools. He is very passionate about Yoga and meditation.</p> <p>Who should join this yoga?<br/>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practised with ClimbOn.</p> <p>Fee?<br/>There is no fee , class is free of cost. Entry fee of park is to be paid by individuals.</p> <p>Where?<br/>Botanical Gardens,</p> <p>What we are going to practice?<br/>Ashtanga Vinyasa Yoga (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashtanga_vinyasa_yoga\" class=\"linkified\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashtanga_vinyasa_yoga</a>): in its traditional form, as taught by the late Sri. K. Pattabhi Jois (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Pattabhi_Jois\" class=\"linkified\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Pattabhi_Jois</a>). – Today this is the practice that is most common around the world. Widely practised for strength, stamina and fitness. Also known as Mysore style of yoga. In Ashtanga vinyasa there are sun salutation A &amp; B series, primary, intermediate and advance series of Asnas. As a beginner we will practice sun salutation A &amp; B, primary series of Asnas and finishing Asnas to have feel of asthanga vinyasa yoga.</p> <p>Sun salutation: The sun salutation (Sūrya Namaskāra) forms the foundation of Aṣṭāṅga vinyasa practice. Here you will establish the calm rhythm of breathing (Ujjāyī) direction of Energy (Bandha) and concentration (Ḍṛṣti). The powerful flow of a moving meditation is born. Primary series (Āsana) helps us to expel toxins and prepare body for advance practice . The dynamic of the sun salutations transform to new forms of movement. (Vinyāsa). Asnas of primary series require power, flexibility and endurance. The finishing sequence guides the practitioner in Aṣṭāṅga Yoga to an energetic culmination. The breathing (Ujjāyī) calms down, muscle contractions (Bandha) become subtle and concentration (Ḍṛṣti) turns inward.</p> <p>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time .<br/>Call or what\'s app :9390336992 or 8008489618 for more info.</p> <p>Well known facts about Yoga:</p> <p>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</p> <p>• Increased flexibility.<br/>• Increased muscle strength and tone.<br/>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality.<br/>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism.<br/>• Weight reduction.<br/>• Cardio and circulatory health.<br/>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p>What you need to bring along?</p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat (alternatives are large bedsheet or towel)<br/>• Wear loose comfortable clothing<br/>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> '),(438,'1539622018000','Lets Climb HariHar Fort','255556086','1542613079000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/255556086/',NULL,'2018-12-07 17:00:00.000000','upcoming','','','','',0,'2018-11-19 07:37:00.000000','<p>Details<br/>Please read full description before RSVP\'ing</p> <p>Difficulty level: Medium+<br/>Only for Ages 18+</p> <p>This is a 2 days trek and we will be covering HariHar Fort .</p> <p>Itinerary:</p> <p>Day 1 - Friday : Catch Ajantha express in Secunderabad at 06:30PM</p> <p>Day 2 - Saturday : Reach Manmad by 07:00 AM.</p> <p>Take Train/Bus and Reach Nashik by 10:00AM. Have breakfast.</p> <p>Take Local Transport and reach Nirgudpada. Start Trek at 12:30PM</p> <p>Reach fort by 6:30 PM. Camp</p> <p>Day 3 - Sunday : Wake up call by 05:00 AM</p> <p>EXplore the fort till 9:00 AM</p> <p>Start to Base village and reach village by 11 A.M</p> <p>Take Bus and reach Manmad railway station</p> <p>Day4 - Monday : Reach Secunderabad by 09:00AM (plan your office accordingly)</p> <p>Tata Bye bye....</p> <p>Please go through the entire description and answer all the RSVP questions.</p> <p>Harihar Fort:</p> <p>Harihar, also known as Harshgad is a beautiful trek located 60 kms away from Kasara. Harihar fort looks like rectangular in shape from base village and built on triangular prism of rock the edges of this stunning fort is absolutely vertical. Rock cut stair case leads you the fort.</p> <p>There is a small temple of Lord Hanuman and Lord Shiva on the plateau. A small pond is there in front of this temple. There is small caves on top of the fort accommodating 10-15 people easily. One of the vertical drops of the fort facing the Nirgudpada village is called ‘Scottish kada’, perhaps because it was climbed for the first time in November 1986 by Doug Scott, the legendary Himalayan mountaineer. It took him two days to climb the cliff which is 170 meters in height.</p> <p>This fort lies in range called Upper Vaitarana range. It lies near Trimbak in the Nashik district of Maharashtra in India. Vaitarna is the main river in this region. It lies at a height of 1120 mt or 3676 ft above the sea level. This fort lies on a traingular rock with all the three sides vertical and is approachable only from one side i.e. through a 200 ft high rock cut staircase. The most fascinating aspect about this trek is the rock cut steps at an 80 degree vertical angle that one has to negotiate to enter the fort. Though it’s a vertical ladder, the steps are provided with groves for proper grip while ascending.</p> <p>Total Cost: ₹2500/- (However anything more or less will be shared equally.)<br/>Excludes Food.</p> <p>Confirm your slot by making the initial payment of 1000RS<br/>Account name: Climb on adventures society<br/>AXIS BANK:916010056765291<br/>IFSC CODE: UTIB0002960<br/>Account Type: Current<br/>mention the trek/event_urname for easy identification</p> <p>Things to bring: [ All are must ]</p> <p>1. 2 Track pants, 2 T-shirts</p> <p>2. Trekking shoes with good grip, and used before. 2 extra pair of socks.</p> <p>3. Personnel medicines if you use any</p> <p>4. Sleeping bag and a proper rucksack (both are mandatory).</p> <p>5. Water : 2-3 litres per head.</p> <p>6. Food for self : Chapatis, Jam, Dry Fruits, Energy Bars, Keera (Cucumber), Beetroot, Carrots, dates, Cashew etc.</p> <p>7. Head Torch or a good Torch light</p> <p>8. Toiletries</p> <p>9. A friendly smile..</p> <p>Please call any questions/ Clarifications</p> <p>Contacts:</p> <p>Sravanthi: 9948752280<br/>Ashish: 9948888980</p> <p>Important Instructions:<br/>1) No smoking and no alcohol.<br/>2) No littering, no pollution of water<br/>3) This is not a luxury trip, We might have to attend our nature calls out in the bushes. Be Prepared.<br/>4) Food will be whatever that is available in a humble village home. Nothing fancy.<br/>5) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention.<br/>6) If you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately.</p> '),(439,'1541180837000','Zindagi na milegi dobara: Scuba Diving & Parasailing at Tarkarli Beach','256072314','1541485610000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/256072314/','Leela - 8309959353, Gaurav - 9592106970','2018-12-14 20:00:00.000000','upcoming','pillar no:-60','hyderabad','in','mehdipatnam',0,'2018-11-06 06:26:00.000000','<p>\"Aazad rehno sikho<br/>Tum ek dariya ke jaise<br/>Lehron mein behna sikho\"</p> <p>No better time to cross off some items from your bucket list than the year end. Let\'s head out to Tarkarli beach this December for Scuba diving and Parasailing in the Arabian sea.</p> <p>Tarkarli over Malvan? There are two diving sites in vicinity: Malvan and Tarkarli beach - we will be diving at Tarkarli beach which is much cleaner and offers good coral views.</p> <p>ATTRACTIONS<br/>- Scuba Diving<br/>- Parasailing<br/>- Water Sports (Banana Ride, Bumper Ride, Kayaking, Jet Skiing, Water Scooter) in Tsunami Island.<br/>- Beach side Home stay<br/>- Sunset, Lots of fun at Beach<br/>- Authentic Malvani Food<br/>- Kolhapuri Dinner at Kolhapur</p> <p>Disclaimer: Swimming is not required for doing scuba diving or any other water sports, given you don\'t experiment too much with the equipment. Proper training will be given for all activities.</p> <p>TARKARLI BEACH</p> <p>Tarkarli is a narrow stretch of beach with pristine waters, located at the convergence of the Karli River and the Arabian Sea. This place has gained prominence because of its transparently clear seas, where on a fairly sunny day, one can see the sea- bed up to a depth of 20 feet. This beach can be rightly called as ‘Queen Beach’ of Sindhudurg.</p> <p>SCUBA DIVING:</p> <p>In India there are a very few places where scuba diving can be done and Malvan is one of them. Due to its relatively clear sea waters, Malvan and Tarkarli beach serves as a perfect spot for scuba diving and snorkelling.</p> <p><a href=\"https://images.thrillophilia.com/image/upload/s--GZWUKEAt--/c_fill,f_auto,fl_strip_profile,h_600,q_auto,w_975/v1/images/photos/000/033/536/original/1522761274_maxresdefault.jpg.jpg?1522761274\" class=\"linkified\">https://images.thrillophilia.com/image/upload/s--GZWUKEAt--/c_fill,f_auto,fl_strip_profile,h_600,q_auto,w_975/v1/images/photos/000/033/536/original/1522761274_maxresdefault.jpg.jpg?1522761274</a></p> <p><img src=\"http://tarkarliscuba.in/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/paragliding.jpg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://hotels.eglobe-solutions.com/eglobeimages/hotels/India/India_Malvan_Hotels_14460_42.jpg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://kokanplanet.in/images/gallery/banana-boat-tarkarli.jpg\" /></p> <p>Itinerary</p> <p>**Friday**</p> <p>07:00 PM - Catch bus (Sleeper/Semi-Sleeper) from Hyderabad to Kolhapur.</p> <p>**Saturday**</p> <p>08:00 AM - Reach Kolhapur, board bus to Malvan.</p> <p>01:00 PM - Reach Tarkarli, Check in to keep luggage and leave for Tsunami Island for Water Sports and Parasailing.</p> <p>06:00 PM - Finish water sports activities, head for sunset at Tarkarli beach followed by some games.</p> <p>08:00 PM - Authentic Malvani Dinner at local place (let\'s find out the best place after reaching there). Back to booked home stay and sleep.</p> <p>**Sunday**</p> <p>05:00 AM - Wake up call, training for scuba diving starts at 06.</p> <p>12:00 PM - Finish the scuba diving, interested members can go for other water sports and Parasailing (need to be pre-booked)</p> <p>01:00 PM - Start back towards Kolhapur</p> <p>06:00 PM - Reach Kolhapur, have Kolhapur Dinner. Catch bus back to Hyderabad at 08 PM.</p> <p>**Monday**</p> <p>09:00 AM - Back to Hyderabad.</p> <p>Total Damages: 6300/- (Scuba Diving only), 7500/- (Scuba Diving, Parasailing and Water Sports)<br/>Other Inclusions:<br/>- AC Sleeper/Semi-Sleeper Bus booking till Kolhapur (Subject to availability - Cost may increase if you confirm late)<br/>- Kolhapur to Malvan bus charges, Malvan Local Transport<br/>- Stay and Sunday Breakfast.<br/>- Club Fund.</p> <p>Excluded:<br/>- Food charges, not mentioned above.<br/>- Personal expenses and anything not mentioned above.</p> <p>Advance Amount: 4000/-</p> <p>Account Details to transfer money to:<br/>Account Num: 20134933082<br/>Account holder name: Gaurav Arora<br/>IFSC: SBIN0002452</p> <p>Tez: 9592106970</p> <p>Refund Policy: 20% deducted only if cancelled before 48 hrs and if organisers are able to find replacement, otherwise 100% deducted.</p> <p>Important Instructions:</p> <p>- Food will be mostly vegetarian. Carry snacks, dry fruits with you for the trek.<br/>- We carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organisers.<br/>- This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable.<br/>- No smoking, alcohol. No littering and pollution of water.</p> <p>Contact Information:</p> <p>Leela - +91 8309959353<br/>Gaurav - +91 9592106970</p> '),(440,'1540971429000','Exploration Trip to Mitte Waterfalls, Adilabad','255992866','1541001982000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/255992866/','ClimbOn ashim@9000567089. ClimbOn arun@8328662479','2019-01-05 05:30:00.000000','upcoming','Bowenpally x road','Hyderabad','in','Bowenpally police station',0,'2018-10-31 16:06:00.000000','<p>About:</p> <p>Saptagundalu waterfalls(also known as Mitte waterfalls by local people.) is located in Sirpur(U) mandal near pittaguda village inside jungle. As the name says, these are 7 waterfalls spread in a distance over 15Kms and only 3 waterfalls out of 7 are accessible on Foot. One has to trek for about 3-4 Kms into jungle to visit these magnificent waterfalls.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/5/2/8/600_458982280.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/a/9/600_458215209.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/5/3/3/600_458982291.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/b/7/600_458215223.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Itinerary</p> <p>Saturday:</p> <p>5.30 am: Start from Hyderabad</p> <p>11.30am reached adilabad</p> <p>Trek into the forest and explore waterfalls. Pitch tents and camp.</p> <p>Sunday:</p> <p>Wakeup and refresh. Pack things and start back to the base point.</p> <p>We will reach Hyderabad by night.</p> <p>**We will travel by our own vehicles.</p> <p>Difficulty level: Difficult<br/>Team size-15</p> <p>Damages: INR 1200 (club fund &amp; forest permission and food).<br/>(Self food preparation)</p> <p>Confirmation of your RSVP by paying advance 500 Rs . Rest can be paid on spot.<br/>Account details</p> <p>Account name: Climb on adventures society<br/>AXIS BANK:916010056765291<br/>IFSC CODE: UTIB0002960<br/>Account Type: Current</p> <p>Travel : We are going in our own vehicles and fule expenses share.</p> <p>climbOn Ashim@9000567089 ClimbOn Arun@ 8328662479</p> '),(441,'1415280275000','trained climber','218015012','1417929571000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/218015012/',NULL,'2014-12-07 05:45:00.000000','past',' Near Raidurgam Bus stop Mumbai Highway Road ','Hyderabad','in','Khajaguda',0,'2014-12-07 05:19:00.000000','<p>We trained as a perfect climbers</p> '),(442,'1416922542000','Beginners LOCAL TREK at Khajaguda Hills','218889803','1417929483000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/218889803/',NULL,'2014-12-07 05:45:00.000000','past',' Near Raidurgam Bus stop Mumbai Highway Road ','Hyderabad','in','Khajaguda',0,'2014-12-07 05:18:00.000000','<p>Open to anyone those who are FIT.Khajaguda is 1 km away from West Durgam Cheruvu. This place has a lot of boulders, a lake and numerous amazing caves. We will hik