otice.</p> <p>Things to bring: Wear Full track pants (avoid jeans). T-shirts(half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>Wear sport/trekking shoes only<br/>sun cap<br/>water bottles - 2x1 lit<br/>get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch on to climb on after and during the trek.<br/>Get your camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/2/b/4/600_435968884.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/5/4/f/600_435969551.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/8/0/e/600_435595310.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/d/e/600_435595262.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>RSVP Rules: We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP  \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case,  just its a humble request to please inform the Organiser a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i> </p> <p>Meeting Place: Mehdipatnam/Reti bowli @ Morine Bakery<br/>Transport: By personal Transport<br/>Cost: Rs 100 towards club.<br/>Contact Details: Climb-On Vamsi: 9700212029, Naveen: 9010143000 </p> <p>Difficulty - Moderate.</p> <p>Please Be On time.</p> '),(456,'1438855725000','Tropical Downpour Season: Grand Canyon of India for Craving Climbers  3-5 Sep\'15','224446120','1441713045000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/224446120/',NULL,'2015-09-03 20:00:00.000000','past','GANDIKOTA ,Kadapa','Hyderabad','in','Gandikota Fort',0,'2015-09-08 11:50:00.000000','<p><b>Tropical Downpour Season: Gandikota- The Grand Canyon of India </b></p> <p>And Yes its for Craving Climbers.</p> <p><b>Gandikota???</b> Why is it called Great Grand Canyon of India? Either you Google it or Come with us to find it.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/7/c/f/600_440602479.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Organiser Pitch: </b>This trip is organised only for serious climbers, the one who have done few treks before. </p> <p>This is a part of Climb-On Hyderabad Training session and apogees have the privilege to take part inn and full fill your thirsting desire of expedition under our trained and certified Pilot. Since this is not a leisure Trek so read this page before saying Yes to it.</p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b><br/>Day1, Day2 .. what we do? what plans do we have? What plans we have made? How we survive there? These are not the questions to be raised for this trip because we are not Travel agents planning for a leisure trip in Woods for Tourists. We are into core outdoor. It will be tough, get prepared for it. Just an overview listed below.<br/>Meetup point will be disclosed only to RSVP members. This will be 2 day trip. We start on Thursday 3rd Sep Evening 8 PM from Hyderabad and reach Gandikota Hills by 7 AM on 4th Sept... </p> <p><i>   Forest hills, Wall climb, Night Camping, Late Night Forest campfire cooking, River crossing, Rock climbing with proper safety equipment, If possible Rappelling too, all these will be a part of our trip for next 2 days.</i></p> <p> We will start back for Hyderabad by late evening of 5th Sep Saturday and reach Hyderabad by morning on Sunday. We all need proper rest for monday schedules.</p> <p><b>Few Instructions and things to Bring: </b><br/>- No smoking, alcohol, littering, and No pollution of water.<br/>- This is not a luxury trip, but out most care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.<br/>- Girls and boys accommodation in separate tents<br/>- Food will be mostly vegetarian, <br/>- We carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers.<br/>- Your Photo Id with a xerox copy of it.<br/>- If you can\'t swim don\'t go deep into the water<br/><b><i> ** Pack light **</i></b><br/>- 1 track pants or loose trousers, Not jeans - full length, 2 T-shirt - No bright colored.<br/>- A rucksack or a hiking bag to keep all the things with a sleeping bag or a Blanket.<br/>- Trekking or sport shoes used at least ones with 2 pairs of socks.<br/>- Torch or headlight with extra spare batteries.<br/>- 2 litres of water, some energy bars or chocolates.<br/>Finally - A good and positive mood.</p> <p><b>Cost:</b><br/>Rs: 2000/- for Transport, Club fund which includes Camping Tents, Ropes, carabiners, Harnesses, Figure-8 (Belay Device) Expertise[Know-how] and first-Aid.<br/>We will share the cost if it is more or less than this, mostly it won\'t be. Food excluded. As a team minor meals like breakfast are taken care by club.</p> <p>Request to transfer the payment to below given account number to confirm your position in the \"Yes\" list. </p> <p>Account Details :-<br/>Account Name : ASHIM KUMAR MAJUMDAR<br/>Account No : 627501513451<br/>Bank : ICICI<br/>Branch Name : Gachibowli<br/>IFSC Code : icic0001114</p> <p>Once payment is transferred, request you to add your transaction ID to comments below to confirm your slot.<br/>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p>Direct numbers : Climb-On Naveen-9010143000. <br/>Climb-On Ashim- 9000567089</p> '),(457,'1440869291000','Mud\' Kabaddi & Night Camping- Welcome to Leisure face of \"Climb On- Hyderabad\"','224971529','1442482638000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/224971529/',NULL,'2015-09-12 14:45:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2015-09-17 09:37:00.000000','<p><b>Mud\' Kabaddi - Welcome to Leisure face of \"Climb On- Hyderabad\"</b>.</p> <p>           We hope it makes your experience with \'Climb on\' more enjoyable!<br/>We Brings you a special event of outplay to live your world and play it Ours for 24 hours. This event is about enjoying and appreciating simple adventure in nature.<br/>You are seriously active when the sun is no more, If you love and enjoy exploring the great outdoors, adventures, fun in natural environment during NIGHTFALL\'S, the moon and the stars are just the perfect companion to a night walk. Same time enjoy meeting new friends with similar interest.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/e/c/5/600_441588837.jpeg\" /></p> <p>It just doesn\'t get much better than camping in Hyderabad outside with friends &amp; family - Food on the grill, a new moon, games around you, enjoying the great outdoors, songs &amp; stories around the campfire, nothing could be better than this for a weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/e/5/d/600_441564157.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/e/a/a/600_441564234.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/8/f/4/600_441399156.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Where: </b>Just across the border from Hyderabad, this is one of our favorites. Got some excellent sites that are right on the shoreline of beautiful fields.</p> <p><b>Date: </b>On Saturday 12th September 3:30pm to 13 Sep 2:30pm. 1D/1N.<br/><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot, just join the waiting list and make the payment.<br/><b>Distance:</b> 90kms away from Uppal on Warangal Highway (2hrs drive)<br/><b>Meetup Point:</b> Uppal X roads, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences: </b>**Mud Kabaddi, yes, you read it right!! Kabbadi in Mud :)</p> <p>a. Trekking.<br/>b. Music &amp; Bon-fire.<br/>c. Camping.<br/>        Plus Nature &amp; fun things to do.</p> <p><b>Things to bring </b>for Mud\' Kabaddi :<br/>A pair of old cloths which you dont mind throwing away.<br/>Sports shoes, preferable old shoes.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and a water bottle.<br/>A plastic bag to carry your muddy clothes.<br/>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Tariff: Rs.650 per head</b> - Limited seats only<br/>Includes:<br/>a. Food (Veg &amp; No n Veg) : Dinner, B/fast, tea &amp; snacks, Bon-fire snacks -           Barbeque and Lunch.<br/>b. Camping gears<br/>c. Activities<br/>d. Campsite charges.</p> <p>Day 1 After reaching by 6pm, Music and dance around the bon-fire; with camping, Dinner.<br/>Day 2 Morning we start the day with a hearty breakfast, enjoying the view,<br/>Then Mud kabaddi followed by lunch and start back by afternoon.<br/>Open to Everyone.</p> <p><i>Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. Its just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p>Request to transfer the payment to below given account number to confirm your position in the \"Yes\" list. </p> <p><b>Account Details : </b><br/>Account Name : ASHIM KUMAR MAJUMDAR <br/>Account No : 627501513451 <br/>Bank : ICICI <br/>Branch Name : Gachibowli <br/>IFSC Code : icic0001114</p> <p>Once payment is transferred, request you to add your transaction ID to comments below to confirm your slot. <br/>For any more questions, our phone lines are open. </p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b> Climb-On Naveen-</i>9010143000<i>, Climb-On Arun-</i>9666031286</p> '),(458,'1422045701000','Rappelling, Scrambling and basic knots.','zbrbflytmbkc','1443409189000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/zbrbflytmbkc/','Contact Event Organiser:  Naveen 9010143000','2015-09-27 06:00:00.000000','past',' Near Raidurgam Bus stop Mumbai Highway Road ','Hyderabad','in','Khajaguda',0,'2015-09-28 02:59:00.000000','<p>Khajaguda is quality outdoor climbing locations all varying in scenery, rock quality and texture. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/f/0/e/600_435483854.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/5/1/d/600_436790461.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Spend the day with our certified guide learning the basics of rock climbing and improving your top-roping skills and techniques.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/d/8/a/600_432191658.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/a/4/600_433495204.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/9/3/2/600_436762834.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor rock climbing experiences. </p> <p><b>Basic Rappelling and Scrambling:</b></p> <p>Time : 6am  - 11:30 am</p> <p>Tee shirt</p> <p>Tracks - No shorts please. </p> <p>Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>Cap advised</p> <p>Water 2 liter</p> <p>Snacks to Fill On to Climb On.</p> <p>Cost breakup: Rs. 100/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], Equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included) <br/><b>Gear Provided.</b>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p>Meet up at Raidurgam bus-stop  near Wells Fargo at 6:00 AM. </p> '),(459,'1443362058000','Star Gazing - Night camping @ Pocharam lake - Leisure face on 2nd October.','225649268','1444014025000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/225649268/',NULL,'2015-10-02 13:00:00.000000','past','Balanagar','Hyderabad','in','Balanagar X Roads',0,'2015-10-05 03:00:00.000000','<p>Pocharam lake is located in Medak district in the Indian state of Telangana. It is adjacent to Pocharam Forest &amp; Wildlife Sanctuary.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/4/d/600_442416685.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/1/0/1/600_442533025.jpeg\" /></p> <p>15 KM from Medak is Pocharam Lake with a dam, and Pocharam Wildlife sanctuary which used to be a hunting ground for the Nizam.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/6/f/600_442416719.jpeg\" /></p> <p>We would also be exploring the Medak Fort which is a citadel built on a hillock that provided as a vantage point for the Kakatiyan rulers in ancient India.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/9/1/600_442416753.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Date:</b> On Friday October 2nd 1p.m to Oct 3rd 11 a.m 1D/1N.</p> <p><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot and make the payment at meetup point.</p> <p><b>Distance: </b>110kms away from (3hrs drive)</p> <p><b>Meetup Point:</b> Balanagar X roads, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences: </b>Night Camping, Star gazing,</p> <p>a. Night camping</p> <p>b. Trekking.</p> <p>c. Bon-fire.</p> <p>d. Stargazing</p> <p>e. Haunted stories</p> <p>f. Fort Visit</p> <p>Plus Nature &amp; fun things to do.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b><br/>A pair of extra clothes if you go for swim. (optional)<br/>Sports shoes.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and 2 ltr water bottle.<br/>Caps/Raincoats(optional)<br/>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b><br/>Day 1 After reaching by 5pm, star gazing around the bon-fire; with camping, Dinner.<br/>Day 2 Morning we start the day lake trek enjoying the view and fun activities.</p> <p><b>Tariff: </b>Rs.300 per head - Limited seats only<br/>Includes:<br/>a. Camping gears (Tents etc..)<br/>b. Activities.</p> <p>Food and Transport <b>Not</b> included in the club fund. We can share it accordingly.<br/>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care will be taken to make your trip comfortable.</p> <p><b>Note: </b><i>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. Its just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b> Climb-On Naveen-</i>9010143000<i>, Climb-On Vamsi- </i>9700212029<i>.</i></p> '),(460,'1442681491000','Devils Circuit - Get Ready for the ultimate obstacle Viking Run.','225469725','1444636217000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/225469725/',NULL,'2015-10-11 09:00:00.000000','past','Chilukur Road','Hyderabad','in','Aziz Nagar Village, Near APPA (AP Police Academy) ',0,'2015-10-12 07:50:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/8/9/c/600_442114972.jpeg\" /></p> <p>After a fantastic response at our previous edition in December 2014, we are once again bringing our premier obstacle running property, the Devils Circuit to Hyderabad on the <b>11th of October</b>, Venue : <b>Near Appa Junction, ORR.</b> </p> <p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UEtBoYASwRA\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UEtBoYASwRA</a></p> <p>For the uninitiated however, Obstacle Running, as a format is quite different from the traditional formats of distance running, i.e. marathons, half-marathons, etc. &amp; essentially involves running across a challenging, rugged, outdoor track littered with military training - styled obstacles. Devils Circuit, in this context, is an amazingly unique experience for all its participants were Jumping over high walls, wading through a freezing pool of ice, crawling through muddy trenches underneath barbed wire &amp; much more; all around a custom-developed 5 km track is quite the norm. While promoting general fitness &amp; well-being, DC is also a great platform to promote team bonding among large groups &amp; organizations. Across its 6 previous editions, DC has attracted close to 15000 participants across age groups &amp; nationalities.</p> <p><b>What to expect:</b></p> <p>· A <b>5 kms</b> long running track interspersed with <b>15 cool challenging obstacles</b> that allow for a unique fun filled team building opportunity</p> <p>· A 3000 sq mtrs of <b>Expo Zone</b> playing host to <b>beach volleyball</b> and <b>football</b>, <b>Zumba</b>, <b>live performances</b>, <b>in house DJ</b>, <b>flash mobs</b>, <b>reebok Crossfit zone</b>, <b>Tug-of-war</b>, <b>Maruti Suzuki Swift fun Zone</b> and a variety of other entertainment absolutely free</p> <p>· A <b>free Goody bag</b> at the bib collection which would include a <b>Reebok play dry T-shirt</b>, a cool <b>DC bag</b>, a <b>headwrap</b> and a variety of other goodies and discount coupons worth more than <b>INR 4000/-</b></p> <p>· <b>One free beer</b> and <b>UNLIMITED Red Bulls</b> on the house for each participant <b>included</b> in the package.</p> <p>· A <b>Chunky Devils Circuit Medal</b> and <b>digital certificate</b> to all the participants who succeed to beat the Devil by completing the Run.</p> <p>· A host of new offers including a chance to win a <b>private workout session</b> with the Telugu Superstar <b>Ram Charan Teja</b>!</p> <p>· A fantastic day out with friends, family and colleagues. <b>One spectator</b> pass given absolutely free to each participant.</p> <p>· A range of <b>food</b> and <b>cool merchandise</b> to pick from.</p> <p>· Cool prizes like <b>Reebok Spartan kits</b>, <b>GoPro cameras</b>, <b>Led TVs</b>, <b>B-Twin Cycles, lots of other stuff</b> &amp; the <b>Grand Prize of a Maruti Suzuki Swift</b>.</p> <p>· Some really <b>cool</b> and <b>crazy photographs</b> of you while trying out the different    obstacles. We will have 30+ photographers stationed across the Circuit.</p> <p>· Last but not the least an experience of a lifetime.</p> <p>We have across the 6 editions hosted in the past, had very positive feedback from all corporates who have participated as a group. Some of these include Infosys, HSBC, Wipro, McKinsey, IGATE, PWC, Pepsi, Amazon, Snapdeal, Metlife and a host of Embassies and consulates.</p> <p>Reference links from earlier editions showcasing the amazing DC experience are attached here for your reference.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RmxdW-jmjuw\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RmxdW-jmjuw</a></p> <p>A truly international event.</p> <p><b>Charges:</b> INR 1500/- per person for non-members,</p> <p>          Avail great discount if you are Climb-On Hyderabad member.</p> <p>        Reach me @ Naveen 9010143000</p> <p>Join us : <b>www.meetup/Theclimbon/</b></p> <p>Like us:<b> <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/climbonhiker?ref=hl\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/climbonhiker?ref=hl\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.facebook.com/climbonhiker?ref=hl</a></a></b></p> '),(461,'1444746276000','Narsapur forest Exploration and Lots of Fun','226029149','1445218261000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/226029149/','Balanagar X roads, Bus stop towards Jeedimetla at 6am','2015-10-18 06:00:00.000000','past','Balanagar','Hyderabad','in','Balanagar X Roads',0,'2015-10-19 01:31:00.000000','<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Narsapur,_Medak_district\">Narsapur forest</a> is 45 KM north from Hyderabad in the Medak district. spread between Gummadidala and Narsapur towns. This forest spans over 30sq km and has a mini-ghat section, thick forest, a hill, a large lake, a good number of birds, butterflies, varied flora and fauna and our ancestors (monkeys)</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/6/3/600_443014659.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b></p> <p>6 am meting at balanagar and start to forest.</p> <p>Exploratory trek so nothing is planned. Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. We request all members to be socially responsible and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/6/c/600_443014668.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/7/9/600_443014681.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Instructions</b></p> <p>1) No smoking/alcohol and No litterin