o confirm your slot :)<br/>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p>Direct numbers : Climb-On Naveen-9010143000,                                                     Climb-On Ashim- 9000567089</p> '),(477,'1451892970000','Let\'s climb the rocks of Peerancheru','227822628','1452675931000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/227822628/','Meetup point at Morine bakery, nanal nagar X roads (Hand Symbol)','2016-01-09 06:00:00.000000','past','Near PBEL City, behind Shadan Medical College ','Hyderabad','in','Peerancheru',0,'2016-01-13 09:05:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/b/e/9/600_445635337.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Peeran Cheruvu is on the road to Gandipet and is an awesome location for rock climbing and bouldering.</p> <p>Itinerary: Exploratory trek so nothing is planned. Responsible Bouldering: Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. We request all members to be socially responsible and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology. </p> <p>5:45 AM : Assemble at meetup point at Morine bakery, nanal nagar X roads (Hand Symbol)<br/>6:00 AM : Start to Peerancheru<br/>6:15 AM : Reach the place and event begins<br/>****** Rock climbing*****<br/>********Bouldering******­**<br/>******Rappelling*******<br/>10:00 AM : Tired?? Let’s get back to our town. TaTa, Bubye :)</p> <p>Important Instructions:<br/>1) No smoking/alcohol and No littering <br/>2) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable<br/>3) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention.<br/>4) If you need any, bring it to the organizers notice.</p> <p>Things to bring: Wear Full track pants (avoid jeans). T-shirts(half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>Wear sport/trekking shoes only<br/>sun cap<br/>water bottles - 2x1 lit<br/>get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch on to climb on after and during the trek.<br/>Get your camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/5/e/600_445713374.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/5/4/f/600_435969551.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/8/0/e/600_435595310.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/c/0/1/600_445635361.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>RSVP Rules: We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP  \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case,  just its a humble request to please inform the Organiser a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i> </p> <p>Meeting Place: Mehdipatnam/Reti bowli @ Morine Bakery<br/>Transport: By personal Transport<br/>Cost: Rs 100 towards club.<br/>Contact Details: </p> <p>Suman: 99660 02025, </p> <p>Difficulty - Moderate.</p> <p>Please Be On time.</p> '),(478,'1452355171000','Sankranti Family Special Kites and Childhood Games','227962472','1452863868000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/227962472/','Sandeep 8008004360, Naveen 9010143000','2016-01-15 07:00:00.000000','past','Behind Ayappa Temple, Ammuguda','Secunderabad','in','Khoe Imam Zamin',0,'2016-01-15 13:17:00.000000','<p>Sankranti (Sanskrit: संक्रान्ति saṁkrānti) means transmigration of the Sun from one Rāshi (constellation of the zodiac in Indian astronomy) to the next. Hence, there are 12 Sankranthi in a year.Each Sankranti is marked as the beginning of a month in the sidereal solar calendars followed in Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Maharashtra, Tamil Nadu, Kerala, Odisha, Punjab, Gujarat. On the other hand, in the sidereal solar Bengali calendar and Assamese calendar, a Sankranti is marked as the end of each month and the day following as the beginning of a new month.</p> <p><b>Games </b>: </p> <p>• Kite flying</p> <p>• Gulli Danda</p> <p>• Stappu </p> <p>• 7-stones</p> <p>• Marbles </p> <p>• Gulel </p> <p>• Latto fight</p> <p>Checkout picture for more...  &gt;&gt; <a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/s/f8fl9z2dvfwo2fq/event.jpg?dl=0\">Games Games Games</a></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/8/6/c/600_445834924.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Lets all get along and enjoy this special day.</p> <p><b>What to Wear : </b></p> <p>• Tee shirt</p> <p>• Tracks / Shorts </p> <p>• Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>• Cap advised</p> <p>• Water 2 liter</p> <p>• Snacks to Fill On to Climb On.</p> <p><b>Cost breakup:</b> Rs. 200/- { Pay on spot }</p> <p><b>Note:</b> <i>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers : </b>Sandeep 8008004360, Naveen 9010143000</i></p> '),(479,'1452014281000','Pongal Spl Night Camping, BBQ in a Farm','227861220','1453177922000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/227861220/','Uppal Cross Road, Contact : Vamsi 9700212029 , Suvarna 8121637588','2016-01-15 15:30:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2016-01-19 04:32:00.000000','<p><b>Welcome to Leisure face of \"Climb On- Hyderabad\"</b>.</p> <p><b>We may play mud kabbadi so plz bring extra pair of clothes.</b></p> <p>You are seriously active when the sun is no more, If you love and enjoy exploring the great outdoors, adventures, fun in natural environment during NIGHTFALL\'S, the moon and the stars are just the perfect companion to a night walk. Same time enjoy meeting new friends with similar interest.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/8/5/4/600_445667188.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/8/3/1/600_445667153.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/8/6/0/600_445458528.jpeg\" /></p> <p>It just doesn\'t get much better than camping in Hyderabad outside with friends &amp; family - Food on the grill, under moon, games around you, enjoying the great outdoors, songs &amp; stories around the campfire, nothing could be better than this for a weekend.</p> <p>We hope it makes your experience with \'Climb on\' more enjoyable!</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/e/5/d/600_441564157.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Where: </b>Just across the border from Hyderabad Mothkur village near to Yadadri, this is one of our favorites. Got some excellent sites that are right on the shoreline of beautiful fields.</p> <p><b>Date: </b>On 15th Jan 3:00pm to 16th Jan 2016 10:00am. 1D/1N.<br/><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot, just join the waiting list and make the payment.<br/><b>Distance:</b> 90kms away from Uppal on Warangal Highway (2hrs drive)<br/><b>Meetup Point:</b> Uppal X roads, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences:</b></p> <p>a. Trekking.</p> <p>b. Music &amp; Bon-fire.</p> <p>c. BBQ</p> <p>d. Camping.</p> <p>e. Kite Flying<br/>Plus Nature &amp; fun things to do.</p> <p><b>Things to bring </b> :</p> <p><b>Packed Dinner very importent</b></p> <p>It\'s going to be cold so bring a solid <b>WARM Blanket </b><br/>Sports shoes, preferable old shoes.<br/>Extra pair if we play in mud or water.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and a water bottle.</p> <p>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Tariff: Rs.400 per head</b> - Limited seats only<br/>Includes<br/>. Camping gears<br/>. Activities<br/>. Campsite charges.</p> <p><b>Not included </b><b>Food &amp; Transport </b></p> <p><i>Note: <b>No booze, No intoxicants</b>, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. Its just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><b>Payment Details: On spot payment.</b></p> <p>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b> </i>Contact : Vamsi 9700212029, Suvarna 8121637588</p> '),(480,'1452869698000','Fitness - Cycling and Climbing - Gachibowli to ORR','228109162','1453017803000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228109162/','Sandeep 8008004360','2016-01-17 06:00:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-01-17 08:03:00.000000','<p>We will rent bicycles from HBC and event is open to all.</p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p>Please carry an original ID card like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept with us and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station before 5:30am </p> <p><b>Distance</b>: 15 KMS on way </p> <p><b>Duration</b>: about 3 hours</p> <p>Route:</p> <p>• Start at HBC at 6:00 am</p> <p>• Gachibowli circle</p> <p>• Microsoft / ISB road</p> <p>• Outer ring road</p> <p>• Movies towers hill  </p> <p>• Will do rock climbing  there and will return back... </p> <p>• Reach Bike station.</p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50 for 3 hours</p> '),(481,'1453173248000','Fitness - Sand Volleyball -  a Friday evening other than routine','228193270','1454436712000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228193270/','Suman 99660 02025','2016-01-22 18:00:00.000000','past','HITEC City','HYDERABAD','in','Raheja Mindspace,',0,'2016-02-02 18:11:00.000000','<p>Sand volleyball is a sport played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.  </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/7/2/600_446053426.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/8/0/600_446053440.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>6 pm meet at mind space and move to springs </p> <p>6.10 introduction and game rules</p> <p>6.15 warm up exercises </p> <p>6.30 game shuru </p> <p>8.30 End game and feedback </p> <p>8.45 Tata bye bye. </p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p>t-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please rsvp NO if you are not sure of attending the meet. </p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 200 per head ( include club fee + ground rent )</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Suman 99660 02025</p> '),(482,'1450438543000','Ride to Gandikota “The Hidden Grand Canyon of India”: 23rd and 24th Jan 2016','227495954','1453862376000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/227495954/','Call Rohith: 9676722155; Arvind: 9640431351','2016-01-23 05:00:00.000000','past','Gachibowli, Hyderabad. ','Hyderabad','in','Indira Nagar',0,'2016-01-27 02:39:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/8/b/4/600_445483188.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><i><br/></i></b></p> <p>If you have ever visited America’s famous Grand Canyon in Colorado River, Gandikota, the Grand Canyon of India would remind you of that again. It is no lesser than “The Grand Canyon” in providing you the excitement of nature’s beauty. It is situated near Jammalamagudu in Erramalai hills on the right bank of the river Pennar in Kadapa district of Andhra Pradesh.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/2/6/5/600_445197957.jpeg\" /></p> <p>It is appx 350 Kms from Hyderabad. To most of the travelers, it is still a hidden and unexplored place. Gandikota gets its name from the word ‘Gandi’ which means gorge and kota means fort in Telugu. There is a fort located right at the edge of this gorge. The gorge formation is such that the Pennar River flows about 90 metres below on the western and northern sides. The Valley has a beautiful landscape and lush forests, and is blessed with many natural resources. Trekking in the valley and experience the wild beauty of nature is very mesmerizing.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/2/7/4/600_445197972.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><i># Guys, please share your mobile number with us either through an option in the answer section inside the RSVP link (preferred) or messages it to the organizers (Rohith: 9676722155; Arvind: 9640431351). Your contact details will be visible to the organizers only.</i></b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Meet-up point: </b>5:00 AM on Saturday 23rd Jan at Mehdipatnam Morine Bakery</p> <p><b>Mode of transport: </b>Bike/car. Please coordinate with other members for Bike/Car pooling, if required.</p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p><b>Day 1 (Saturday): </b></p> <p>04:30AM : At meet Up point.</p> <p>05:00AM sharp -Start from Hyderabad<br/>01:00 PM -Reach Yaganti and have lunch</p> <p>02:00 PM -Reach Gandikota and food supplies<br/>04:00 PM –Forest exploration</p> <p>07:00 pm -Halt and pitch tents for overnight camping at suitable place having amazing landscape.<br/>08:00 PM- 1:00 AM – Night <i>campfire cooking</i></p> <p><b>Day 2 (Sunday)*</b><br/>05:00 AM – Good morning</p> <p>06:00 AM - 12 PM - Visit the Gandikota fort, Belum caves, Gorges, and explore the Penna River. We may also do <i>climbing/scrambling, if time allows. </i></p> <p>12:00 PM - Lunch and vote of thanks<br/>01:00 PM - Back to Hyderabad</p> <p>9:00 PM – Hello Hyderabad</p> <p><i> *We may have a little variation in the plan, based on the situations.</i></p> <p><b><i>Trekking outfit and a few things to bring: </i></b></p> <p>· One full length track pant or loose trouser (avoid Jeans); Two T-shirts - No bright colored.</p> <p>· A rucksack or a hiking bag to keep all the things with a sleeping bag or a bed-sheet/ blanket.</p> <p>· Trekking or sport shoes used at least ones with 2 pairs of socks.</p> <p>· Toiletries (Brush, tooth paste, soap, shampoo etc).</p> <p>· Hat or cap, sun screen/sun glasses.</p> <p>· At-least 3 water bottles.</p> <p>· Electrol /glucose/energy bars/chocolates etc.</p> <p>· Torch or headlight with extra spare batteries.</p> <p>· Any medications physician prescribed.</p> <p>· Two emergency notes with your name, address, emergency contact number.</p> <p>· Your photo Id with a xerox copy of it.</p> <p>· And, of-course a good and positive mood</p> <p><b>Instructions</b></p> <p>· No smoking, alcohol, littering, and no pollution of water.</p> <p>· This is not a luxury trip, but out most care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</p> <p>· Girls and boys accommodation in separate tents</p> <p>· Food will be mostly vegetarian</p> <p>· We carry basic First Aid; if you need anything you can ask the organizers.</p> <p>· If you can\'t swim please avoid going deep into the water</p> <p>· This trip is organized only for serious climbers, the one who have done few treks before.</p> <p>· This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care will be taken to make your trip comfortable</p> <p><b>Tariff: </b>Rs.400 per head, which includes Rs.300 as club fund for camping tents, trekking activities, first-Aid etc. and Rs 100 as miscellaneous charges.</p> <p><b>Food and Transport </b>(car/bike pooling in case we all have sufficient cars) not included in the club fund.We can share it accordingly. <b>In case, we do not have sufficient cars with participants, we will hire a Bus and will share the charges.</b></p> <p><b>Payment Details</b>: I will send u a link through whatsap, for that Guys plz whatsap Arvind (9640431351) from ur number <b>saying \"<i>HI I WANT TO JOIN 31st EVENT SEND ME THE PAYMENT LINK</i>\" </b>to confirm your spot.</p> <p>We look forward to having fun!</p> <p>For any more questions, please reach out to the organizers of the event.</p> <p><b>Rohith:</b> 9676722155; <b>Arvind:</b> 9640431351</p> '),(483,'1445786814000','Rock climbing and hiking at Khajaguda','zllsllyvcbgc','1453785682000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/zllsllyvcbgc/','Contact Event Organiser:  Naveen 9010143000','2016-01-24 06:00:00.000000','past',' Near Raidurgam Bus stop Mumbai Highway Road ','Hyderabad','in','Khajaguda',0,'2016-01-26 05:21:00.000000','<p>Khajaguda is quality outdoor climbing locations all varying in scenery, rock quality and texture. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/f/0/e/600_435483854.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/5/1/d/600_436790461.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Spend the day with our certified guide learning the basics of rock climbing and improving your top-roping skills and techniques.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/d/8/a/600_432191658.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/a/4/600_433495204.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/9/3/2/600_436762834.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor rock climbing experiences. </p> <p><b>Basic Rappelling and Scrambling:</b></p> <p>Time : 6am  - 11:30 am</p> <p>Tee shirt</p> <p>Tracks - No shorts please. </p> <p>Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>Cap advised</p> <p>Water 2 liter</p> <p>Snacks to Fill On to Climb On.</p> <p>Cost breakup: Rs. 100/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], Equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included) <br/><b>Gear Provided.</b>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p>Meet up at Raidurgam bus-stop  near Wells Fargo at 6:00 AM. </p> '),(484,'1453133213000','Go karting, Paintball and Laser Combat at Runway 9','228177358','1453829308000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228177358/','Arvind Semwal 9640431351','2016-01-26 16:00:00.000000','past','Kompally','Hyderabad','in','Runway 9',0,'2016-01-26 17:28:00.000000','<p>Guys, lets meet up on Republic day for Paintball, Go karting, and Laser Combat at <b>Runway 9, Kompally</b></p> <p><b>Timing:</b> 4:00 to7:00 PM, 26th Jan, 2016</p> <p><b>Meetup point: Runway 9</b>, 5-115, Mohan Reddy Commercial Complex, Medchal Road, Kompally, Hyderabad.</p> <p><b>Total Cost: </b>Rs. 800 (Rs. 40 Club fee + Rs.60 Runway 9 entry fee  + Rs. 500 for [Paintball and Go karting] Combo + Rs. 200 for laser combat). Pay at spot.</p> <p><b> Cost break up<br/></b></p> <p><b>1-Go karting</b></p> <p>A go-kart is a small four-wheeled vehicle. Go-karts come in all shapes and forms, from motorless models to high-powered racing machines, some, like Superkarts, being able to beat racing cars on long circuits.</p> <p><b>Cost for </b><b>go Karting: </b> Rs. 260/4 lasps (Each laps: 700 mts);</p> <p><b>2-Paintball:</b></p> <p>Paintball is a game in which players compete, in teams or individually, to eliminate opponents by tagging them with capsules containing water-soluble dye and featuring a gelatin outer shell (referred to as paintballs) propelled from a device called a paintball marker (commonly referred to as a paintball gun). Paintballs are composed of a non-toxic, biodegradable, water-soluble polymer. The game is regularly played at a sporting level with organized competition involving major tournaments, professional teams, and players</p> <p><b>Cost for </b><b>Paint Ball:  Rs. 400/40 balls; Go-karting with Laser combat combo (Rs. 500)</b></p> <p><b>3-Laser combat:</b></p> <p>Laser tag is a team or individual sport or recreational activity where players attempt to score points by tagging targets, typically with a hand-held infrared-emitting targeting device. Infrared-sensitive targets are commonly worn by each player and are sometimes integrated within the arena in which the game is played. Laser tag is popular with a wide range of ages. When compared to paintball, laser tag is painless because it uses no physical projectiles</p> <p><b>Cost for </b><b>laser combat: </b> Rs. 200/9 life</p> '),(485,'1452405015000','Fun at Ameenpur Lake - Hiking / Bouldering','227976327','1454172811000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/227976327/',NULL,'2016-01-30 06:00:00.000000','past','Ameenpur Village ','Hyderabad','in','Ameenpur Lake',0,'2016-01-30 16:53:00.000000','<p><b>LOCATION </b>: </p> <p>Ameenpur Lake is located approximately 4.5 km from miyapur circle. Ameenpur Lake have many small and big boulders. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/9/d/a/600_444134810.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/9/7/b/600_444134715.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/9/7/5/600_444134709.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/9/6/c/600_444134700.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>SPECIAL NOTE</b>: </p> <p>• No littering, No Sound Pollution. No Smoking at this natural place.</p> <p><b>GETTING READY</b>: </p> <p>• Full track pants and T-shirts (half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>• Sun cap</p> <p>• 2 water bottles <b>must</b>. </p> <p>• Get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch on after and during the trek and making some good friends ;)</p> <p>• Eat something before trek [ <b>recommended </b>]</p> <p>• Camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p>• Kids should be accompanied by Parent or Guardian</p> <p><b>MEETING POINT</b>: </p> <p>In front of BHEL Gate @ 6:00 AM.</p> <p>6:00 - Start from BHEL Gate</p> <p>6:30 - Reach venue, start warm up</p> <p>6:30 - 9:00 - Hiking, scrambling activity</p> <p>9:30 - Snacks / BFast [ Bring your own ] </p> <p>10:00 - Bye Bye friends</p> <p><b>Cost breakup: </b>Rs. 100/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], Equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(<b>Fuel, food, water is not included</b>) </p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/227976327/\">Click here to pay online</a></p> <p><b>COMMUNICATION: </b></p> <p><b>Sandeep</b>@ 800 800 4360</p> '),(486,'1453374790000','RIDE to beautiful Laknavaram Lake - Hyd- Aler - Kolanpaka - Hyd on 31st Jan','228252382','1454307283000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228252382/','Call Rohith 9676722155','2016-01-31 06:00:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2016-02-01 06:14:00.000000','<p>You can\'t party all the time - especially in January!</p> <p>Kolanapaka belongs to<b> Aler mandal</b>  of Nalgonda Dt, TS.</p> <p>Famous for Jain Temple, Beautiful historic (Sri Someshwara Temple) village with lots of small temples and scriptures.<br/>Not only that, it has Veera Narayana temple, Sai temple, Goddes Renuka temple and small Anjaneya temples. It is located in Aler mandal, Nalgonda district. It is about 75 km away from Hyderabad. The people come from mostly Maharasta, Rajastan, Gujarath states to visit famous jain temple. Karnataka and our state people come to visit Sri Someshwara temple.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/6/0/600_446103424.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/5/c/600_446103420.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Laknavaram Lake</b> is located in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Govindaraopet\">Govindaraopet mandal</a>, about 80km from <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warangal\">Warangal</a>,<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telangana\">Telangana</a>. It is spread over an area of 10,000 acres and holds about 2.135 tmcft of water. It irrigates over 3,500 acres of land. It was build by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kakatiya\">Kakatiya</a> kings.It has about 13 islands in it and has a 160 metres long hanging bridge, which connects three islands. It is surrounded by a thick deciduous forest and it is a very popular tourist spot</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/f/0/e/600_446308430.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/6/6/600_446103430.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/6/9/600_446103433.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>* Itinerary:</b></p> <p>6:00am Meetup at Uppal Cross roads</p> <p>9:00am Break for breakfast in Aler</p> <p>9:30am visit 800 years old Jain temple and 1200 years old Archaeological monuments.  </p> <p>11:00am start to Laknawaram </p> <p>1:00pm lunch</p> <p>2:00pm visit laknawaran</p> <p>4:00pm start back to hyderabad</p> <p>6:30pm reach hyderabd</p> <p>                Bubye...........</p> <p><b>* What to wear:</b></p> <p>• Wear Shoes</p> <p>• Wear any dress comfortable to you</p> <p>• One extra pair of dress </p> <p>• Towel</p> <p>• As we will be starting early, wear something to keep you warm.</p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>* What to bring:</b></p> <p>• Water bottles - 2 x 1 litres</p> <p>• Hat or cap as it will be hot afternoons</p> <p>• Electrol or glucose</p> <p>• Camera</p> <p>• Any medications physician prescribed</p> <p>• Loads of energy.</p> <p><b>Guidelines:</b> This is a historical place . No venturing towards steep cliff drops .</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Rohith 9676722155</p> <p><b>Difficulty :</b> Easy</p> <p><b>Transport:</b> Personal Vehicles, if got no self commute,  will try for pooling and petrol cost will be shared.</p> <p>PLEASE ANSWER ALL THE QUESTIONS. IF YOU DO NOT WE WILL NOT BE ABLE TO WAIT FOR YOU AND YOUR RSVP WILL BE CONSIDERED VOID.</p> <p><b>Damages:</b> 200 towards club includes club fund and 2 halts chai pani on our way to ride.</p> '),(487,'1453494521000','HAMPI on Feb Friday eve. 5th - 8th Monday Morning','228288084','1454900480000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228288084/','Vamsi Climb On : 9700212029, Right :9676722155','2016-02-05 21:00:00.000000','past','Nampally','Hyderabad','in','Hyderabad Railway Station at Nampally',0,'2016-02-08 03:01:00.000000','<p><b>Organisers Experience: </b><br/>A backpacker\'s Paradise. A place worth filling few pages on your travel diary.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/4/9/2/600_446129842.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>About: </b></p> <p>Hampi, once the capital of the Vijayanagar Empire and a UNESCO World Heritage Site today,lies scattered over a landscape that leaves you spellbound: heaps of giant boulders perch precariously over miles of undulating terrain, their rusty hues offset by jade-green palm groves, banana plantations and paddy fields, while the azure sky painted with fluffy white cirrus adds to the magical atmosphere. </p> <p>               Vast stretches of boulder-strewn hills make the backdrop of Hampi unique. Dotted around the hills and valleys are 500 plus monuments. Among them are beautiful temples, basements of palaces, remains of aquatic structures, ancient market streets, royal pavilions, bastions, royal platforms, treasury buildings.., the list is practically endless. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/4/8/b/600_446129835.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Outline:</b></p> <p>Day 1 : Saturday Morning reach Hampi.<br/>Day 2 : Explore, Start back by evening and reach hyd by Monday Morning. </p> <p><b>Indepth:</b><br/>Day 0 : Friday evening.<br/>Leave from Hyd to Hoospet.</p> <p>Day 1 &amp; 2: Reach Hampi and check into Homestay / Guesthouse. After breakfast and some rest we leave for our 1st day of our Hampi Tour by 9 a.m. First stop is the Hampi Bazaar, Virupaksha Temple, Hemkuntha Hilltop and Sasivekalu Gnesha. Post lunch we proceed to Monolithic Bull, Achyuta Raya’s Temple, Watch Towers, Guard\'s Quarters, Hazara Rama Temple, Elephant\'s Stables, King\'s Audience Hall, King\'s Palace, Throne Platform, Octagonal Water Pavillion, Octagonal Bath, Chandrasekhara Temple starting from Pattabhi Rama Temple via the Domed Gate.<br/>-Evening we explore the riverside ruins and the gorge of the Tungabhadra River. One can take a Coracle Ride on the River in the evening for a relaxing and fun experience. Back to the guesthouse after sunset.<br/>--Of Course we not bound to time and day 2 is for exploring hampi and <i>understand why its called Backpackers paradise on a individual note.</i><br/>Evening pack our stuff, Dine and start back to our town.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts.</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. - Sleeping bag or thick blanket and a proper rucksack (backpack) (both are must) and some plastic covers.</p> <p>- Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p>- Some snacks to climb on.</p> <p>- Torch light is must.</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b><br/><i>Note:</i> No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun.</p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.<br/>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</p> <p><b>Damages: </b><br/>2600/- Will share the cost if it is more or less.<br/>[ Food is excluded]</p> <p><b>Payment Details:</b> You will be in waiting list unless you make the payment. Account Details :<br/>Account Name : ASHIM KUMAR MAJUMDAR<br/>Account No : 627501513451<br/>Bank : ICICI<br/>Branch Name : Gachibowli<br/>IFSC Code : icic0001114</p> <p>Once payment is transferred, request you to add your transaction ID to comments below, we will confirm your slot.<br/>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> '),(488,'1453880407000','Ride to Bhongir Fort and Hike 6th Feb Sat','228394368','1454779323000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228394368/','Near police station','2016-02-06 06:00:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2016-02-06 17:22:00.000000','<p><b>About Place: </b>Bhongir or Bhongiri or Bhuvanagiri is a small town about 40km from uppal Hyderabad on the way to Warangal. The fort is on top of a small hill - in fact the hill is a monolith - a huge rock. The surrounding areas being flat, the hill affords a grand view of the vistas beyond.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/b/3/1/600_431903345.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/6/c/2/600_433110402.jpeg\" /></p> <p>What do we plan to do :Hiking, Fort climbing and collecting memories that will last a lifetime</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/7/0/7/600_433110471.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/f/5/b/600_446532123.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/7/1/5/600_433110485.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p>6:00am: Meetup at Uppal X Road (near Uppal Police Station)</p> <p>Start towards Bhongir</p> <p>7:00 Reach Bhongir and start climbing<br/>8:00 Reach hill top with an magnificent overview of horizon<br/>11:30 Start descending down.<br/>12:00 Start back to Hyderabad</p> <p><b>What to wear:</b></p> <p>Wear Shoes with \"lots\" of grip.</p> <p>• Wear anything comfortable, preferably tracks and tees.</p> <p>• As we will be starting early, wear something to keep you warm.</p> <p>• What to bring:</p> <p>• Water bottles - 2 x 1 litres</p> <p>• Hat or cap as it will be hot afternoons</p> <p>• Electrol or glucose</p> <p>• Camera</p> <p>• Any medications physician prescribed</p> <p>• Loads of energy.</p> <p><b>Costs </b>: Rs 100 Towards Club fund</p> <p><b>Guidelines</b>: This is a historical place . No venturing towards steep cliff drops .</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Vamsi 9700212029</p> <p><b>Difficulty </b>: Easy</p> <p>Transport: Personal Vehicles If possible there will be pool and petrol cost will be shared</p> <p><b>PLEASE ANSWER ALL THE QUESTIONS. IF YOU DO NOT WE WILL NOT BE ABLE TO WAIT FOR YOU AND YOUR RSVP WILL BE CONSIDERED VOID.</b></p> '),(489,'1452405916000','Trekking/ Swimming/Caving at Khilla Ghanpur Fort','227976454','1454945224000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/227976454/','Sandeep 8008004360','2016-02-07 06:00:00.000000','past','Mahaboob Nagar','Hyderabad','in','Khilla Ghanpur Fort',0,'2016-02-08 15:27:00.000000','<p>Khilla Ghanpur or Ghanpur, Mahbubnagar district was ruled by Recharla, Malyala and Gona dynasties in 13th century.Recharla, Gona and Malyala Dynasty Kings were the Feudatores of Kakatiya Kings. Khilla Ghanpur has a fort and a lake (known as Ganapa Samudram) built during Kakatiya dynasty rule. The lake, Ganapa Samudram, was constructed by the King Malyala Gunda Dandadeeshudu (also known as Malyala Gundanna) during Rudrama Devi’s rule. Malyala Gunda Dandadeeshudu married Gona Budda Reddy’s daughter.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/2/f/600_445773327.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/3/7/600_445773335.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary :</b></p> <p>06:00 : Assemble at Meeting Point- Gachibowli X Road ( will share details based on route )<br/>06:10 : Start to Ghanpur Fort<br/>08:00 : Breakfast and packed Lunch<br/>09:00 : Reach Ghanpur Fort and start hiking<br/>17:00 : Complete Trek<br/>17:30 : Start to hyderabad<br/>19:30 : Tata bye bye</p> <p><b>What to Wear :</b> </p> <p>• Tee shirt - prefer full sleeves</p> <p>• Tracks / Shorts </p> <p>• Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>• Cap advised</p> <p>• Water 2-3 liter</p> <p>• Snacks to Fill On to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Cost breakup :</b> Rs. 200/- as club fee ( for equipments / know-how / first aid kit ). Please note Food / Transport expenses will be shared equally as we will go using private vehicles.  </p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/227976454/\">Click here to pay online</a></p> <p><b>Contact :</b></p> <p>Sandeep 8008004360</p> '),(490,'1452870888000','Night Camping & Papikondalu Boat Trip','228109518','1455692672000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228109518/','Climb-On Naveen-9010143000,  Climb-On Pravallika - 77025 23099','2016-02-12 20:30:00.000000','past','west godavari','Hyderabad','in','papikondalu',0,'2016-02-17 07:04:00.000000','<p>One of the most popular weekend leisure getaway into the beauty of papi kondalu along with a boat ride in the beautiful River Godavari and camping at the famous bamboo huts...</p> <p>One of the most popular destinations in AP is a treat and a great getaway into nature.</p> <p>Papi Kondalu is a hill in Godavari District.</p> <p>The scenery, including the waterfalls at Munivaatam, and the peaceful atmosphere at this tribal area make this area a tourist attraction. . The village Peranta palli is in this area.</p> <p>The most popular route to reach Papi kondalu is through Rajahmundry of East Godavari district by boat. </p> <p>Papi kondalu has a wide varieties of natural vegetation and wildlife.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/9/5/0/600_446058768.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/1/4/9/600_445913577.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>BAMBOO HUTS</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/9/5/7/600_446058775.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/0/d/b/600_445913467.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>ITINERARY</b></p> <p><b>Friday </b>: Train to Rajahmundry</p> <p><b>Saturday </b>- 1st Day <br/>7:30 AM Pick up from Rajahmundry Railway Station.  Fresh up in a hotel and then get into hired vehicle to the riverside.</p> <p>9.00 AM Check in to Boat. Breakfast in the Boat and then start the boat ride.</p> <p>10.00 AM Reach Gandi Pochamma Temple situated on bank of River Godavari, darshan <br/>1.00 PM Vegetarian lunch in the Boat while on journey. <br/>2.00 PM Reach Papi kondalu.</p> <p>3.00 PM Reaches Peranta palli Tribal Village. Local sight seeing then journey towards Camp site <br/>4.30 PM Reaches Bamboo huts situated on the bank of River Godavari at Koruturu Tribal Village of Khammam district. Check out of Boat, evening snacks and free time at Camp site.</p> <p>Night Dinner and accommodation in huts with camp fire.</p> <p><b>Sunday </b>- 2nd Day <br/>6.00 AM Local sight seeing by walk in the Forest area with guide. Bathing in PAMALERU wagu situated in between Papikondalu, is a memorable experience. <br/>9.00 AM Breakfast will be provided at camping site and local sight seeing. <br/>2.00 PM Lunch  &amp;</p> <p>3.00 pm Get into the boat for the return journey. <br/>6.30 PM Reaches Pattiseema revu <br/>7.00 PM  Get into our vehicle to reach Rajahmundry railway station.  Have dinner and get into the train to Hyderabad.</p> <p>Monday 8 AM- Reach Hyderabad.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/9/6/a/600_446058794.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/9/7/a/600_446058810.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Very Important :</b></p> <p>No SMOKING and No ALCOHOL , No littering, NO pollution of water </p> <p>Food will be mostly vegetarian. </p> <p>Organizer will carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers </p> <p><b>Cost Breakup -  </b><b>Rs.3300/-  </b></p> <p>The cost includes Hyd- Rajahmundry-Hyd SL Train tickets, local transport, boat ride, food on Saturday and Sunday, Club Fees. Anything more or less will be shared.</p> <p>Payment Details: You will be in waiting list unless you make the payment. </p> <p><b>Account Details : </b><br/>Account Name : ASHIM KUMAR MAJUMDAR <br/>Account No : 627501513451 <br/>Bank : ICICI <br/>Branch Name : Gachibowli <br/>IFSC Code : icic0001114</p> <p>Add yourself to Waiting list and You will be moved to YES list after receiving the payment on First come First Serve basis.</p> <p><b>Contacts </b>- Climb-On Naveen-9010143000,  Climb-On Pravallika - 77025 23099</p> '),(491,'1453881438000','Let\'s climb the rocks of Peerancheru with Basic Rappling 14th Feb','228394508','1455478307000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228394508/','Meetup point at Morine bakery, nanal nagar X roads (Hand Symbol)','2016-02-14 06:00:00.000000','past','Near PBEL City, behind Shadan Medical College ','Hyderabad','in','Peerancheru',0,'2016-02-14 19:31:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/b/e/9/600_445635337.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Peeran Cheruvu is on the road to Gandipet and is an awesome location for rock climbing and bouldering.</p> <p>Itinerary: Exploratory trek so nothing is planned. Responsible Bouldering: Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. We request all members to be socially responsible and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology.</p> <p>6:00AM : Assemble at meetup point at Morine bakery, nanal nagar X roads (Hand Symbol)<br/>6:15 AM : Start to Peerancheru<br/>6:30AM : Reach the place and event begins<br/>****** Rock climbing*****<br/>********Bouldering******­**<br/>******Rappelling*******<br/>12:00 PM : Tired?? Let’s get back to our town. TaTa, Bubye :)</p> <p>Important Instructions:<br/>1) No smoking/alcohol and No littering<br/>2) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable<br/>3) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention.<br/>4) If you need any, bring it to the organizers notice.</p> <p>Things to bring: Wear Full track pants (avoid jeans). T-shirts(half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>Wear sport/trekking shoes only<br/>sun cap<br/>water bottles - 2x1 lit<br/>get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch on to climb on after and during the trek.<br/>Get your camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/5/e/600_445713374.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/5/4/f/600_435969551.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/8/0/e/600_435595310.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/c/0/1/600_445635361.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>RSVP Rules: We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case, just its a humble request to please inform the Organiser a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i></p> <p>Meeting Place: Mehdipatnam/Reti bowli @ Morine Bakery<br/>Transport: By personal Transport<br/>Cost: Rs 100 towards club.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228394508/\">Click here to pay online</a></p> <p>Contact Details: Suman 9966002025</p> <p>Difficulty - Moderate.</p> <p>Please Be On time.</p> '),(492,'1453490948000','Into the lap of nature, trek to beaches in Gokarna on Friday eve. Feb 19 - 22','228286428','1456980480000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228286428/','Rohit  9676722155, Naveen Kodela 9010143000','2016-02-19 15:00:00.000000','past','Secunderabad','Hyderabad','in','Secunderabad Railway Station',0,'2016-03-03 04:48:00.000000','<p><b>Organiser\'s Experience:</b></p> <p>Cosseted in the lap of nature, the beaches in <b>Gokarna</b> are pristine and make for a riveting holiday experience. Add the fun and excitement of trekking along the beach and unfold the beauty of this vicinity.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/1/1/f/600_446128959.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Sathodi Falls:-</b></p> <p>The Sathodi Falls are formed by several streams near the Kallaramarane Ghat, 32 km from Yellapur. The falls are about 15 meters in height. After flowing from the waterfall the streams then flow into the backwaters of the Kodasalli Dam, into the Kali River. Owing to the picturesque view, the place is fondly called “Mini Niagara”. These falls form an integral part of the Ganeshgudi forest range.</p> <p><b>About:</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/b/3/9/600_446332025.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Gokarna is famous for its beautiful beaches and landscapes. The main beaches in Gokarna are the Gokarna beach, Kudle Beach, Om Beach, Half moon Beach and Paradise Beach (also known as Full moon). The Gokarna beach forms the coast of the town while the other four beaches lie to the south of Gokarna. Kudle and Om are around 6 km from Gokarna town along a muddy hill; they are accessible by rickshaw or foot. Half moon and Paradise are beyond Om beach and are accessible only by foot or boat. Om beach is named so because it is shaped like the auspicious ॐ [Om] symbol. Om beach is the only naturally Om shaped beach. Two other beaches - Paradise and Half Moon - are smaller and remote beaches.</p> <p><b>Outline:</b><br/>Day 1 : Beach Trekking along the coastline from Gokarna Beach to Paradise Beach [ 12 km ]<br/>Day 2 : sathodi falls</p> <p><b>Indepth:</b><br/>Friday 3pm : Kacheguda train to Hubli<br/>Sat 9am : Hubli station to Gokarna.<br/>Sat 12pm : Lunch &amp; Beach Trek from Gokarna - Om beach - Half Moon - Paradise / Gokarna (12km Approx)<br/>Sat 8pm : Stay in Gokarna<br/>[Accommodation is separate in tents for Men and woman]<br/>Sun 4am : Wakeup call<br/>Sun 5am : Gokarna to sathodi water falls<br/>Sun 7 am : Trekking in sathodi Falls<br/>Sun 12 noon : sathodi Falls to hubli Station.<br/>Sun 4pm: Train to reach hyd.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts, at the beach, a pair of shorts would be a good.</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. - Sleeping bag or thick blanket and a proper rucksack (backpack) (both are must) and some plastic covers</p> <p>- Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p>- some snacks to climb on.</p> <p>- Torch light is must.</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b><br/>Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun.</p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.<br/>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</p> <p><b>Damages:</b><br/>2900 /- Will share the cost if it is more or less.<br/>[ Food is excluded]</p> <p><b>Payment Details:</b> You will be in waiting list unless you make the payment.</p> <p>Account Details : -<br/>Account Name : ASHIM KUMAR MAJUMDAR<br/>Account No : 627501513451<br/>Bank : ICICI<br/>Branch Name : Gachibowli<br/>IFSC Code : icic0001114</p> <p>Once payment is transferred, request you to add your transaction ID to comments below, we will confirm your slot.<br/>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> '),(493,'1456207810000','Fitness - Cycling and Climbing - Gachibowli to ORR','229062353','1456600933000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229062353/','ClimbOn Rohit - 96767 22155 & Pallavi-7674070563','2016-02-27 05:30:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-02-27 19:22:00.000000','<p>We will rent bicycles from HBC and event is open to all.</p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p>Please carry an original ID card like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept with us and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station before 5:30am </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/f/3/5/600_447177141.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Distance</b>: 15 KMS on way </p> <p><b>Duration</b>: about 3 hours</p> <p><b>Route</b>:</p> <p>• Start at HBC at 6:00 am</p> <p>• Gachibowli circle</p> <p>• Microsoft / ISB road</p> <p>• Outer ring road</p> <p>• Movies towers hill  </p> <p>• Will do rock climbing  there and will return back... </p> <p>• Reach Bike station.</p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One Registration Fee Rs 100/-</p> '),(494,'1456922783000','Fitness Boot Camp for Kedarnath Himalaya Winter Trek','229282234','1457149004000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229282234/','Arvind: 9640431351; Naveen: 9010143000)','2016-03-05 05:30:00.000000','past','Mumbai Highway road','Hyderabad','in','Raidurgam stop Khajaguda. ',0,'2016-03-05 03:36:00.000000','<p>ClimbOn is excited to organize a 44 km winter trek to Kedarnath Himalaya, which is situated at the altitude of 12000 Ft above sea level. This trek is being organized in association with NEHRU INSTITUTE OF MOUNTAINEERING (NIM), UTTARKASHI from 23rd- 30th March 2016 (Meetup page link: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228129742/\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228129742/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228129742/</a></a>).</p> <p>We are organizing a <b><i>FITNESS BOOT CAMP  </i></b>to have the participants fit and boosting their fitness/endurance for the trek. In addition, participants can also get your queries answered from event hosts regarding the trek.</p> <p><b><i>Who should attend this FITNESS BOOT CAMP?</i></b></p> <p>Those who have RSVPed or interested to join Kedarnath trekking event (23rd March to 30th March 2016).</p> <p><b><i>What this  FITNESS BOOT CAMP covers?</i></b></p> <p>It include briefing about the trip, trekking, running, and cardiovascular &amp; general body workout, which will improve the endurance level for the trekking at high altitude.</p> <p><b><i>Meeting Point:</i> </b>Rai Durgam Bus Stop.<b> Opposite to Food Nation Restaurant</b></p> <p><b><i>Time:</i> </b>5:30 AM at Rai Durgam Bus Stop; 6:00 AM – 8:30 AM at Khajaguda<b>.(Please be ON time)</b></p> <p><b><i>Instructions:</i></b></p> <p>Please bring trekking/sports shoes with a good grip</p> <p>Please wear track pant and T shirt (no jeans please)</p> <p>Please bring at least 2 Litters of water with you.</p> <p>Electrol /glucose/energy bars/chocolates etc.</p> <p><b>Cost: </b>Rs.50 as club fee (stationary charges, first aid, etc.).Those who have confirmed their seat for Kedarnath trip, this is  exempted.</p> <p><b>For any more questions, please reach out to event hosts (Arvind: 9640431351; Naveen: 9010143000)</b></p> '),(495,'1454963015000','Spiritual Adventure - Night Camping @ Kadthal Pyramid','228708684','1457446895000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228708684/','Rohith- 9676722155','2016-03-05 15:00:00.000000','past','Nanal nagar X roads','Hyderabad','in','Morine bakery',0,'2016-03-08 14:21:00.000000','<p><b>Welcome to Leisure face of \"Climb On- Hyderabad\"</b>.</p> <p><b>Kadthal</b> is a village in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amangal\">Amangal</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tehsil\">Mandal</a> in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahbubnagar\">Mahbubnagar</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/District\">District</a> in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telangana\">Telangana</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a>.</p> <p>Pyramid:-</p> <p>A <b>pyramid</b> is a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonbuilding_structure\">structure</a> whose outer surfaces are triangular and converge to a single point at the top, making the shape roughly a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyramid_(geometry)\">pyramid in the geometric sense</a>. The base of a pyramid can be trilateral, quadrilateral, or any <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polygon\">polygon</a> shape, meaning that a pyramid has at least three outer triangular surfaces (at least four <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Face_(geometry)\">faces</a> including the base). The <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_pyramid\">square pyramid</a>, with square base and four triangular outer surfaces, is a common version.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/f/c/7/600_446684999.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/f/c/d/600_446685005.jpeg\" /></p> <p>It just doesn\'t get much better than camping in Hyderabad outside with friends &amp; family - Food on the grill, under moon, games around you, enjoying the great outdoors, songs &amp; stories around the camp fire, nothing could be better than this for a weekend.</p> <p>We hope it makes your experience with \'Climb on\' more enjoyable!</p> <p><b>Where: </b>Just across the border from Hyderabad , this is one of our favourites. Got some excellent sites that are right on the shoreline of beautiful fields.</p> <p><b>When:</b></p> <p><b>Date: </b>On 5th march 3:00pm to 6th march 2016 1:00pm. 1D/1N.<br/><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot, just join the waiting list and make the payment.<br/><b>Distance:</b> 75kms away from Hyderabad on bangalore Highway (2hrs drive)<br/><b>Meetup Point:</b> Morine bakery, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences:</b></p> <p><b>a.  Camping </b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/d/3/7/600_446976151.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>b. Forest exploration</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/0/4/8/600_446685128.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>c. Trekking.</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/2/1/c/600_446685596.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>d. Rock climbing</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/2/2/8/600_446685608.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>e. Pyramid visiting</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/2/e/9/600_446685801.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>f. Nature &amp; fun things to do.</b></p> <p><b>Things to bring </b> :</p> <p>It\'s going to be cold so bring a solid <b>WARM Blanket </b><br/>Sports shoes, preferable old shoes.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and a water bottle.</p> <p>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Tariff: Rs.500 per head</b> - Limited seats only<br/>Includes<br/>. Camping gears<br/>. Activities<br/>. Campsite charges.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228708684/\"><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228708684/\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228708684/</a></a></p> <p>please use this link and do the payment to conform your slot thanku...</p> <p><b>Not included food &amp;</b><b> Transport </b></p> <p><i>Note: <b>No booze, No intoxicants</b>, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. Its just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><b>Payment Details: On spot payment.</b></p> <p>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b> </i>Contact:-9676722155</p> '),(496,'1456811689000','Fitness - Cycling to Golkonda Fort and Photography','229248788','1457792730000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229248788/','ClimbOn Pallavi - 7674070563','2016-03-12 05:30:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-03-12 14:25:00.000000','<p><b>Distance</b>: 7km + 7 km ride </p> <p><b>Duration</b>: about 3 hours</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/f/3/5/600_447177141.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Route</b>:</p> <p>• Start at HBC at 5:30 am</p> <p>• After reaching the fort, we hike to the top of the Fort. Spend some time there while enjoying the city view and click pictures. </p> <p>• Will stop for breakfast in between.</p> <p>• Reach Bike station.</p> <p><b>History of Golconda Fort</b> : The 13th century Golconda Fort was built by the Kakatiya kings. The existing structure was later built by Qutub Shahi Kings into a massive fort with granite walls having eight gates and 87 bastions spread upto 7 kms, in circumference over a span of 62 years. Golconda Fort, popularly known in Telugu as \"Golla Konda\", which means \"Shepherd\'s Hill\", has an exotic story behind it. In 1143, on the rocky hill known as \'Mangalavaram\', a shepherd boy came across an image and conveyed to the Kakatiya king, who was ruling at that time. The 10 km long road from Golconda to outer Hyderabad was a fantastic market selling jewellery, diamonds, pearls and other gems, popular in all over the world.</p> <p><b>Photographers </b>- Bring on your camera\'s - <b>Capture Sunrise at Golconda Fort</b>.......  \"Let\'s capture the beauty of Golconda in the morning sunrise. Breathtaking landscapes, beautiful sunrise, architecture of Golconda and aerial shots are few of the best possible pics that can be clicked in this trip\", in the description and add some of the history of Golconda, it helps some.</p> <p><b>What to click.. </b></p> <p> The route we take to reach Golconda Fort from HBC has lot of hills and greenery and Golconda fort is paradise for photographers.. Most of the shots will be landscape </p> <p><b>We will rent bicycles from HBC and event is open to all.</b></p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p>Please carry an original ID card like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station before 5:30am </p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Club Fee - 50/-  includes entry to golconda fort</p> <p> [ Please bring exact change ] </p> <p><b>Bicycle Rent Cost</b> - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee Rs 100/-</p> '),(497,'1457036462000','Ride to historical sites Bhongir Fort & Aler - Kolanpak on Mar 13th.','229322740','1466741766000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229322740/','Near Uppal police station, Contact : Rohith-9676722155','2016-03-13 06:00:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2016-06-24 04:16:00.000000','<p><b>About Place: </b>Bhongir or Bhuvanagiri is a small town about 40km from uppal Hyderabad on the way to Warangal. The fort is on top of a small hill - in fact the hill is a monolith - a huge rock. The surrounding areas being flat, the hill affords a grand view of the vistas beyond.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/b/3/1/600_431903345.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What do we plan to do</b> :Hiking, Fort climbing and collecting memories that will last a longtime.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/f/5/b/600_446532123.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/7/1/5/600_433110485.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>JAIN TEMPLE:-</b></p> <p>Kolanapaka belongs to Aler mandal  of Nalgonda Dt, TS.</p> <p>Famous Jain Temple, Beautiful historic (Sri Someshwara Temple) village with lots of small temples and scriptures. <br/>Not only that, it has Veera Narayana temple, Sai temple, Goddes Renuka temple and small Anjaneya temples. It is located in Aler mandal, Nalgonda district. It is about 75 km away from Hyderabad. The people come from mostly Maharashtra, Rajastan, Gujarat states to visit famous Jain temple. Sri Someshwara temple attracts devotees from all over Karnataka.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/6/0/600_446103424.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/5/c/600_446103420.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p>6:00am: Meetup at Uppal X Road (near Uppal Police Station)</p> <p>Start towards Bhongir</p> <p>7:00 Reach Bhongir and start climbing</p> <p>9:00 Reach hill top with and magnificent overview of horizon</p> <p>11:00 Start descending down. </p> <p>12:00 Start to aler</p> <p>1:00 Reach aler </p> <p>LUNCH</p> <p>2:00 Visit 800 years old Jain temple and 1200 years old Archaeological monuments.  </p> <p>4:00 Start back to town.</p> <p>6:00 Reach Hyderabad.</p> <p> bye bye...........</p> <p><b>What to wear:</b></p> <p>Wear Shoes with good of grip. Helmet must for bike riders.</p> <p>• Wear anything comfortable, preferably tracks and tees.</p> <p>• As we will be starting early, wear something to keep you warm.</p> <p><b>What to </b></p> <p><b>NOTE :- Bikers carry your HELMET</b></p> <p>• Water bottles - 2 x 1 liters</p> <p>• Hat or cap as it will be hot afternoons</p> <p>• Electrol or glucose</p> <p>• Camera</p> <p>• Loads of energy.</p> <p><b>Costs </b>: Rs. 200 which includes breakfast - tea snacks &amp; club fund</p> <p><b>Guidelines</b>: This is a historical place . No venturing towards steep cliff drops. No littering.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Rohith-9676722155</p> <p><b>Difficulty </b>: Easy</p> <p>Transport: Personal Vehicles, If possible there will be pool and petrol cost will be shared.</p> <p><b>PLEASE ANSWER ALL THE QUESTIONS. IF YOU DO NOT, WE WILL NOT BE ABLE TO WAIT FOR YOU AND YOUR RSVP WILL BE CONSIDERED VOID.</b></p> '),(498,'1457855774000','Beat the Heat in an Indoor Swimming Pool and Get the Fitness','229550291','1457886607000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229550291/','Please contact Arvind: (9640431351)','2016-03-13 18:30:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-03-13 16:30:00.000000','<p><b>Beat the Heat in an Indoor Swimming Pool, followed by Dinner at a Dhaba (Optional). </b></p> <p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, ncreasing muscle strength,Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core,Endurance,Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down.</p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour swimming meetup at Kondapur. Post swimming, we will go for dinner together at a Dhaba in Gachibowli.</p> <p>People who are new to swimming can also join and they can learn the swimming. Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Time : </b>6:30 PM to 7:30 PM (Swimming); 8:00 to 9:30 PM Dinner at a Dhaba in Gachibowli</p> <p><b>Venue: </b>Seasons Swimming Pool. Kondapur</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges, which includes swimming costumes for Boys, and swimming gears like cap etc.  Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b></p> <p><b>Dinner at a Dhaba: We all will share the cost. </b></p> '),(499,'1458150889000','Climb-On Flash events - Trekkers Paradise Kumara Parvata Toughest in Karnataka','229640929','1458573501000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229640929/','Naveen Kodela  901 0143 000','2016-03-17 20:00:00.000000','past','JNTU KUKATPALLY ','HYDERABAD ','IN','NEAR JNTU COLLEGE, KUKATPALLY',0,'2016-03-21 15:18:00.000000','<p>Announcing a new face of<b> Climb-On Hyderabad - “FLASH” </b>for sincere trekkers.</p> <p><b><i>Note: </i></b>Climb-On Flash Events -These events are for serious trekkers, level of difficulty will be back-breaking. <b>Such events will be posted 24 hrs before the meetup time and closing of RSVP will be 6 hrs before the event starts. </b>Members who are serious about such event got hardly 14 hrs of window to join RSVP list. Nothing much is planned and almost no itinerary. We are backpackers - so called travellers and not tour agents.  So be like “By plane, by train, by boat…actually it doesn’t matter as long as I can travel”</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/6/8/7/600_447905767.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What: </b>Trekkers Paradise - Kumara Parvatha - The toughest trek in Karnataka<br/><b>When:</b> 17th Thursday March 2016, 8:00 PM start – 21th Monday 7:00 AM back.<br/><b>Where: </b>(A location has not been chosen yet)<br/><b>About: </b>Kumara Parvata, the third tallest peak in Karnataka. Else, find online.<br/><b>Difficulty level :</b> High<br/><b>Temperature : </b>Max 30 degrees C<br/><b>Accommodation :</b> Tents<br/><b>Washrooms :</b> Not available, (only at bus or train stations).<br/><b>Food : </b>Veg food<br/><b>Transport :</b> Group Transport<br/>Distance from Bangalore 230 kms (one way)<br/>Total trekking distance 14-15 kms approx. (one way)<br/>Will be adding finer details of this trek as we move on.<br/><b>Things to bring: </b>Two track pants/ loose trousers 2 full hand T-shirt, Hat or Cap (avoid bright coloured)<br/>Trekking shoes with Anklet to protect yourself from blood sucking leeches.<br/>Torch / Flashlight /headlight with spare batteries for night trek. Raincoat. Sleeping Bag.<br/>Water bottle – 2 Litres,Toilet paper / wet tissues<br/>Photo Id (Employee/College Id, Pan card/Election Card/ Driving License)<br/>A rucksack / haversack to carry above stuff.</p> <p>Are you ready for this Challenge?<br/><b>This is not for the following people:</b><br/>1. Not for first timers.<br/>2. Not for families or children below 18 years.<br/>3. If you cannot carry your own luggage, it’s not for you.<br/>4. If you can’t carry around 10-12+kg luggage, it’s not for you.<br/>5. Smokers are discourages as you will be climbing almost the whole day time. </p> <p><b>Cost: </b>More or less Rs.2200. NO Club Fee :-).<br/>Only people with a tough spirit, pls RSVP. All the best !</p> <p>Tourists don’t know where they’ve been, Travelers don’t know where they are going.<br/>– Paul Theroux.</p> '),(500,'1457938676000','A day trip exploration adventure activities more fun @ Divya retreat, keesara','229573378','1458444757000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229573378/','Contact : Rohith-9676722155','2016-03-20 05:30:00.000000','past','Hyderabad','Hyderabad','in','Meeting point: Tarnaka X Road ',0,'2016-03-20 03:32:00.000000','<p>Date &amp; time:- March 20,2016 5:30 AM</p> <p>Place: -<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;q=Keesara%2C+Hyderabad%2C+in\">Divya Retreat</a> (27 kms from meetup point)</p> <p><b>Meeting point: Tarnaka petrol bunk</b></p> <p>Category: Adventure / Trek / fun activities</p> <p>Difficulty level: Easy</p> <p><b>Trek Notes: </b></p> <p>Keesaragutta is a hillock at the village of Keesara in Rangareddy District. It is famous for Ramalingeswara temple and the vast shrub forest with huge boulders and small lakes.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/8/b/600_447839531.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This is more of a easy exploration of keesara hills, rock climbing, repelling trip than a hard-core trek, the basic aim of the event is to show the taste of easy level exploration.. Trekking, repelling, rock climbing, chimney etc.</p> <p><b>Trekking:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/b/5/600_447839573.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Rappelling:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/e/6/600_447839622.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Rock climbing:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/f/2/600_447839634.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Team games:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/f/d/600_447839645.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/9/0/6/600_447839654.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Itinerary[May Vary]:</b></p> <p><b>Sunday:</b></p> <p><b>5.15 am: gather at meetup point</b></p> <p><b>5.30 am: start from meetup point to divya retreat.</b></p> <p><b>6.30 am: reach the place</b></p> <p><b>6.45 am: start trekking</b></p> <p><b>9.00 am: complete trekking and breakfast </b></p> <p><b>9.30 am: Adventure activities (rappelling, rock climbing….)</b></p> <p><b>12.30 pm: lunch &amp; relax</b></p> <p><b>2.00 pm: team games </b></p> <p><b>5.00 pm: start back to Hyderabad</b></p> <p><b>6.00 pm: reach Hyderabad</b></p> <p><b>Bye bye…..</b></p> <p><b>CHARGES – Rs 800/- per head</b></p> <p><b>Breakfast and lunch provided by us</b></p> <p><b>note:-transport excluded</b></p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b></p> <p>Ø ID Proof - Driving license, Voter ID card etc</p> <p>Ø Water bottles</p> <p>Ø Trek shoes</p> <p>Ø track pants</p> <p>Ø Swimming clothes (if possible we can do swimming)</p> <p>Ø towel</p> <p>Ø Toilet kit</p> <p>Ø Camera</p> <p>Ø Snacks (Dry fruits, Energy bars, Citrus fruits, salty food)</p> <p>Important Instructions:</p> <p>1) ABSOLUTELY NO SMOKING AND NO ALCOHOL<br/>2) No littering, no pollution of water<br/>3) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable<br/>4) We carry basic first aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers<br/>5) If you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately.<br/>6) Please ensure that you wear on long pants (Jeans or tracks) and shoes only on the trek phase.</p> '),(501,'1452937256000','Kedarnath Himalaya Trek in association with NEHRU INSTITUTE OF MOUNTAINEERING','228129742','1460519412000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228129742/','Arvind: 9640431351; Naveen: 9010143000','2016-03-23 16:30:00.000000','past','KACHIGUDA RAILWAY STATION','Hyderabad','in','KACHIGUDA RAILWAY STATION',0,'2016-04-13 03:50:00.000000','<p>• <b>WINTER SNOW-BOUND TREK TO KEDARNATH, HIMALAYA, in association with NEHRU INSTITUTE OF </b><b>MOUNTAINEERING</b><b>(NIM).</b></p> <p><b>• About NIM - <a href=\"http://www.nimindia.net/#!about/cquc\"><a href=\"http://www.nimindia.net/#!about/cquc\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.nimindia.net/#!about/cquc</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/3/b/3/600_445929139.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Climb On is excited to organize a 44 km winter trek to Kedarnath, which is situated at the altitude of 11,755 ft (3600 mt) above sea level. Trek is being organized in association with <b><i>NEHRU INSTITUTE  OF </i></b><i><b>MOUNTAINEERING</b></i><b><i> (NIM), UTTARKASHI</i>.</b></p> <p>Kedarnath is situated in Uttarakhand at a distance of 223 km from Rishikesh (470 km from Delhi). Kedarnath is a sacred shrine dedicated to Lord Shiva and its temple was built by Adi Shankaracharya in 8th A.D. It is not just a pilgrim place but also celebrated as a<b> high altitude destination</b> among trekkers. For pilgrimage, Kedarnath is open only from May to October as during winter (middle of September to the second or third week of April) snow sets there. Kedarnath gives a very close view of the lofty peaks of the Himalaya, one of the greatest mountain range in the world. The way to Kedarnath is also <b>full of rich flora &amp; fauna</b> and the local people are very hospitable. </p> <p><b>- </b>So, let’s Climb On to the hills of Kedarnath in end of this winter.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/4/9/a/600_445929370.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/3/c/6/600_445929158.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/3/c/d/600_445929165.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Route: </b>Hyderabad – Delhi –Rishikesh – Devprayag – Rudraprayag – Guptkashi – Sonprayag – Gaurikund- Kedarnath.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/a/6/9/600_446091817.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Expected temperature in end of March: </b>(-) 10 to (+) 5 °</p> <p><a href=\"http://www.accuweather.com/en/in/kedarnath/196565/march-weather/196565\"><a href=\"http://www.accuweather.com/en/in/kedarnath/196565/march-weather/196565\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.accuweather.com/en/in/kedarnath/196565/march-weather/196565</a></a></p> <p><b>Grade:</b> Moderate</p> <p><i><b>Itinerary:</b><br/></i></p> <p><i><b>A: Travel - Hyderbad to Sonprayag</b></i></p> <p><b> Day 0 (Wednesday, 23rd March):</b> 5:00 PM- Hyderabad to Delhi (Train, <b>Sleeper</b>; 24 hours)</p> <p><b>Day 01 (Thursday, 24th March- </b>It’s Holi, so no leave to be taken<b>)</b> Reach Delhi (6:00 PM) and start to Rishikesh by night bus (Drive 230 Km, 6-8 hours; <b>People who wants to go Delhi by flight can join  us at ISBT Delhi or can join us in Rishikesh, if you are flying to Dehradun as Rishikesh is just 25 kms from Dehradun Airport</b>).</p> <p><b>Day 02 (Friday, 25th March, </b>It’s Good Friday, so no leave to be taken<b>):</b> Rishikesh (5:00 AM) to Sonprayag (Drive 215 kms, 8 hrs): Night stay at Sonprayag.</p> <p>------------------------------------------------------------------</p> <p><b><i>B: Trekking</i> (3 days)</b></p> <p><b> Day 03 (Saturday, 26th March): </b>Sonprayag to a forest campsite (Trek – 14kms) </p> <p><b> Day 04 (Sunday, 27th March): </b>Camp-site to Kedarnath (Trek – 8kms). We may also go to Chorabari Lake</p> <p><b>Day 05 (Monday, 28th March):</b> Kedarnath to Sonprayag (22 Km). Night stay at Sonprayag</p> <p>------------------------------------------------------------------</p> <p><i><b>C: Travel from Sonprayag to Hyderabad</b></i></p> <p><b>Day 06 (Tuesday, 29th March):</b> Sonprayag to Rishikesh (Drive 215 kms, 8hrs) and Rishikesh to Delhi in night bus (Reaching Delhi on 7th Morning)</p> <p><b>Day 07 (Wednesday, 30th March):</b> Delhi to Hyderabad (Train, Sleeper, Morning train). </p> <p>Reach Hyderabad on 8th day (before noon)</p> <p><i>*We may have a little variation in the plan, based on the situations.</i></p> <p><b><i>Trekking outfit and things to bring: </i></b></p> <p>·  A <b>rucksack (must)</b> to keep all the things with a sleeping bag (good to have)/blanket</p> <p>·  At least 4 sets of clothes (Prefer full length track pants or loose trouser; avoid Jeans)</p> <p>·  1 heavy Jacket to withstand <b>(-)5 to 10 degree temp</b>; 1 normal sweater/jacket</p> <p>·  Sunglasses for snow</p> <p>·  Skull cap and Gloves</p> <p>·  Trekking shoes used at least ones with 2 pairs of socks. </p> <p>·  Toiletries (Brush, tooth paste, soap, shampoo etc).</p> <p>·  Electrol /glucose/energy bars/chocolates etc.</p> <p>·  Torch or headlight with extra spare batteries. </p> <p>·  Any medications physician prescribed.</p> <p>·  Two emergency notes with your name, address, emergency contact number.</p> <p>·  <i>Your photo Id with a xerox copy of it. </i></p> <p><b>Instructions</b></p> <p>·  This trip is organized only for serious climbers, the one who have done few treks before. It’s a 44 kms trek in 3 days.</p> <p>·  No smoking, alcohol, littering, and no pollution of water. </p> <p>·  This is not a luxury trip, but out most care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p>·  Food will be vegetarian</p> <p>·  We carry basic First Aid; if you need anything you can ask the organizers. </p> <p><b>Cost:</b> <b>Approximately Rs. 8000 </b>which includes Hyd-Delhi train fare <b>+</b> Delhi - Rishikesh Volvo Bus fare <b>+</b> Mini bus to Rishikesh - Sonprayag <b>+</b> Cottages at Sonprayag <b>+</b> 3 days meals during the trek from Sonprayag to Kedarnath <b>+</b> Stay at Proper military standard tepees and back to Hyderabad.</p> <p><b>Note: </b>As many of club members knew that this is a Non-profit organisation and we are not much bothered about cost breakup, nevertheless, a slight variation in expenses will be shared among the members if required.</p> <p>Got some Surprise event at the end of the trek to make your trip more adventurous and memorable.</p> <p><b>Payment Details:  </b>You will be in waiting list unless you make the payment. Guys, Please make a payment of Rs. 4000 to confirm your seat. We would need this advance to book train tickets and making other arrangements. </p> <p>Payment Link: <a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228129742/\"><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228129742/\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228129742/</a></a></p> <p>For any more questions, please reach out to the organizers of the event (Arvind: 9640431351; Naveen: 9010143000)</p> '),(502,'1455731615000','Climb-On Holi, Unlimited Fun!!! Celebrate Holi & Night camping on 23-24 March.','228924115','1459151305000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/228924115/','Climb-On pallavi - 7674070563      climb on prudhvi-9908023223','2016-03-23 18:00:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2016-03-28 07:48:00.000000','<p><i><b>CLIMB-ON HOLI. OPEN AIR FESTIVAL With CLIMB-ON.</b></i></p> <p><i>Celebration begins here....with Climb-ON </i></p> <p><b><i>We welcome you to celebrate Holi with natural colors in natural Habitat....</i></b></p> <p><b>HOLI- The festival of colors,</b><b> party with your friends AND LOVED ONES at our private farm. The day calls for celebrations and enjoyment in the company of closed pals coming together to share music, dance and unlimited fun. The best way to celebrate HOLI is to spend the time in a way your group enjoys the most.</b></p> <p>It just doesn\'t get much better than playing holi with organic colors camping in outside hyderabad with friends &amp; family, Food on the grill, a new moon, games around you, enjoying the great outdoors, songs &amp; stories around the campfire, nothing could be better than this to make your festival a great experience.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/1/f/4/600_447020980.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Where: </b>Just across the border from Hyderabad, this is one of our favorites. Got some excellent sites that are right on the shoreline of beautiful fields.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/2/4/4/600_441985156.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Date: </b>On Wednesday 23nd March 6:00pm to 24rd March 3:00pm. 1D/1N.<br/><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot, just join the waiting list and make the payment.<br/><b>Distance:</b> 90kms away from Uppal on Warangal Highway (2hrs drive)<br/><b>Meetup Point:</b> Uppal X roads, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences: Colours, Music Dance.</b></p> <p>a. Organic colours</p> <p>b. Music &amp; Bon-fire</p> <p>c. Camping.</p> <p>d. Mud Holi</p> <p>E. Tamatino</p> <p>Plus Nature &amp; fun things to do.</p> <p><b>Things to bring </b>for the celebration :</p> <p>Preferred color to wear is White (optional)<br/>A pair of old cloths which you don\'t mind throwing away.<br/>Sports shoes, preferable old shoes.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or a blanket, and a water bottle.<br/>A plastic bag to carry your muddy clothes.<br/>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Tariff: Rs.750 per head</b> - Limited seats only.<br/><i>Includes: </i><br/>a. Food (Veg &amp; No n Veg) : Dinner, B/fast, tea &amp; snacks, Bon-fire snacks - Barbecue and Lunch.<br/>b. Camping gears(tents)<br/>c. Activities<br/>d. Campsite charges.</p> <p><b>Day 1 </b>After reaching by 6pm, Music and dance around the bon-fire; with camping, Dinner.<br/><b>Day 2</b> Morning we start the day with a hearty breakfast, enjoying the view,<br/>Then Mud Holi followed, tamatino and start back.</p> <p>Open to Everyone.</p> <p><i>Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p>Request to make the payment to below given payment link to confirm your position in the \"Yes\" list.</p> <p><b>Payment Link:</b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228924115/\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/228924115/</a></b></p> <p>Once payment is transferred, request you to add your transaction ID to comments below to confirm your slot.<br/>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers : </b></i><i>Climb-On pallavi-7674070563 Climb-On</i> prudhvi-9908023223</p> '),(503,'1458372125000','Parkour basics by an American Parkour Certified Coach Sreeramachandra','229708784','1458960677000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229708784/','ClimbOn Suman 9966002025','2016-03-26 05:30:00.000000','past','Lower Tankbund','Hyderabad','in','Indira Park',0,'2016-03-26 02:51:00.000000','<p>Parkour is the activity/sport of moving rapidly through an area, typically in an urban environment, negotiating obstacles by running, jumping, and climbing. The art which helps you to explore your mind, body and spirit and helps you become your best version.</p> <p>This meetup is for all the enthusiasts belonging to all age groups (5-50 years) who have been waiting to get started with the natural art of overcoming obstacles in the most creative and fun filled way. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/5/a/600_447966746.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/2/5/600_447966693.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Sreeramachandra Modukuru is an American Parkour Certified Coach, Professional Parkour Athlete, Official Trainer of the Paramilitary Forces (CISF) and a Fitness Freak. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/3/8/600_447966712.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Links to Sreeramachandra\'s Parkour/Freerunning: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Us_DODpziS0\">Video 1</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iXOUQR0Yuhw\">Video 2</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fiTCHoD0pLg\">Video 3</a></p> <p><b>Itinerary :</b></p> <p>05:30 : Assemble at Meeting Point - Indra Park<br/>05:45 : Little warm up <br/>06:00 : Start of the event <br/>08:00 : End of the event<br/>08:10  : Tata, bye bye</p> <p><b>What to Wear :</b> </p> <p>• Tee shirt - prefer full sleeves</p> <p>• Tracks / Shorts  ( No jeans please ) </p> <p>• Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>• Water 1-2 liters</p> <p><b>Cost :</b> Rs. 100/- as club fee.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/229708784/\">Click here to pay online</a></p> <p><b>Contact :</b></p> <p>ClimbOn Suman 9966002025</p> '),(504,'1458626061000','Night camping ,night trek , - rock climbing ,rapelling & more @keesara','229781104','1459683615000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229781104/','Contact : Rohith-9676722155,arun-9666031286','2016-04-02 16:00:00.000000','past','Hyderabad','Hyderabad','in','Meeting point: Tarnaka X Road ',0,'2016-04-03 11:40:00.000000','<p>Date &amp; time:- Aprial 2nd,2016 4:00 pM</p> <p>Place: -<a href=\"https://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&amp;hl=en&amp;q=Keesara%2C+Hyderabad%2C+in\">Divya Retreat</a> (27 kms from meetup point)</p> <p><b>Meeting point: Tarnaka petrol bunk</b></p> <p>Category: Adventure / Trek / fun activities</p> <p>Difficulty level: Easy</p> <p><b>Trek Notes: </b></p> <p>Keesaragutta is a hillock at the village of Keesara in Rangareddy District. It is famous for Ramalingeswara temple and the vast shrub forest with huge boulders and small lakes.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/8/b/600_447839531.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This is more of a easy exploration of keesara hills, rock climbing, repelling trip than a hard-core trek, the basic aim of the event is to show the taste of easy level exploration.. Trekking, repelling, rock climbing, chimney etc.</p> <p><b>Trekking:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/b/5/600_447839573.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Rappelling:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/e/6/600_447839622.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Rock climbing:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/f/2/600_447839634.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Zipline:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/5/b/5/600_448114229.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Team games:-</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/8/f/d/600_447839645.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/9/0/6/600_447839654.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Swimming &amp; more fun activities.......</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Itinerary[May Vary]:</b></p> <p>saturday:</p> <p>4 to 4.30 pm:gather at meetup point</p> <p>4.30 p.m: start from meetup point to divya retreat.</p> <p>7.00 p.m: reach base and have snacks.</p> <p>7.30 p.m: start camp fire,games, dinner</p> <p>9.30 p.m: start to night trek</p> <p>11.00 p.m: pitch tents &amp; retire for the day</p> <p>Sunday:</p> <p>6.00 :wake up </p> <p>6.30:team games &amp;breakfast </p> <p>8.00: rock climbing </p> <p>10.00:play seven stones </p> <p>12.30: lunch</p> <p>1.00 p.m: rapelling</p> <p>5.30 p.m: Start back </p> <p><b>CHARGES – Rs 1300/- per head</b></p> <p><b>cost breakup:- 600 food(dinner,breakfast,lunch,snacks &amp; tea)-300 for activities-300 club fund (which includes tents,equipment,first aid)-100 organizer reimbursement </b></p> <p><b>Breakfast and lunch provided by us</b></p> <p><b>Account details:- Rohith eravalli</b></p> <p><b>     kotak mahendra bank</b></p> <p><b>     Ac no:- 9211678893</b></p> <p><b>     ifsc code:- KKBK0000552</b></p> <p><b>     branch:- somagi guda   </b></p> <p><b>note:-transport excluded</b></p> <p>Things to bring:</p> <p>Ø  Torch</p> <p>Ø  ID Proof - Drivers license, Voter ID card etc</p> <p>Ø  sleeping bag/badsheet</p> <p>Ø  Water bottles </p> <p>Ø  Trek shoes</p> <p>Ø  track pants, shorts</p> <p>Ø  towel </p> <p>Ø  Extra pair of clothes and a jacket for the cold.</p> <p>Ø  Toilet kit</p> <p>Ø  Camera</p> <p>Ø   Dry fruits, Energy bars, Citrus fruits, salty food.</p> <p>Ø  Ors packets</p> <p>Important Instructions:</p> <p>1)  ABSOLUTELY NO SMOKING AND NO ALCOHOL <br/>2) No littering, no pollution of water <br/>3) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable <br/>4) ladies and gent’s accommodation is separate in tents. <br/>5) Food will be basic vegetarian <br/>6) We carry basic first aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers <br/>7) If you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately. <br/>8) Please ensure that you wear on long pants (Jeans or tracks) and shoes only on the trek phase.</p> '),(505,'1459310392000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','229981314','1460042322000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229981314/','ClimbOn Suman 99660 02025','2016-04-07 18:00:00.000000','past','HITEC City','HYDERABAD','in','Raheja Mindspace,',0,'2016-04-07 15:18:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 25 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and  a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\".  </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.  </p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Thursday 7th April 6:00-8:00 PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend (8th-10th April;  Friday 8th April would probably be off for most of you for Ugadi).</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/0/600_448372560.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/d/600_448372573.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/6/600_448372582.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/d/600_448372589.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>6.00: Meet at mind space and move to springs </p> <p>6.10:  Introduction and game rules</p> <p>6.15:  Warm up exercises </p> <p>6.30: Game shuru </p> <p>8.30: End game and feedback </p> <p>8.45: Tata bye bye. </p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet. </p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 200 per head (include club fee + ground rent )</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Suman 99660 02025</p> '),(506,'1459855182000','ClimbOn Social Celebrate UGADI in village with STEP UP organization','230140230','1460177513000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230140230/','ClimbOn Rohith 9676722155','2016-04-08 09:00:00.000000','past','maheswaram mandal','Hyderabad','in','mohabbath nagar',0,'2016-04-09 04:51:00.000000','<p>STEP UP organization is nonprofit set up with the primary motive to RECONNECT WITH THE  RURAL COMMUNITIES </p> <p>Step up adopts the problems in the rural community &amp; finds the solution within them</p> <p>Our first field work started  in mohabbatnagar (30km from hyd) [ <b>Its not Mahaboob Nagar</b> ] which is in maheswaram mandal ,Ranga Reddy district</p> <p>Step up cordially invites you to participate in ugadi celebrations(10am to 5pm) in mohabbatnagar ,starts with  ugadi pacchadi, distribution of clothes to the Anganwadi kids,and sports equipment for the two primary schools ,interact n play with them ,have the Telugu food in lunch  under the tamarind tree,participate in rangoli /play volleyball with the locals ,interaction session with the villagers &amp; sharing the experience &amp; knowledge with them ..</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/a/5/1/600_448599505.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Activities</b></p> <p>==&gt; Small meeting with village people</p> <p>==&gt; Start the festival celebrations with UGADI pachadi</p> <p>==&gt; Donating sports items and dresses for anganwadi children and spend                    some time with them</p> <p>==&gt; Special lunch with UGADI dishes </p> <p>==&gt; Interaction with old people, farmers and students and know their                            problems</p> <p>==&gt; Spend some time with children followed by some fun activities.                              (Rangoli,volleyball and some kids games)</p> <p><b>Itinerary</b></p> <p>9.00   am :- start from Hyderabad</p> <p>10.00 am :- reach the village </p> <p>10.30 am :- donation program for children and spend some time with them</p> <p>1.00  pm  :- Lunch </p> <p>2.00 pm  :- visit village and know the problems of people</p> <p>4.00 pm :- rangoli and volley ball competition</p> <p>5.30 pm :- start back to Hyderabad </p> <p>STEP UP organization is a non profit organization which is an startup to help people by choosing current problems in society as their projects. </p> <p>They have chosen their first project as RIAS(revival of Indian agricultural sector) main motto of this project is to stop the suicides of farmers by teaching them the proper way of agriculture such as model farming, organic farming, permaculture (permanent agriculture) </p> <p><b>NOTE</b> It\'s a totally free of service program anyone can join who are interested in social service activities.</p> <p><b>Club Fee</b>  Zero </p> '),(507,'1458979900000','Night camping Beside Lake @ Pocharam Forest 9th April','229885147','1460349570000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229885147/','Rohith 9676722155 Pravallika 7702523099','2016-04-09 13:00:00.000000','past','Balanagar','Hyderabad','in','Balanagar X Roads',0,'2016-04-11 04:39:00.000000','<p>Pocharam lake is located in Medak district in the Indian state of Telangana. It is adjacent to Pocharam Forest &amp; Wildlife Sanctuary.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/4/d/600_442416685.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/1/0/1/600_442533025.jpeg\" /></p> <p>15 KM from Medak is Pocharam<br/>We would also be exploring the Medak Fort which is a citadel built on a hillock that provided as a vantage point for the Kakatiyan rulers in ancient India.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/9/1/600_442416753.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Date:</b> On Sat 9th 1p.m to Sun 10th 11 a.m 1D/1N.</p> <p><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot and make the payment at meetup point.</p> <p><b>Distance: </b>110kms away from (3hrs drive)</p> <p><b>Meetup Point:</b> Balanagar X roads, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences: </b>Night Camping, Star gazing,</p> <p>a. Night camping</p> <p>b. Trekking.</p> <p>c. Bon-fire.</p> <p>d. Stargazing</p> <p>e. Haunted stories</p> <p>f. Fort Visit</p> <p>Plus Nature &amp; fun things to do.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b><br/>A pair of extra clothes if you go for swim. (optional)<br/>Sports shoes.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and 2 ltr water bottle.<br/>Caps/Raincoats(optional)<br/>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b><br/>Day 1 After reaching by 5pm, Roam Around, bon-fire with camping, Dinner.<br/>Day 2 Morning we start the day lake trek enjoying the view and fun activities.</p> <p><b>Tariff: </b>Rs.400 per head - Limited seats only<br/>Includes:<br/>a. Camping gears (Tents etc..)<br/>b. Activities.</p> <p>Food and Transport <b>Not</b> included in the club fund. We can share it accordingly.<br/>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care will be taken to make your trip comfortable.</p> <p><b>Note: </b><i>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. Its just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b> Rohith 9676722155 Pravallika 7702523099<br/></i></p> '),(508,'1459831229000','Evening Ride @ Necklace Road','230136331','1460303674000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230136331/','ClimbOn Pallavi - 7674070563','2016-04-10 18:00:00.000000','past','Necklace Road, Opp Sanjeeviah Park','Hyderabad','in','Necklace Road Bike Station',0,'2016-04-10 15:54:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride at the Neckace road bike station. Starting time is 5:45 pm. You can rent a bicyce from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/3/5/d/600_448597725.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Necklace Road is a boulevard in Hyderabad, adjoining the Hussain Sagar lake, which connects NTR Gardens to Sanjeevaiah Park. Named after the first and the famous Necklace Road in Mumbai\'s Marine Drive. The road from Sanjivaiah park connects to the Tankbund road which in turn connects to the NTR Gardens completing a circle. This stretch of road, along with the Tank Bund, appears in the form of a necklace as seen from the sky - and hence the name.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/3/8/0/600_448597760.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p><b>Please carry an original ID card</b> like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station before 6:00pm </p> <p><b>Cost - </b>Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit and air pump)</p> <p> [ Please bring exact change ] </p> <p><b>Own Bicycle Rent Cost</b> - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee  Rs 100/-</p> '),(509,'1459234307000','Let\'s explore and burn ur calories in the forest @ Nagalapuram','229955208','1461212415000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/229955208/','ClimbOn Rohit - 96767 22155 ClimbOn arun - 9666031286','2016-04-15 17:00:00.000000','past','Nagalapuram Hills, Chittoor, Andhra Pradesh, India','Hyderabad','in','Nagalapuram Hills, Chittoor, Andhra Pradesh, India',0,'2016-04-21 04:20:00.000000','<p><b>Place : NAGALAPURAM, Near to Tirupathi </b></p> <p>Duration : 2 Days weekend Trek <br/>Difficulty level : Easy to medium  (people can join those who are fit)</p> <p>IMP Notes:</p> <p>No kids [ Only for Ages above 18]</p> <p><b>About Place: </b></p> <p>Nagalapuram  is a pristine beauty which offers lovely  trek with a beautiful view of the water falls, Hills , pools and forest. Thrown in with some steep climbs for experienced trekkers along with easy climbs routes for starters, natural wilderness and 20 foot water slides; make a perfect blend for an ultimate experience.</p> <p><b><br/></b> <img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/c/3/0/600_448376368.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/e/4/a/600_448376906.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This place needs no introduction for the Trek savvies, Now that the monsoon has shown its mercy upon us, its time for CLIMBON now to return back the love towards exploring the pure nature through jumping into the countless crystal clear water pools in Nagalapuram Hills.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/e/1/8/600_448376856.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Nagalapuram Falls:-</b></p> <p>Nagalapuram Falls is a pristine beauty which offers lovely one-day treks from <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chennai\">Chennai</a> with a beautiful view of the water falls. Thrown in with some steep climbs for experienced trekkers along with easy climbs routes for starters, natural wilderness and 20 foot water slides; make a perfect blend for an ultimate experience.</p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p><b>Friday :  </b></p> <p>Start to Tirupathi by <b>5:30pm </b></p> <p> <b>Saturday : </b></p> <p>7am :Reach tirupati</p> <p>10am : Reach nagalapuram and explore path to the Target waterfall</p> <p>7pm : Camp outside in open sky(we will provide tents)</p> <p>9pm : Start snoring Loudly</p> <p><b>Sunday :</b></p> <p>6am : Wake up, Take a bath in the Waterfall, Explore the forest and Trek back </p> <p>4 pm: Start back to Tirupati  </p> <p>7:30 PM: Catch bus to Hyderabad   </p> <p><b>Monday :</b></p> <p>Reach hyderabad by <b>Morning 8:30 AM </b></p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b> [ All are must ] </p> <p>* Food (during trek) </p> <p>* Swimming tube (Mandatory)</p> <p>* Swim shorts</p> <p>* Full sleeves shirt and full pank during trek</p> <p>* Sleeping bag</p> <p>* Own Food Items +2L water bottles [ Extra weight ] <br/>   Torch , Rain sheets  or tarps</p> <p>* Shoes &amp; Extra pair of socks.</p> <p>     [ Get good shoes and better if you are using them already] </p> <p>* Extra snacks to make more friends .. :) <br/>    </p> <p><b>Note: Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. CLIMBON requests all the tp members to be socially responsible while the treks and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology. Try to avoid plastics as much as possible, especially plastics. </b></p> <p><b>Estimated Cost  :</b> Rs 2000/- approx.per head</p> <p> which includes transportation by train/ bus /stay(tents and any equipment required /local transportation and club fund. (food excluded)</p> <p><b>Note : </b>Food basic VEG..we will cook on our own</p> <p><b>Important Instructions:  </b></p> <p>1) No smoking and no alcohol <br/>2) No littering, no pollution of water <br/>3) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable <br/>4) ladies and gents accommodation is separate in tents. <br/>5) Food will be mostly vegetarian <br/>6) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention. <br/>7) if you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately.</p> <p>NOTE: Please answer all the questions.</p> <p>Contact : 9676722155 Rohith   ClimbOnrohithdeekshith@gmail.com</p> <p>* Please add your self to the waiting list; you will be moved to confirm list once your payment is done</p> <p>pls transfer the above mentioned costs for confirmation of slots </p> <p>Name : rohith eravalli <br/>Bank :kotak mahendra bank <br/>Branch : somagiguda <br/>Acc/no :9211678893<br/>IFSC code : KKBK0000552</p> <p>Mention trek name for easy identification thank you....</p> <p>ClimbOn Rohith - 9676722155</p> '),(510,'1460781077000','ClimbOn Fun Beat the heat - fun from your couch','230414537','1461211609000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230414537/','ClimbOn Suman 99660 02025','2016-04-16 19:00:00.000000','past','WhatsApp Group Online','Hyderabad','in','WhatsApp Grou