Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-05-07 14:54:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride to Gandipet Lake. Starting time is 5:15 pm from HBC bike station Gachibowli. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p>[Gandipet Lake]</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/5/d/4/600_449142452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Potluck: </b>A potluck is a gathering where each guest contributes a dish of food that is to be shared. Please comment below what u are planning 2 bring so that we can avoid duplication.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/3/8/0/600_448597760.jpeg\" /></p> <p>PC: From last cycling event of ClimbOn</p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p><b>Please carry an original ID card</b> like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station before 5:00pm </p> <p><b>Cost - </b>Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit and air pump and Paper Plates)</p> <p> [ Please bring exact change ] </p> <p><b>Own Bicycle Rent Cost</b> - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee  Rs 100/-</p> '),(519,'1462235889000','Experience unparalleled adventure of lifetime:Into Exhilarating world of Corals','230828980','1463594331000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230828980/','ClimbOn Suman 9966002025','2016-05-13 20:00:00.000000','past','Malvan','Maharastra','in','Tarkarli',0,'2016-05-18 17:58:00.000000','<p><b>About Place</b>:</p> <p><b>Tarkarli</b> is a village in <b>Malvan</b> taluka in Sindhudurg district, the southernmost district of Maharashtra State, India. It is well known for the historically important Sindhudurg Fort. It is tourist destination and a coral beach.</p> <p>Tarkarli beach has a long coastline and clear waters. Located at the confluence of the Karli River and the Arabian Sea, This place has gained prominence because of its long and narrow stretch of beach with pristine waters and water sports.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/2/b/6/600_449597078.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/2/9/e/600_449597054.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Scuba Diving</b>:</p> <p>Scuba diving is a form of underwater diving in which a diver uses a self contained underwater breathing apparatus (scuba) to breathe underwater.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/2/e/9/600_449597129.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Parasailing</b>:</p> <p>The harness attaches the pilot to the parasail, which is connected to the boat, or land vehicle, by the tow rope. The vehicle then drives off, carrying the parascender (or wing) and person into the air. The activity is primarily a fun ride, not to be confused with the sport of paragliding.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/2/8/600_449597192.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Jetski</b>:</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/8/0/600_449597280.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Other water sports</b>:</p> <p>• Banana ride</p> <p>• Bumper ride</p> <p>• Speed boat </p> <p>• Water scooter</p> <p><b>Itinerary :</b></p> <p><b>Day 0</b>:</p> <p><b>Friday</b> evening catch the bus and start to Malvan at 8 P.M.</p> <p><b>Day 1</b>:</p> <p>07:00 : Reach Malvan and get fresh</p> <p>08:00 : Break fast</p> <p>09:00 : Start of the event with Water sports</p> <p>13:00 : Lunch</p> <p>15:00 : Visit Sindhudurg Fort</p> <p>18:00 : Spend time at beach</p> <p>21:00 : Dinner and Night Beach Camping</p> <p><b>Beach Camping</b>:</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/4/c/9/600_449597609.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Day 2</b>:</p> <p>06:00 : Wake up and get fresh</p> <p>07:00 : Breakfast</p> <p>09:00 : Scuba diving and Parasailing</p> <p>13:00 : Lunch</p> <p>15:00 : Beach Volley ball</p> <p>18:00 : Spend time at beach</p> <p>20:00 : Dinner and Start back to Hyderabad</p> <p><b>Day 3</b>:</p> <p>Reach Hyderabad by 7 A.M</p> <p>Tata, Bubye :)</p> <p><b>Things to bring</b>:</p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts, at the beach, a pair of shorts would be a good.</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. - Sleeping bag or thick blanket and a proper rucksack (backpack) (both are must) and some plastic covers</p> <p>- Some snacks to climb on.</p> <p>- Torch light is must.</p> <p>- Water 1-2 liters</p> <p><b>Cost :</b> Rs. 5850/-  includes <b>Scuba diving</b>, <b>Parasailing</b>, other water sports, <b>transportation</b> and club fee. (own expense for food )</p> <p><b>Bank Details</b>:</p> <p>Bank name              :    ICICI bank ltd.<br/>Account Name       :    Suman K<br/>Account number   :    004001570137<br/>IFSC Code              :     ICIC0000040</p> <p>If you wish to use your <b>credit card</b>, you can transfer it to my <b>PayTM</b> account (<b>9849036491</b>) with <b>2% extra</b>.</p> <p><b>P.S: Please pay a minimum amount of Rs.1850/- to confirm your slot. If you are paying full amount, it is highly appreciated. </b></p> <p><b>Contact :</b></p> <p>ClimbOn Suman 9966002025</p> '),(520,'1461404505000','Indoor Climbing with ClimbOn (For the beginners also)','230587785','1463198309000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230587785/','Climb-On Arvind (9640431351)','2016-05-14 07:00:00.000000','past','Gachibowli Miyapur Road','Hyderabad','in','Crag Studio',0,'2016-05-14 03:58:00.000000','<p>It\'s heating up outside, but it doesn\'t mean that your adventure activities should be stopped in this summer. Why should you not  be having climbing adventure at an indoor studio? </p> <p>Indoor climbing is an increasingly popular form of rock climbing performed on artificial structures that attempt to mimic the experience of outdoor rock. Indoor rock climbing is one of the most adrenaline-pumping sports you can do. </p> <p>Let\'s climb  to indoor artificial walls at Kondapur  and train your body for outdoor climbing adventures.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/2/2/4/600_449197412.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This is a fun and safe sport for all ages in controlled environment. First timers are also welcome and encouraged to come and climb with ClimbOn! You don\'t need to come with a friend, you would  make many climber friends at the end of event. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/2/4/b/600_449197451.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Place and meet-up point</b></p> <p>CRAG Studio: Plot No 198, Opposite Harsha Toyota Show room, Gachibowli Miyapur Rd, Prashanth Nagar Colony, Kondapur.</p> <p><b>Please be there 15 minutes before the event.</b></p> <p><b>Cost:  Rs. 350 </b>(this includes climbing basics by instructors, club fee, trekking shoes, climbing gears,and emergency first-aid kit support). </p> <p><b>Attire: </b>Shorts or tracks that stretch well. </p> <p><b>Basic Fundamentals of Indoor Rock Climbing | Rock Climbing</b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>FAQ: </b></p> <p><b><i>Can I come if I\'ve never climbed before? <br/></i></b></p> <p>Yes of course. Studio have climbers of all different skill levels, and there\'s usually at least one person at each meetup who hasn\'t climbed before. It\'s not a problem.</p> <p><b><i>Do I have to bring gear? <br/></i></b>No, you can hire gear at the climbing studio. If you have your own gear, feel free to bring it along. Note that you don\'t need to bring any rope, carabiners or the like. </p> <p><b>Do I need strong arms for climbing?</b></p> <p>The most common myth about indoor climbing! Climbing and bouldering is all about getting your legs to do all the hard work.  Going climbing does make you stronger however as you do have to use your arms, but that happens over time! These climbing sessions are designed to help you learn the basics of footwork and progress faster and smoother.</p> <p>Any questions, please comment below, or call/whatsApp the Arvind at 9640431351 </p> <p><b>Disclaimer</b>: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times. By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.</p> '),(521,'1462817234000','Summer Special:Beat the Heat at an Indoor Swimming Pool and Learn Basic Swimming','230994509','1463209098000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230994509/','Contact Event Organiser:ClimbOn-Pravallika 7702523099','2016-05-14 10:00:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-05-14 06:58:00.000000','<p><b>Beat the Heat at an Indoor Swimming Pool:</b></p> <p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength,Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core,Endurance,Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 200/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(522,'1462188223000','From mats to messy mud: Mud kabbadi,Stargazing n Much More@ a random farm','230809156','1463483335000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230809156/','Climb-On Prudhvi-9908023223, Climb-On Pallavi-7674070563','2016-05-14 15:30:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2016-05-17 11:08:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/3/6/a/600_448264970.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/0/4/3/600_449633315.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/1/8/7/600_448264487.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Pics from past events of ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Welcome to the leisure face of \"Climb On\". </b></p> <p>At Climb On, along with organizing adventure activities like trekking, climbing, hiking , bouldering, etc. we also aim to make you feel closer to the nature and living your world to the fullest with an experience like never before.</p> <p>This event is about enjoying and appreciating simple adventure in nature. You are seriously active when the sun is no more, If you love and enjoy exploring the great outdoors, adventures, fun in natural environment during NIGHTFALL\'S, the moon and the stars are just the perfect companion to a night walk. Same time enjoy meeting new friends with similar interest.</p> <p>It just doesn\'t get much better than camping in Hyderabad outside with friends &amp; family - Food on the grill, a new moon, games around you, enjoying the great outdoors, songs &amp; stories around the campfire, nothing could be better than this for a weekend.</p> <p><b>Highlights of the event:</b></p> <p><b>a) Mud Kabaddi (Kabbadi in mud), mud wrestling, tug of war, and many other mud activities</b></p> <p><i>Lets come out from your marvelous mat at home to a messy mud at a farm. You wont realize that mud has many health benefits. Just google it out, you will find many. Moreover, it also works as stress reliever as the mud therapy is soothing, relaxing and calming.</i></p> <p><b>b) Night camping, bone fire, full on music, dance and masti, ghost stories, sharing sweet memories</b></p> <p>c) Stargazing</p> <p><b>d) Trekking</b></p> <p><b>e)An exciting experience of living a life </b><b>in a farm setup near a village</b></p> <p>Yes, you read it right! <b>HAI NA SUPER EXCITING? </b></p> <p><b>Where?</b></p> <p>At a random farm. Just across the border from Hyderabad, this is one of our favorites. Got some excellent sites that are right on the shoreline of beautiful fields. Distance: 90kms away from Uppal on Warangal Highway (2hrs drive)</p> <p><b>Meetup Point: </b>Uppal X roads, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Date of event:</b></p> <p>On Saturday 14th May 4:30 pm to 15th May 1:00pm. 1D/1N.</p> <p><b>How do I participate?</b></p> <p>Book your slot, just join the waiting list and make the payment.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/4/c/e/600_449574478.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p>1) A pair of old cloths which you don\'t mind throwing away - for mud activities</p> <p>2) A plastic bag to carry your muddy clothes.</p> <p>3) Sports shoes, preferable old shoes.</p> <p>4) Torch with extra batteries,</p> <p>5) Sleeping bag or just a blanket,</p> <p>6) a water bottle.</p> <p>7) A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p>8) Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><b>Note:</b> No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. Its just all about having fun.</p> <p><b>Tentative Itinerary </b></p> <p><b>Day 1 </b>:Meet us at 3:30PM at meeting point</p> <p>6PM: Reach at farm, Pitch tents</p> <p>6PM - 9PM - Its music and dance around the bon-fire, camping, Dinner, ghost stories, night trekking.</p> <p>10PM: Star gazing and capturing some stars with eyes of camera :) after that time to sleep</p> <p><b>Day 2:</b></p> <p>5:30 AM: Wakeup Call</p> <p>6AM: Start the day with a healthy breakfast, enjoying the view, Then Mud Games(kabaddi, mud wrestling, tug of war, and many more) and start back by afternoon.</p> <p><b>Tariff: </b>Rs.600 per head (Limited seats only), which Includes:</p> <p>a. Food (Veg &amp; No n Veg) : Dinner, B/fast, Bon-fire snacks -Barbeque.</p> <p>b. Camping gears</p> <p>c. Activities</p> <p>d. Campsite charges.</p> <p><b>Pay 200/- in advance to confirm your slot</b>.. Please find payment link/details below</p> <p><i><b>Payment link - <a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/from-mats-to-messy-mud-mud-kabbadi-and-other/\">Click here to pay</a> </b></i></p> <p><i>Once payment is transferred, request you to add your transaction ID to comments below to confirm your slot. For any more questions, our phone lines are open. </i></p> <p><b>Direct numbers : </b>Climb-On Prudhvi-9908023223, Climb-On Pallavi-7674070563</p> '),(523,'1462712645000','Let\'s Play: Childhood Games @ Botanical Garden','230965209','1463291107000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230965209/','Climb On Pravallika - 7842137464 Babu Reddy - 9966693964','2016-05-15 06:00:00.000000','past','kondapur','Hyderabad','in','Botanical Garden',0,'2016-05-15 05:45:00.000000','<p>Relish your childhood fun with games like pithoo (7 Stones), langdi tang, vish amrit , kho-kho and many more…</p> <p><b>Timing</b>: 6:00 AM to 9:00 AM</p> <p><b>Games</b>: </p> <p>·  Kho Kho</p> <p>·  7 Stones</p> <p>·  Blindfold</p> <p>·  Langdi Tang</p> <p>·  Dog and the Bone</p> <p>·  Vish Amrit</p> <p>·  Tug of War </p> <p><b>Note</b>: These are tentative list of games. We will play based on time availability and everyone\'s interest.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/7/2/c/600_449765932.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Pics from Last event of ClimbOn</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gU7Q_q1hlQc\">Fun from last event</a></p> <p><b>What to Wear</b>:  </p> <p>• Tee shirt</p> <p>• Tracks / Shorts </p> <p>• Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>• Cap advised</p> <p>• Water 2 liter</p> <p>• Snacks to Fill On to Climb On.</p> <p><b>Cost breakup: </b>Rs 65 ; Kids(below 10yrs)  entry FREE FREE FREE </p> <p>15 Park entrance (You need to pay)</p> <p>50 Club fund </p> <p><i><b>Note</b>: </i><i>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><b>Swimming (Optional)</b></p> <p>Guys, post this game event, we plan to go for swimming  (optional; Rs 200) at Seasons Indoor Pool Kondapur to cool us down, followed by breakfast (optional; pay for your own) at some nearby Bandi/restaurant. If interested, Please RSVP through the link below. Bring  your towel and swimming costumes.</p> <p><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230965613/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230965613/</a></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(524,'1462714697000','Summer Special:Beat the Heat at an Indoor Swimming Pool and Learn Basic Swimming','230965613','1463294684000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230965613/','Contact Event Organiser:ClimbOn-Pravallika 7702523099','2016-05-15 11:00:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-05-15 06:44:00.000000','<p><b>Beat the Heat at an Indoor Swimming Pool:</b></p> <p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength,Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core,Endurance,Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 200/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(525,'1463625463000','Into the lap of nature, trek to beaches in Gokarna on Friday eve. May 21-22','231234682','1464004749000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231234682/','ClimbOn Pravallika -7702523099','2016-05-20 21:00:00.000000','past','Nr Gachibowli ORR Entrance','Hyderabad','in','Punjabi Rasoi',0,'2016-05-23 11:59:00.000000','<p><b>Organiser\'s Experience:</b></p> <p>Cosseted in the lap of nature, the beaches in <b>Gokarna</b> are pristine and make for a riveting holiday experience. Add the fun and excitement of trekking along the beach and unfold the beauty of this vicinity.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/1/1/f/600_446128959.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Sathodi Falls:-</b></p> <p>The Sathodi Falls are formed by several streams near the Kallaramarane Ghat, 32 km from Yellapur. The falls are about 15 meters in height. After flowing from the waterfall the streams then flow into the backwaters of the Kodasalli Dam, into the Kali River. Owing to the picturesque view, the place is fondly called “Mini Niagara”. These falls form an integral part of the Ganeshgudi forest range.</p> <p><b>About:</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/b/3/9/600_446332025.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Gokarna is famous for its beautiful beaches and landscapes. The main beaches in Gokarna are the Gokarna beach, Kudle Beach, Om Beach, Half moon Beach and Paradise Beach (also known as Full moon). The Gokarna beach forms the coast of the town while the other four beaches lie to the south of Gokarna. Kudle and Om are around 6 km from Gokarna town along a muddy hill; they are accessible by rickshaw or foot. Half moon and Paradise are beyond Om beach and are accessible only by foot or boat. Om beach is named so because it is shaped like the auspicious ॐ [Om] symbol. Om beach is the only naturally Om shaped beach. Two other beaches - Paradise and Half Moon - are smaller and remote beaches.</p> <p><b>Outline:</b><br/>Day 1 : Beach Trekking along the coastline from Gokarna Beach to Paradise Beach [ 12 km ]<br/>Day 2 : sathodi falls</p> <p><b>Indepth:</b></p> <p>Friday 9pm : Bus to Gokarna</p> <p>Sat 10am : Lunch &amp; Beach Trek from Gokarna - Om beach - Half Moon - Paradise / Gokarna (12 km Approx)</p> <p>Sat 8pm : Stay in Gokarna [Accommodation is separate in tents for Men and woman]</p> <p>Sun 4am : Wakeup call</p> <p>Sun 5am : Gokarna to Sathodi Falls</p> <p>Sun 8am : Trekking in Sathodi falls and click some cool pics</p> <p>Sun 8pm: Bus to Hyderabad.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts, at the beach, a pair of shorts would be a good.</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. - Sleeping bag or thick blanket and a proper rucksack (backpack) (both are must) and some plastic covers</p> <p>- Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p>- some snacks to climb on.</p> <p>- Torch light is must.</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b><br/>Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun.</p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.<br/>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</p> <p><b>Damages:</b><br/>2900 /- Will share the cost if it is more or less.<br/>[ Food is excluded]</p> <p><b>Payment Details:</b> You will be in waiting list unless you make the payment.</p> <p>Name: NATHI PRAVALLIKA</p> <p>IFSC Code: CITI0000006</p> <p>Account No: 5281411553</p> <p>Please pay 1000/- as an advance payment to confirm your slot.</p> <p>Contact Details :ClimbOn Pravallika 7702523099</p> <p>Once payment is transferred, request you to add your transaction ID to comments below, we will confirm your slot.<br/>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> '),(526,'1461822035000','Night Ride!! Full on Fun!!','230709217','1464042098000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230709217/','ClimbOn Pallavi - 7674070563','2016-05-21 22:00:00.000000','past','gachibowli','Hyderabad','in','IIT circle',0,'2016-05-23 22:21:00.000000','<p>How about a Night Ride on unplanned destination...</p> <p>It\'s hot outside so let\'s hit the road at night and come back early in the morning...</p> <p>Night ride is a lot of fun and it will test out your skills!</p> <p>   \"Jithe jawange gadi modange\"</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/c/0/b/600_449415371.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/b/1/2/600_449415122.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Tentative Plan:</b></p> <p>9 pm: Ride to Random Place (Warangal Highway,ORR, etc.)</p> <p>1 am-2am: Break (will play some fun games)</p> <p>4 am: Breakfast at Random Bandi</p> <p>5 am: Watch sunrise</p> <p>6 am: Bye Bye!!</p> <p><b>Please have your tanks full.  Do follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing halmet, using car seat belt etc.</b></p> <p>Things to bring: - </p> <p>- Water : 2 litres must. Please use reusable bottles.</p> <p> - Torch light. </p> <p> - Camera to capture awesome photos.[Optional] </p> <p> - Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Club Fee: 100/-  </b>(includes First Aid )[Food and Petrol excluded]</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/230709217/\">Click here to pay online</a></p> <p><b>Note:</b> No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event.</p> <p>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm. This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p><b>Disclaimer:</b> The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.</p> '),(527,'1463571250000','Let\'s climb the rocks of Peerancheru......','231214104','1463892570000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231214104/','Meetup point at Morine bakery, nanal nagar X roads (Hand Symbol)','2016-05-22 06:00:00.000000','past','Near PBEL City, behind Shadan Medical College ','Hyderabad','in','Peerancheru',0,'2016-05-22 04:49:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/b/e/9/600_445635337.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Peeran Cheruvu is on the road to Gandipet and is an awesome location for rock climbing and bouldering.</p> <p>Itinerary: Exploratory trek so nothing is planned. Responsible Bouldering: Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. We request all members to be socially responsible and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology.</p> <p>6:00AM : Assemble at meetup point at Morine bakery, nanal nagar X roads (Hand Symbol)<br/>6:15 AM : Start to Peerancheru<br/>6:30AM : Reach the place and event begins<br/>****** Rock climbing*****<br/>********Bouldering******­**<br/>******Rappelling*******<br/>12:00 PM : Tired?? Let’s get back to our town. TaTa, Bubye :)</p> <p>Important Instructions:<br/>1) No smoking/alcohol and No littering<br/>2) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable<br/>3) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention.<br/>4) If you need any, bring it to the organizers notice.</p> <p>Things to bring: Wear Full track pants (avoid jeans). T-shirts(half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>Wear sport/trekking shoes only<br/>sun cap<br/>water bottles - 2x1 lit<br/>get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch on to climb on after and during the trek.<br/>Get your camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/5/e/600_445713374.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/5/4/f/600_435969551.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/8/0/e/600_435595310.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>RSVP Rules: We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case, just its a humble request to please inform the Organiser a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i></p> <p>Meeting Place: Mehdipatnam/Reti bowli @ Morine Bakery<br/>Transport: By personal Transport<br/>Cost: Rs 100 towards club.</p> <p>Contact Details: CLIMBON ROHITH - 9676722155</p> <p>Difficulty - Moderate.</p> <p>Please Be On time.</p> '),(528,'1463380703000','Evening Ride to Golconda and Potluck','231157662','1464019773000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231157662/','Climb On Arvind - 9640431351','2016-05-22 15:45:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-05-23 16:09:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride to Golconda Fort. Starting time is 4:00 pm from HBC bike station Gachibowli. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/6/d/7/600_450125847.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>History of Golconda Fort</b> : The 13th century Golconda Fort was built by the Kakatiya kings. The existing structure was later built by Qutub Shahi Kings into a massive fort with granite walls having eight gates and 87 bastions spread upto 7 kms, in circumference over a span of 62 years. Golconda Fort, popularly known in Telugu as \"Golla Konda\", which means \"Shepherd\'s Hill\", has an exotic story behind it. In 1143, on the rocky hill known as \'Mangalavaram\', a shepherd boy came across an image and conveyed to the Kakatiya king, who was ruling at that time. The 10 km long road from Golconda to outer Hyderabad was a fantastic market selling jewellery, diamonds, pearls and other gems, popular in all over the world. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/6/f/a/600_450125882.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Potluck: </b>A potluck is a gathering where each guest contributes a dish of food that is to be shared. Please comment below what u are planning 2 bring so that we can avoid duplication.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/7/3/6/600_450125942.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>PC:</b> From last cycling event of ClimbOn</p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p><b>Please carry an original ID card</b> like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station before 4:00pm </p> <p><b>Cost - </b>Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit and air pump and Paper Plates)</p> <p> [ Please bring exact change ] </p> <p><b>Own Bicycle Rent Cost</b> - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee  Rs 100/-</p> '),(529,'1460684394000','Climb On CRICKET - ChakDe','230387498','1464447175000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230387498/','ClimbOn Suman 99660 02025','2016-05-28 05:45:00.000000','past','Shamirpet','Hyderabad','in','English Willow Cricket Grounds',0,'2016-05-28 14:52:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/0/f/3/600_449896627.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/0/f/1/600_449896625.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Cost  :</b> Rs 250/per head  - this <b>doesn\'t</b> include transportation and food. Food will be shared equally. <a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/230387498/\">Payment link </a></p> <p><b>Important Instructions:  </b></p> <p>1) No smoking and no alcohol <br/>2) No littering, no pollution of water </p> <p><b>NOTE</b>: Please answer all the questions. </p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Suman 99660 02025</p> '),(530,'1463986475000','Narsapur forest Exploration and Lots of Fun','231331425','1464515811000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231331425/','Balanagar X roads, Bus stop towards Jeedimetla at 6am','2016-05-29 06:00:00.000000','past','Balanagar','Hyderabad','in','Balanagar X Roads',0,'2016-05-29 09:56:00.000000','<p><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Narsapur,_Medak_district\">Narsapur forest</a> is 45 KM north from Hyderabad in the Medak district. spread between Gummadidala and Narsapur towns. This forest spans over 30sq km and has a mini-ghat section, thick forest, a hill, a large lake, a good number of birds, butterflies, varied flora and fauna and our ancestors (monkeys)</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/6/3/600_443014659.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b></p> <p>6 am meting at balanagar and start to forest.</p> <p>Exploratory trek so nothing is planned. Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. We request all members to be socially responsible and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/6/c/600_443014668.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/7/9/600_443014681.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Instructions</b></p> <p>1) No smoking/alcohol and No littering <br/>2) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable <br/>3) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention. <br/>4) If you need any, bring it to the organizers notice. </p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b> Wear Full track pants (avoid jeans). T-shirts(half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>Wear sport/trekking shoes only </p> <p>sun cap</p> <p><b> Mandatory things </b></p> <p>Water bottles - 2x1 lit MUST</p> <p>Get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch MUST  to climb on after and during the trek.<br/>Get your camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p><i>RSVP Rules: We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP  \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case,  just its a humble request to please inform the Organiser a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i> </p> <p><b>Meeting Place:</b> Balanagar X roads bus stop towards Jeedimetla. </p> <p><b>Transport: </b>We will be traveling on our vehicles (bikes and cars),on fuel contribution basis. This is a half day trip and we shall be back by 1 PM.</p> <p><b>Cost:</b> Rs 100 towards club. </p> <p><b>Contact Details: ClimbOn Rohith-9676722155</b></p> <p><b>Difficulty </b>- Moderate.</p> <p>Please Be On time.</p> '),(531,'1462816743000','Indoor Climbing with ClimbOn (For the beginners also)','230994364','1464583485000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230994364/','Climb-On Arvind (9640431351)','2016-05-29 17:00:00.000000','past','Gachibowli Miyapur Road','Hyderabad','in','Crag Studio',0,'2016-05-30 04:44:00.000000','<p>It\'s heating up outside, but it doesn\'t mean that your adventure activities should be stopped in this summer. Why should you not be having climbing adventure at an indoor studio?</p> <p>Indoor climbing is an increasingly popular form of rock climbing performed on artificial structures that attempt to mimic the experience of outdoor rock. Indoor rock climbing is one of the most adrenaline-pumping sports you can do.</p> <p>Let\'s climb to indoor artificial walls at Kondapur and train your body for outdoor climbing adventures.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/2/2/4/600_449197412.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This is a fun and safe sport for all ages in controlled environment. First timers are also welcome and encouraged to come and climb with ClimbOn! You don\'t need to come with a friend, you would make many climber friends at the end of event.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/2/4/b/600_449197451.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Place and meet-up point</b></p> <p>CRAG Studio: Plot No 198, Opposite Harsha Toyota Show room, Gachibowli Miyapur Rd, Prashanth Nagar Colony, Kondapur.</p> <p><b>Please be there 15 minutes before the event.</b></p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 350 </b>(this includes climbing basics by instructors, club fee, trekking shoes, climbing gears,and emergency first-aid kit support).</p> <p><b>Attire: </b>Shorts or tracks that stretch well.</p> <p><b>Basic Fundamentals of Indoor Rock Climbing | Rock Climbing</b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>FAQ: </b></p> <p><b><i>Can I come if I\'ve never climbed before?<br/></i></b></p> <p>Yes of course. Studio have climbers of all different skill levels, and there\'s usually at least one person at each meetup who hasn\'t climbed before. It\'s not a problem.</p> <p><b><i>Do I have to bring gear?<br/></i></b>No, you can hire gear at the climbing studio. If you have your own gear, feel free to bring it along. Note that you don\'t need to bring any rope, carabiners or the like.</p> <p><b>Do I need strong arms for climbing?</b></p> <p>The most common myth about indoor climbing! Climbing and bouldering is all about getting your legs to do all the hard work. Going climbing does make you stronger however as you do have to use your arms, but that happens over time! These climbing sessions are designed to help you learn the basics of footwork and progress faster and smoother.</p> <p>Any questions, please comment below, or call/whatsApp Arvind at 9640431351</p> <p><b>Disclaimer</b>: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times. By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.</p> '),(532,'1461734156000','Lets explore the Beautiful City of Gates - Aurangabad - Ajanta and Ellora caves','230681166','1465301881000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230681166/','climbOn Pallavi - 7674070563','2016-06-03 17:30:00.000000','past','Lingampally Railway Station','Hyderabad','in','Lingampally Railway station',0,'2016-06-07 12:18:00.000000','<p><b>Open to anyone those who are FIT </b></p> <p>Aurangabad serves as a major tourist hub that offers a wide array of network services to visit some of the most important attractions around it. Also, as a city, Aurangabad fascinates with its culture and lifestyle, offering discerning tourists a wide gamut of hospitality.</p> <p>Recently declared the ‘Tourism Capital of Maharashtra’, Aurangabad is an important hub in the state’s tourism sector with its close connection to such significant tourist destinations as caves of Ajanta and Ellora which have been declared ‘World Heritage Sites’ by UNESCO as well as the famous Mughal monument BibikaMaqbara. </p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Places we are planning to visit:</b></p> <p>1. Ellora Caves </p> <p>2. Daulatabad fort </p> <p>3. Ajanta Caves </p> <p>4. Bibi-Ka-Maqbara </p> <p><b>Bibi-Ka-Maqbara (Mini Taj Mahal)</b></p> <p>It was built by Azam Shah, son of Aurangzeb, in 1678 in memory of his mother. It bears a striking resemblance to the famous Taj Mahal, the mausoleum of his grandmother, Mumtaz Mahal. </p> <p>Due to the strong resemblance, it is also called the Dakkhani Taj (Taj of the Deccan).</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/b/6/6/600_449567974.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Ellora Caves</b></p> <p>Ellora is known for Hindu, Buddhist and Jain cave temples built during (6th and 9th centuries) the rule of the Kalachuri, Chalukya and Rashtrakuta dynasties. Ellora is an UNESCO World Heritage Site and forms one of major tourist attraction in Marathwada region of Maharashtra. Ellora represents the epitome of Indian rock-cut architecture. The 34 \"caves\" are actually structures excavated out of the vertical face of the Charanandri hills. The 17 Hindu (caves 13–29), 12 Buddhist (caves 1–12) and 5 Jain (caves 30–34) caves, built in proximity, demonstrate the religious harmony prevalent during this period of Indian history.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/7/f/2/600_449391186.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Devagiri-Daulatabad fort</b><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daulatabad,_Maharashtra#cite_note-1\">&lt;/a&gt;</p> <p>Lord Shiva is believed to have been stayed on the hills surrounding this region. Hence the fort was originally known as Devagiri literally (Hills of Gods). It is also considered to be one of the seven wonders of Maharashtra and a developing tourist spot.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/7/f/5/600_449391189.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Ajanta Caves</b></p> <p>The caves include paintings and sculptures that are masterpieces of Buddhist religious art, with figures of the Buddha and depictions of the Jataka tales. The caves were built in two phases starting around the 2nd century BCE, with the second group of caves built around 400–650 CE according to older accounts.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/5/600_449460837.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Difficulty Level</b>: Medium</p> <p><b>Tentative Itinerary:</b></p> <p><b>Friday</b>: 6:00 pm Start From Hyderabad </p> <p><b>Saturday:</b></p> <p>5:00 am: Reach Aurangabad and freshen up.</p> <p>6:30 am: Start to Ajanta Caves</p> <p>09:30 am:   Reaching Ajanta caves</p> <p>Start exploring Ajanta caves followed by a lunch brk in the meanwhile.</p> <p>5:30 pm: We ll start again to Aurangabad </p> <p>9:00 pm: Dinner and go to sleep.</p> <p><b>Sunday:</b></p> <p>5:00AM: Good morning wake up call and be ready in an hour.</p> <p>6:30AM: We\'ll start our journey to the Ellora caves, the world\'s heritage site and explore all 34 caves till noon (including lunch offcourse :p).</p> <p>2:00PM: We will move on to the Devagiri fort.</p> <p>5:00PM: We will start to Aurangabad and visit either Bibi ka maqbara</p> <p>9:00PM: Catch your train/bus.</p> <p><b>Monday:</b> Reaching Hyderabad........Ta Ta Bye Bye.....:).</p> <p><b>Things to bring: - </b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts and T-shirts</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. </p> <p>- Sleeping bag or blanket</p> <p> - Water : 2 litres must. Please use reusable bottles.</p> <p> - Torch light with extra set of batteries. </p> <p> - A proper rucksack (backpack) to keep all of the above things </p> <p> - Camera to capture awesome places.[Optional] </p> <p> - Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Important Instructions</b>: (Please read)</p> <p>1) No smoking and No alcohol </p> <p>2) No littering, no pollution of water </p> <p>3) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable </p> <p>4) Accommodation will be separate for Men and woman.</p> <p>5) Food will be mostly vegetarian. </p> <p>6) We carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers 7) if you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately. </p> <p>8) If you cant swim don\'t go deep into the water </p> <p>9)Organizer word is final</p> <p>10) We will be staying at tents or basic budget hotels which will have basic amenities. So do not expect luxury :)</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event</p> <p>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm. This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p> <b>Damages</b>: 2900/- Ball park figure [Transport + Accommodation + Club Fund + Organiser reimbursement] Will share  the cost if it is more or less. [ <b>Food is excluded</b>]</p> <p><b>Pay 1000/- in advance to confirm your slot</b>.. Please find payment link/details below</p> <p><i><b>Payment link - &lt;a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/230681166/\"&gt;Click here to pay</a><br/></b></i></p> <p><i><b>-OR-</b></i></p> <p><i><b>Payment details - </b></i></p> <p>Name: Pallavi Gupta<br/>Bank Name &amp; Branch: ICICI, Punjagutta<br/>Account No: 020201564996<br/>IFSC Code: ICIC0000202</p> <p><i><b>Note:</b> Please add your self to the waiting list; you will be moved to confirm list once your payment is done and share the payment details in comment section</i></p> '),(533,'1464877693000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','231594231','1465052031000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231594231/','ClimbOn Prudhvi 9908023223','2016-06-04 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-06-04 14:53:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 25 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and  a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\".  </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.  </p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 6:00-8:00 PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/0/600_448372560.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/d/600_448372573.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/6/600_448372582.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/d/600_448372589.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40:  Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45:  Warm up exercises </p> <p>6.00: Game shuru </p> <p>8.00: End game and feedback </p> <p>8.15: Tata bye bye. </p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet. </p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 200 per head (include club fee + ground rent )</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Prudhvi 9908023223</p> '),(534,'1464706611000','Morning Cycling @ Necklace Road and Dog Park Photography','231535756','1466087703000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231535756/','ClimbOn Sandeep - 8008004360','2016-06-05 05:30:00.000000','past','Necklace Road, Opp Sanjeeviah Park','Hyderabad','in','Necklace Road Bike Station',0,'2016-06-16 14:35:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride at the Necklace road bike station. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/3/5/d/600_448597725.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Necklace Road is a boulevard in Hyderabad, adjoining the Hussain Sagar lake, which connects NTR Gardens to Sanjeevaiah Park. Named after the first and the famous Necklace Road in Mumbai\'s Marine Drive. The road from Sanjivaiah park connects to the Tank Bund road which in turn connects to the NTR Gardens completing a circle. This stretch of road, along with the Tank Bund, appears in the form of a necklace as seen from the sky - and hence the name.</p> <p>Also Hyderabad is known as DOG Lovers paradise - and Dog park is right across the HBC cycling station. We will get to see some amazing cute dogs and will do some photography. It will be Super fun</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/0/4/6/600_450604166.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p><b>Please carry an original ID card</b> like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. </p> <p><b>Cost - </b>Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit and air pump)</p> <p> [ Please bring exact change ] </p> <p><b>Own Bicycle Rent Cost</b> - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee  Rs 100/-</p> '),(535,'1463994346000','Ride To Bidar Fort and Photography June 11','231332581','1466418859000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231332581/','Call Sandeep 8008004360','2016-06-11 06:00:00.000000','past',' (B.H.E.L check post)','Hyderabad','in','Lingampally',0,'2016-06-20 10:34:00.000000','<p>Bidar city (<b> 3 h 28 min (145.8 km) via NH 65</b> )  in the Indian state of Karnataka. It is also called as crown of Karnataka. Bidar city is known for its <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bidri_ware\">Bidri</a><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Handicraft\">handicraft</a> products. <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Manjira_River\">Manjira River</a> is one of the main rivers supplying drinking water to Bidar. Bidar is a charming district- one of its charms being a very bracing climate practically throughout the district and for the greater part of the year.</p> <p>Bidar has lots of historical monuments from the Bahmani era. The structure of the great Mahmud Gawan Arabic University is reminiscent of the rich architecture of the Bahmani era. The <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bidar_Fort\">Bidar Fort</a> situated next to the city is one of the biggest forts in India</p> <p>Places to visit in Bidar</p> <p><b>Bidar Fort: </b>The Bidar Fort in Karnataka is a beautiful creation of the then ruler of Karnataka which is surrounded by a triple-moated wall. It is constructed out of red rock and had an intricate battlement and a baronial gateway. If you ever visit the Fort, you will get to see the crumbling ruins of the bastions and gates. Other features of the Bidar Fort at Karnataka are the royal baths and spacious kitchens, a large audience hall and wide pleasure-pavilions, all in a state of ruin. But this grand edifice still stands the ravages of time as a silent tribute to the past glory of the Bidar Kingdom.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/9/0/1/600_445158689.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/4/1/c/600_266622012.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Rangeen Mahal</b>: The Rang Mahal of the Bidar Fort of Karnataka has intricately carved beautiful wooden pillars. You will be amazed to see the wonderful tiles that are engraved with Persian couplets. The exquisite mother-of-pearl inlay work in the Bidar Fort is really worth seeing. There is a Madrassa of Khwaja Mahamud Gawan adjacent to it. The madrassa is an Islamic seminary constructed by the prime minister of the Bahmani court, Khwaja Mahamud Gawan. We will try to get permission to see this but is not guaranteed.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/a/2/d/600_445158989.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Narasimha Jhira Cave Temple</b>: Narasimha Swami Temple is known to be a Sacred Temple for a Hindu devotee. This water cave temple virtually runs into a cave with water measuring 300 meters. The temple is a powerful deity of Lord Narasimha as per the belief<br/>where one has to wade through water up to chest height to have darshan of the idol. It’s a thrilling experience to travel through the cave as there is<br/>natural water within it. The bats and owls sitting on the rooftop of cave are harmless to the devotees. The place is surrounded by picturesque valley.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/6/3/8/600_266622552.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Gurudwara Nanak Jhira Sahib</b>: Gurudwara Nanak Jhira Sahib, which was built in the year 1948 and, is dedicated to the first Sikh Guru Nanak Dev Ji. The gurudwara comprises of Darbar Sahib, Diwan Hall and Langar Hall. In the Sukhaasan Room, Guru Granth Sahib, the holy book of Sikh, has been placed. Opposite to the front stairs of the gurudwara, there is a holy water tank. It is believed that a holy dip in the tank is enough to cleanse the body and soul, of the devotee of all the sins.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/6/9/2/600_266622642.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary</b>:</p> <p>6:00am: Meetup at BHEL Gate Lingampally</p> <p>Start towards Bidar by National Highway 9 ( NH9 ) </p> <p>7:00am Break for breakfast on the way</p> <p>10:30am Reach bidar fort and explore then continue to other places mentioned above and few more in bidar till 5pm</p> <p>5:00pm start back to Hyderabad</p> <p>9:00pm Tata Bye Bye</p> <p><b>What to wear:</b></p> <p>• Wear any dress comfortable to you</p> <p>• Wear Shoes</p> <p>• One extra pair of dress because in Narasimha Swami temple we have to go in water for darshan.</p> <p>• Towel</p> <p>• As we will be starting early, wear something to keep you warm.</p> <p><b>What to bring:</b></p> <p>• Water bottles - 2 x 1 litres </p> <p>• Hat or cap as it will be hot afternoons</p> <p>• Electrolyte or Glucose</p> <p>• Camera</p> <p>• Any medications physician prescribed</p> <p>• Loads of energy.</p> <p><b>Damages </b>: Rs 100 Towards Club fund</p> <p><b>Guidelines</b>: This is a historical place . No venturing towards steep cliff drops .</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Sandeep 8008004360</p> <p><b>Difficulty</b> : Easy</p> <p><b>Transport</b>: Personal Vehicles If possible there will be pool and petrol cost will be shared</p> <p><b>This is important for bikers.</b></p> <p>Safety is considered first priority when it comes to riding motorbikes.</p> <p>• All the bikers will be educated of hand signs the group will be using during the ride. Everybody has to follow those signs without fail.</p> <p>• A helmet, any kind of jacket or hoodie (full sleeves) and shoes are mandatory as a part of riding gear.</p> <p>• Riders to carry their driving license, bike\'s registration, pollution and insurance certificates.  </p> <p>• Your bikes have to be at least above 150cc to participate.in this ride. Exception for Yamaha R15 and Honda CBR150</p> <p>PLEASE ANSWER ALL THE QUESTIONS. IF YOU DO NOT WE WILL NOT BE ABLE TO WAIT FOR YOU AND YOUR RSVP WILL BE CONSIDERED VOID.</p> <p><b>Disclaimer</b>: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times. By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.</p> '),(536,'1465458812000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','231766578','1465671375000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231766578/','ClimbOn Prudhvi 9908023223','2016-06-11 21:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-06-11 18:56:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 4 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 9:30PM-12:00 AM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/0/600_448372560.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/d/600_448372573.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/6/600_448372582.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/d/600_448372589.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>9.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>9.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>9.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>10.00: Game shuru</p> <p>12.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>12.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 200 per head (include club fee + ground rent )</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Prudhvi 9908023223</p> '),(537,'1461722758000','Nature trek to Matheran (June 17-19)','230677589','1466436721000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230677589/','ClimbOn Pallavi - 7674070563 Babu Reddy- 9966693964','2016-06-17 20:30:00.000000','past','Nampally','Hyderabad','in','Hyderabad Railway Station at Nampally',0,'2016-06-20 15:32:00.000000','<p>One of the best places to trek in India - Matheran</p> <p>Matheran is a small hill station in Raigad district of Maharashtra. Located on the Western Ghats range at an elevation of around 800 m (2,625 feet) above sea level. It is located around 90 km from Mumbai, and 120 km from Pune. It is one of the most ecologically sensitive hill stations in the country and no form of motorised transport is allowed. The name Matheran means either \"forest on top\" or \"mother forest\".</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/c/b/3/600_449388307.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Moving around in Matheran</b></p> <p>The only modes of transport, on the red soiled roads, are on horseback or by man-pulled rickshaw or on foot. It is one of the few places in the world where all motorised vehicles are banned which makes the place unique. That calls for trekking all the way.</p> <p><b>Height</b> </p> <p>At an elevation of about 800m (2,625 ft) above Mean Sea Level.</p> <p><b>Area</b></p> <p>5000 acres or eight sq miles</p> <p><b>Climate </b><br/>Matheran has cool and moderate climate. During monsoon rainfall is heavy and it provides a different charm. The climate after the rains is very pleasant.</p> <p><b>Topography</b></p> <p>Level with sparse undulations. The topmost layer of rock is of soft porous iron-clay with abundant small black boulders. The surface is covered by red soil with less humus.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/c/9/3/600_449435987.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>About our trek</b></p> <p>We will stay in a booked Guest House .</p> <p><b>Difficulty Level</b>: Medium (Approx 15-20 kms in 2 days)</p> <p>17th June 2016 (Friday)</p> <p>Leave by Train No 17032 Mumbai Express which will depart from Nampally / Begumpet station at 8.40 pm</p> <p>18th June 2016 (Saturday)</p> <p>11:00 am:  Reach Karjat <br/>11:30 am: Local train to Nerul <br/>12.30 pm : Trek to Matheran /Board Toy train to Metheran which is an awesome journey<br/> 2.30 pm: Reach Matheran and<a href=\"http://s.igmhb.com/click?v=SU46MTE2NTI1OjEzOTk6Y2hlY2s6OTViNjUzMGFlYjllNjFlNGNlMGNmMzU4ZTczNmY1Mjk6ei0yNDkyLTg3NzM0NjUzOnd3dy5tZWV0dXAuY29tOjMzNjU0MzpiMjZmYTQ0NmY4MjkyNTMzYzgxODkyZmY1NzI4OTY3NTplNDY0NGU1Zjg1NjA0NTgyOTg2NDRiN2Y3ZDQwMDdjNzoxOmRhdGFfc3MsMTA5OXgxOTIwO2RhdGFfcmMsMztkYXRhX2ZiLG5vOzo0NDIxMjk3OnZ3b3B0LDA&amp;subid=g-87734653-52128aaa073e42e88d2929b7cb4d0c87-&amp;data_ss=1099x1920&amp;data_rc=3&amp;data_fb=no&amp;data_tagname=A&amp;data_ct=image_only&amp;data_clickel=link&amp;data_sid=490ff72c6c75738f781ab15382791b21\"> check</a> into Guest House and we will cover few places like Sunset point and Chaorlete Lake after a break.  <br/>10 pm: Dinner, Chat up and Sleep</p> <p>19th June (Sunday)</p> <p>4:30 am: Wake Up Call <br/>5 am - 2pm : We will cover some awesome places like Sunrise point,Alexandar Point,One tree point and do shopping in Matheran Market <br/> 2pm - Pack luggage and start to Karjat</p> <p>4.50 pm - Catch Konark Express from Karjat</p> <p>20th June (Monday):</p> <p>7:00 am / 7.50 am: Reach  Begumpet /Secunderabad Station.</p> <p><b>Itinerary</b>may change depending on situations</p> <p><b>Things to bring : </b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts[Comfortable]</p> <p>- Raincoat</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. </p> <p>- Sleeping bag or thick blanket</p> <p> - Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p> - Torch light with extra set of batteries. </p> <p> - A proper rucksack (backpack) to keep all of the above things </p> <p> - Camera to capture awesome places.[Optional] </p> <p> - Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Important Instructions:  </b></p> <p> <b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm. This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p><b> Damages: 2900/- Ball park figure</b> [Transport + Accommodation] Will share  the cost if it is more or less. [ Food is excluded]</p> <p><b>Pay 1000/- in advance to confirm your slot</b>.. Please find payment link below</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/230677589/\">Click here to pay</a></p> '),(538,'1465749231000','Exclusive Scooter & Motor bike Ride to Anantagiri Hills & Kotpalli Reservoir','231840089','1466220428000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231840089/','See us at Morine Bakery, Nanal Nagar (Big hand statue at the junction), 2nd Signal after M\'patnam Bus stand. Call your organizer Uday@ 9666531565','2016-06-18 05:30:00.000000','past','Nanal nagar X roads','Hyderabad','in','Morine bakery',0,'2016-06-18 03:27:00.000000','<p><b>*Update: Motorbikes are also allowed along with scooters.</p> <p>ClimbOn Ride</b> - It\'s a superb feeling riding a gearless scooter in city. The kind of convenience these vehicles offer is impeccable, from commuting to work every day or in shopping groceries or to drop mom and sister at the bus stop every morning. If they could make our lives that easy in the city, why shouldn\'t we be taking these fun machines to the highways and see how much more fun they could offer.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/5/f/600_451053375.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>(</b>All Models and all Makes of scooters such as<b> Activa, Jupiter, Wego, Access, Pep are allowed to participate in this ride, irrespective of their engine capacity.) No Motorbikes </b>please<b>. This is exclusively for gearless scooters.</b><br/>Let us go on a beautiful early morning ride to Anantagiri Hills on our gearless scooters.</p> <p><b>*Update: Motorbikes are also allowed along with scooters.</b></p> <p>Ananthagiri Hills are located at Vikarabad, Ranga Reddy district, TG, India. It is 5 kms from Vikarabad and 80 Kms from Hyderabad. The water flows from these hills to Osman Sagar and Himayat Sagar. It is one of the dense forests in Telangana. Ananthagiri Temple is located in this forested area. It is the Birthplace of Musi river, which flows through Hyderabad.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/7/6/600_451053398.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What do we visit at Anantagiri Hills?</b></p> <p><b>Anantha Padmanabhaswamy Temple:</b></p> <p>It is one of the earliest habitat areas. Ancient caves, medieval fort structures and temple show the antiquity of this area.</p> <p><b>Kotpalli Reservoir:</b></p> <p>This is a reservoir located 28 Kms from Ananthagiri hills. Very often, Kayaking is also available at this place.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/8/6/600_451053414.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Haritha Resort:</b></p> <p>Harita resort operated by Govt. of Telangana has a swimming pool in it and serves buffet lunch as well. (If a dhaba is preferred, we shall have lunch at a Dhaba).</p> <p><b> Schedule</b>:</p> <p>5:30AM-Meeting at Morine Bakery, Nanal Nagar (2nd signal after Mehandipatnam bus stop, Land Mark: Big Hand sign statue at the intersection of the road.)</p> <p>5:30-6:00AM-Briefing of Hand signs and orientation on safe riding habits.</p> <p>06:00 AM-Start towards Ananthagiri Hills</p> <p>07:30 AM-Stop for Breakfast &amp; Chai at Chevella</p> <p>08:30 AM-Arrive at Anantapadmanabha Swamy temple</p> <p>09:00 AM-Go to the fantastic view point at the hills. Spend time clicking pictures and a lot of selfies for sure J<br/>10:00 AM- Start to Kotpalli Reservoir</p> <p>10:40 AM- Reach the reservoir &amp; If available, we shall do Kayaking or chill out until we get back to our scooters.</p> <p>12:00 PM- Start back to Anantagiri hills, to visit Harita Resort and swim if the pool is open.<br/><b>(We can refresh at this place. Washrooms are available and they are clean)</b></p> <p>01:00 PM- Have lunch at the resort itself or we can go to a dhaba on the way back.</p> <p>04:00 PM- Back at Morine bakery, Hyd and disperse.</p> <p><b>*Update: Motorbikes are also allowed along with scooters.</p> <p>Safety Instructions:<br/>This scooter ride happens at a professional level, unlike any rides you may have attended before. This is going to be a wonderful experience to you, fellow riders and a visual treat for the onlookers on the roads, provided we all stick to the expectations as described below:</b></p> <p>* Though we might be riding a gearless scooter, being cautious on the road is vital. Please ensure that your scooter is in good condition (Head light, Brake Light, Indicators and Horn are in working condition and both Mirrors are to be on the bike.)<br/><b>* Carry your Driver’s License, Vehicle Registration card, the Insurance certificate and the pollution certificate. In case you are not, ClimbOn Hyderabad is not liable for any consequences you may have to face, as described in the motor vehicle Act. All you need to do is carry them with you and the ride will be seamless.<br/>* Helmet (Full Faced/ Half Faced), a Full Sleeved Jacket or a Hoodie and Shoes are mandatory for all the riders. (It is highly recommended for a pillion too, to wear a helmet).<br/></b> * Every rider will follow the hand signs and safety instructions as instructed by the Host.<br/>*No stunting, racing or any activities those are hazardous to the rider and other vehicles on the high way.<br/>* Consuming Alcohol and Smoking tobacco and products related to it in any form are restricted, from the time of assembling at the meeting point, until dispersing at the closing point<br/>* Your host will carry the First-Aid kit throughout the event (Just in case).</p> <p>*Update: Motorbikes are also allowed along with scooters.</p> <p><b>Convenience Instructions:</b><br/>* Scooters hardly have 5 Liters fuel tank. So we may have to refill the tanks while coming back. Get enough cash, as some petrol bunks don’t have swiping machines. We will be riding close to (160KMS) from the start to the end. If our scooters give an average mileage of 35 KMPL, we will need about 5 liters of fuel, which closely amounts to 69*5=345/-.</p> <p>* Since we may do kayaking, get a pair of slippers, as you cannot sit with the shoes on. As swimming is also an option, get an extra pair of clothes. For boys, swimming shorts are provided. Remember folks.. If you are getting your clothes, make sure they are of Sportswear type<b> (Changing rooms and showers are available there, for men and women separately)</b>. Cotton shorts are not allowed in the pool. For kayaking they might charge close to 400/- and for swimming it is less than 150/-.</p> <p>* Tea, Coffee and Biscuits are covered under Club Fee. Cost of lunch can be shared, once we finish digging into the dishes.</p> <p>* Please get at least one water bottle and a backpack. You will need them during the ride, though we may get water bottles post reaching the hill site.</p> <p>* Since the monsoon has already started, please get your rain wear as well. Nothing will stop us from experiencing this early morning ride in the midst of the forest. We will go ahead, even if it rains or drizzles.</p> <p><b>How much do I pay?</b><br/>Post the event, each participant has to pay 150/- (Includes Tea/Coffee, Organizer’s Reimbursement and the Club Fee &amp; Expertise).</p> <p><b>Disclaimer: </b>The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.</p> <p>Contact Details: ClimbOn Uday-9666531565, ClimbOn Pravallika-7702523099</p> '),(539,'1465761929000','Beginners Scrambling, Leaping & Lot More Fun at Shamirpet Lake','231844075','1466411931000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231844075/','Trimulgherry cross roads, petrol pump.','2016-06-19 06:00:00.000000','past','Near the Petrol Pump','Secunderabad','in','Trimulgherry Cross Roads',0,'2016-06-20 08:38:00.000000','<p><b>Shamirpet Lake</b> is situated about 20 kms north of Secunderabad built during the reign of the Nizams. Its beautiful rocky terrain gives us ample opportunity to use our skills to navigate around the boulders while keeping an eye on the lake and surrounding water bodies…sure is a sight for sore eyes. The lush green countryside too helps. The area attracts a lot of birds too, hence a destination for bird watchers.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/6/1/0/600_444274320.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/6/1/f/600_444274335.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/6/c/c/600_444274508.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/4/1/600_444274625.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Who can take part in:</b> The whole world :D. One who is fit mentally. </p> <p><b>Level of difficulty: </b>Chill folks, we\'ll make sure U \'just do it\'. Based on climatic conditions one can experience bouldering, rock climbing and  chimney.</p> <p><b>Intent :</b> Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor climbing and make you experience the true nature of physical and mental strength in you.</p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b><br/>6:00 AM : Assemble at Trimulgherry cross roads<br/>7:00 AM Reach Lake. On our way let\'s pause at a hotel and eat<br/>Lo, here it begins. <br/>[Fun] <br/>[Adventure] <br/>[Fun] <br/>11:30 AM  : Tired?? let\'s get back to our town. Hasta la vista. </p> <p><b>Mode of Commute:</b> personal transport. Get your vehicles or we can share with others. It\'s not too far so not to worry much about transport. </p> <p><b>Instructions: </b><br/>• Tee shirt, Tracks - No shorts, <br/>• Shoes are a MUST, Cap advised. <br/>• Some fruits, juices, Snacks to Fill On to \'Climb On\'. <br/>• 2 Liters of water is advised</p> <p><b>Cost breakup:</b> RS.100/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], equipment, stationary and first-Aid. (Fuel, food, water is not included).</p> <p>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p>Sandeep : 800 800 4360 Whatsapp preferred.. :)</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event. No littering - fine 100 rs. </p> '),(540,'1466355601000','Ride to the magnificent Nagarjuna Sagar Dam & Ethipotala falls','232008874','1466859079000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232008874/','We will have our vehicels parked at KFC Parking, LB Nagar, Hyderabad. Call your Host Uday @ 9666531565','2016-06-25 05:30:00.000000','past','Nalgonda','Hyderabad','in','Nagarjuna Sagar',0,'2016-06-25 12:51:00.000000','<p>Hey there! How about putting on our riding gear and riding to Nagarjun Sagar dam on our bikes? Are you ready to experience the extravaganza of riding the bikes on this scenic route and visiting the dam and the waterfalls?</p> <p><b>What do we visit:</b><br/><b><br/>Ethipothala Falls: <br/>A 70 feet (21 m) high river cascade, situated in Guntur district,Andhra Pradesh India. Located on the Chandravanka River, which is a tributary of River Krishna, joining on its right bank. The waterfall is a combination of three streams namely Chandravanka Vagu, Nakkala Vagu and Tummala Vagu. It is situated about 11 Kms from Nagarjuna Sagar Dam. The river then joins the River Krishna after the dam after travelling about 3 Kms from the falls. A strategic view point was created by Andhra Pradesh Tourism Department from the adjacent hillock.</b></p> <p><b>Nagarjuna Sagar Dam:</b><br/><b>Built across the River Krishna at Nagarjuna Sagar, where the river forms a boundary between Nalgonda district of Telangana state and Guntur district of Andhra Pradesh state in India. </b><br/><b><br/>One Surprise view point...</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/2/8/600_451263368.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/9/600_451263449.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/d/5/600_451263541.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b><br/><b>How far do we ride:</b></p> <p>One way-150 Kms from Hyderabad<br/><b><br/>Who can join:</b></p> <p>* All bikes and scooters above 100 CC.  <b>NO CARS.</b><br/>* <b>If you want to be a pillion and share a ride, it is the rider\'s discretion to accept or not. </b><br/>* <b>Please consider this, before doing an RSVP. Organizers can not guarantee you that there will be a seat for a pillion.</b><br/>* If the rider himself is coming with a pillion, please RSVP and do a +1 as guest.</p> <p><b>Timeline:</b></p> <p>* 0530 AM: Meet at KFC, LB Nagar<br/>* 0600 AM: Finish orientation on Hand Signs and Safety Instructions and Start to Nagarjun Sagar<br/>* 0700 AM: Stop for breakfast at Ibrahimpatnam<br/>* 0930 AM: Reach Nagarjun Sagar and spend time there<br/>* 1030 AM: Go to the surprise view point and click pics<br/>* 1130 AM: Visit Ethipotala falls<br/>* 0230PM: Have lunch and Start back to Hyderabad<br/>*0600PM: Reach LB Nagar Hyd and close the event.</p> <p><b>Safety Instructions: </b><br/>This ride happens at a professional level, unlike any rides you may have attended before. This is going to be a wonderful experience to you, fellow riders and a visual treat for the onlookers on the roads, provided we all stick to the expectations as described below: </p> <p><b>Monsoon folks! It might rain. Bring in your rain wear. Event happens despite of rain. We will definetly stop and wait if it is a downpour. If it just drizzles, you don\'t know how funtastic it will be to ride.<br/></b><br/>* Since we will be riding our bikes, being cautious on the road is vital. Please ensure that your bike is in good condition (Head light, Brake Light, Indicators and Horn are in working condition and both Mirrors are to be on the bike.) <br/>* <b>Carry your Driver’s License, Vehicle Registration card, the Insurance certificate and the pollution certificate. In case you are not carrying them, ClimbOn Hyderabad is not liable for any consequences you may have to face, as described in the motor vehicle Act. All you need to do is carry them with you and the ride will be seamless. </b><br/>* <b>Helmet (Full Faced/ Half Faced), a Full Sleeved Jacket or a Hoodie and Shoes are mandatory for all the riders. (It is highly recommended for a pillion too, to wear a helmet). </b><br/>* Every rider will follow the hand signs and safety instructions as instructed by the Host. <br/>*No stunting, racing or any activities those are hazardous to the rider and other vehicles on the high way. <br/>* Consuming Alcohol and Smoking tobacco and products related to it in any form are restricted, from the time of assembling at the meeting point, until dispersing at the closing point <br/>* Your host will carry the First-Aid kit throughout the event (Just in case). </p> <p><b>How much do you pay:</b></p> <p>150/- (Includes Tea/Coffee, First Aid, Expertise &amp; Clubfee)<br/><b>Breakfast, lunch, water, fuel, parking and entry tickets (20/- for Ethipotala waterfall) expenses are excluded.<br/></b></p> <p>Disclaimer: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.<b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/6/a/7/600_451310855.jpeg\" /></p> '),(541,'1466530440000','Ammuguda Hill Trek','232058160','1466845874000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232058160/','Sandeep 8008004360','2016-06-25 06:00:00.000000','past','Behind Ayappa Temple, Ammuguda','Secunderabad','in','Khoe Imam Zamin',0,'2016-06-25 09:11:00.000000','<p><b>About Ammuguda </b></p> <p>Near Ammuguda railway station is a beautiful Hill with a dargah, known as Khoe Imam Zamin, it has steep steps, The hill is surrounded by water on one side, the steps are just 250 in number but quite a challenge with heavy bags. From top of the hill the whole bolaram, sainikpuri and trimulgherry is visible The Dargah on the Hill is dedicated to <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ali_al-Rida\">Imam Reza</a></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/9/6/2/600_451355170.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Instructions </b></p> <p>Please be aware it’s a Heritage Site and sacred to some people, No littering on the hill, No noises, respect the pilgrims on the hill and don\'t get into any arguments with anyone When you reach the top and If you want to go into the dargah, please remove your footwear before entering the dargah Not all places inside the dargah are open to everyone, please ask if in doubt Females will need to cover their heads with a churni/dupata over their head before going in the dargah </p> <p>Lets all get along and enjoy this special day.</p> <p><b>What to Wear : </b></p> <p>• Tee shirt</p> <p>• Tracks / Shorts </p> <p>• Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>• Cap advised</p> <p>• Water 2 liter</p> <p>• Snacks to Fill On to Climb On.</p> <p><b>Cost breakup:</b> Rs. 50/- { Pay on spot }</p> <p><b>Note:</b> <i>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers : </b>Sandeep 8008004360</i></p> '),(542,'1465471254000','Road trip to a spiritual destination @ Kadthal Pyramid','231768463','1472560763000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231768463/','ClimbOn Rohith 9676722155','2016-06-25 15:00:00.000000','past','Nanal nagar X roads','Hyderabad','in','Morine bakery',0,'2016-08-30 12:39:00.000000','<p><b>Welcome to Leisure face of \"Climb On- Hyderabad\"</b>.</p> <p><b>Kadthal</b> is a village in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amangal\">Amangal</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tehsil\">Mandal</a> in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mahbubnagar\">Mahbubnagar</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/District\">District</a> in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telangana\">Telangana</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a>.</p> <p>Pyramid:-</p> <p>A <b>pyramid</b> is a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonbuilding_structure\">structure</a> whose outer surfaces are triangular and converge to a single point at the top, making the shape roughly a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pyramid_(geometry)\">pyramid in the geometric sense</a>. The base of a pyramid can be trilateral, quadrilateral, or any <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polygon\">polygon</a> shape, meaning that a pyramid has at least three outer triangular surfaces (at least four <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Face_(geometry)\">faces</a> including the base). The <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Square_pyramid\">square pyramid</a>, with square base and four triangular outer surfaces, is a common version.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/f/c/7/600_446684999.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/f/c/d/600_446685005.jpeg\" /></p> <p>It just doesn\'t get much better than camping in Hyderabad outside with friends &amp; family - Food on the grill, under moon, games around you, enjoying the great outdoors, songs &amp; stories around the campfire, nothing could be better than this for a weekend.</p> <p>We hope it makes your experience with \'Climb on\' more enjoyable!</p> <p><b>Where: </b>Just across the border from Hyderabad , this is one of our favourites. Got some excellent sites that are right on the shoreline of beautiful fields.</p> <p><b>When:</b></p> <p><b>Date: </b>On 25th June 3:00pm to 26th June 2016 1:00pm. 1D/1N.<br/><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot, just join the waiting list and make the payment.<br/><b>Distance:</b> 75kms away from Hyderabad on bangalore Highway (2hrs drive)<br/><b>Meetup Point:</b> Morine bakery, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences:</b></p> <p><b>a. Camping </b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/d/3/7/600_446976151.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>b. Forest exploration</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/0/4/8/600_446685128.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>c. Trekking.</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/2/1/c/600_446685596.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>d. Rappelling</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/2/5/d/600_451425661.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>e. Rock climbing</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/2/2/8/600_446685608.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>f. Pyramid visiting</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/2/e/9/600_446685801.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>g. V</b>olleyball</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/2/9/600_450901321.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>h. Nature &amp; fun things to do.</b></p> <p><b>Things to bring </b> :</p> <p>It\'s going to be cold so bring a solid <b>WARM Blanket </b><br/>Sports shoes, preferable old shoes.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and a water bottle.</p> <p>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Tariff: Rs.550 per head </b>including<b> food</b> - Limited seats only<br/>Includes<br/>. Camping gears<br/>. Activities<br/>. Campsite charges.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231768463/\"><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231768463/\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231768463/</a></a> -- link</p> <p>please do the 150/- payment and book your slots thanks...</p> <p><b>** Not included</b><b> Transport</b></p> <p><i>Note: <b>No booze, No intoxicants</b>, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><b>Payment Details: On spot payment.</b></p> <p>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b> </i>Contact:-9676722155</p> '),(543,'1463598583000','Trek to thrilling kalavantin durg.......','231224033','1467600753000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231224033/','Event Organiser:CLIMBON ROHITH-9676722155','2016-07-01 20:00:00.000000','past','Nampally','Hyderabad','in','Hyderabad Railway Station at Nampally',0,'2016-07-04 02:52:00.000000','<p><b>Trek Notes :</b></p> <p>Add yourself to WAITING LIST</p> <p>This is not for kids</p> <p><b>DIFFICULTY:</b> Easy to Medium (People who are FIT can RSVP) with slippery climbs. The trek demands sharing, endurance, adjustment and discipline. Please be prepared.</p> <p><b>Details of place :-</b></p> <p><b>KALAVANTIN DURG :-<br/></b><br/>Kalavantin Pinnacle is situated on northeast side of Panvel at a height of 2330 ft , on Mumbai-Pune road. Can see it from express highway a V-Shaped one. The Left one is Kalavantin Durg &amp; right side is Prabalgad.</p> <p>Kalavantin Durg is considered as one of the best trekking spots in the Sahyadri mountain range. It offers dangerous yet thrilling trekking experience.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/b/e/e/600_450135342.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/f/7/1/600_450136241.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/f/7/9/600_450136249.jpeg\" /></p> <p>It provides an awesome opportunity for rock climbing at a high heights !! It is a thrilling experience!!! We will be camping on top of the pinnacle hill during night time!!!</p> <p><b>Note:</b> Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. We request all its members to be socially responsible whilst the treks and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology.</p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b></p> <p>FRIDAY :<br/>8:30 pm : karjat by Train</p> <p>SATURDAY :<br/>11:30 - Reach karjat<br/>11:45 : Reach Karjat and take a bus to Panvel, reach the base village Thakurwadi and start trekking .<br/>07:00 - reach top(camping)</p> <p>SUNDAY :<br/>5AM : Descend and trek to the adjacent Prabalgad. start back to Panvel.<br/>12 AM : Start back to Karjat<br/>2 PM : catch Train to HYD</p> <p>MONDAY :</p> <p>8AM : Reach HYD</p> <p><b>Things to Bring:</b> [All are compulsory&gt; pack light around 5-6 Kg’s</p> <p>1. Rucksack/ Backpack to keep all things with nice support.<br/>2. Sleeping Bag or couple of blankets.<br/>3. Shoes with good grip used before &amp; two pairs of socks<br/>4. Dress change for 2 days (Light Colors preferable, Avoid jeans) &amp; few plastic covers to keep wet cloths.</p> <p>5. Slippers/ floaters for using in night.<br/>6. Torch with extra batteries.<br/>7. Water Bottle min (2 litres)<br/>8. Personal stuff (Mosquito cream, Toiletries, Medicines).<br/>9. Camera to click moments- OPTIONAL<br/>10. First – Aid kit, any specific medicines you need. (That anyway organizer will carry)<br/>11. Traveller’s/Swiss knife<br/>12.Carry Identification card.- Govt recognized one<br/>13. Food: Jam, Dry Fruits, Energy Bars, Keera (Cucumber), Beetroot, Carrots, dates, Cashew etc .. Citrus fruits, salty food, Ready to eat packets would be good as well</p> <p><b>Price</b><b>: </b>Rs: 2100/- per person excluding food .....</p> <p><b>CONTACT :-<br/>CLIMBON ROHITH - 9676722155</b></p> <p><b>Name : Rohith eravalli<br/>Bank : kotak mahendra bank<br/>Branch : somagiguda<br/>Acc/no : 9211678893<br/>IFSC code : KKBK0000552<br/>mention the trek/event_urname for easy identification</b></p> <p><i><b>NOTE:</b></i><i> Event Hosts have all the rights to add or remove any member and do necessary changes in route, activity, time, duration depending on the situations and climate conditions. ORGANIZER\'S DECISION IS FINAL (ITS ALL ABOUT SAFETY, PLZ CO-OPERATE)</i></p> <p><i><b>Contact Details:</b></i></p> <p><i>ROHITHDEEKSHITH - 9676722155</i></p> <p><i>( you can do whatsaap also to my no)</i></p> '),(544,'1466390026000','Morning Cycling ride to Gandipet Lake and Games','232018831','1467513026000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232018831/','ClimbOn Sandeep - 8008004360','2016-07-02 05:30:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-07-03 02:30:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride to Gandipet Lake. We will start from HBC bike station Gachibowli. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p>[Gandipet Lake]</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/5/d/4/600_449142452.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Weather is just awesome in Hyderabad - We might get a chance to enjoy the mist on our way </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/f/8/9/600_451292649.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p><b>Please carry an original ID card</b> like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station 10-20 minute before to rent the cycles. </p> <p><b>Cost - </b>Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit etc.)</p> <p> [ Please bring exact change ] </p> <p><b>Own Bicycle Rent Cost</b> - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee  Rs 100/-</p> <p><i>Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event,</i></p> '),(545,'1465645693000','Let\'s ClimbOn to Kavadipally Hills','231816705','1467905388000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231816705/','ClimbOn Prudhvi- 9908023223 , ClimbOn Jaydev 8500691621','2016-07-03 06:00:00.000000','past','L B Nagar','Hyderabad','in','Orange Hospitals',0,'2016-07-07 15:29:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/f/f/b/600_439257339.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Kavadipally is on way to Ramoji Film city. A huge chain of boulders yet untouched and unexplored.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/f/7/5/600_439257205.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Who can take part in</b>: The whole world :D. One who is fit mentally.</p> <p><b>Level of difficulty</b>: Chill folks, we\'ll make sure U \'just do it\'. Based on climatic conditions one can experience bouldering, rock climbing, rappelling,  chimney and basic knots training.</p> <p><b>Intent</b> : Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor climbing and make you experience the true nature of physical and mental strength in you.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/5/6/3/600_451101859.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary</b>:</p> <p>7:00 AM : Assemble at LB nagar X Roads near Orange Hospitals<br/>7:45 AM Reach Kavadipally. On our way lets pause at a hotel eat and pack some for afternoon.<br/>8:15 AM : Lo, here it begins.<br/>[Fun]<br/>[Adventure]<br/>[Fun]<br/>5: 30 PM : Tired?? lets get back to our town. Hasta la vista.<br/>6:00 PM : Reached Hyderabad!!!</p> <p><b>Mode of Commute</b>: Personal transport. Get your vehicles or we can share with others. It\'s not too far so not to worry much about transport.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.google.co.in/maps/@17.3074222,78.7139979,388a,20y,81.96t/data=!3m1!1e3!5m1!1e4?hl=en\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.google.co.in/maps/@17.3074222,78.7139979,388a,20y,81.96t/data=!3m1!1e3!5m1!1e4?hl=en</a></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>:<br/>• Tee shirt, Tracks - No shorts,<br/>• Shoes are a MUST, Cap advised.<br/>• Some fruits, juices, Snacks to Fill On to \'ClimbOn\'.<br/>• 2-3 Liters of water is mandatory and lunch.</p> <p><b>Cost breakup</b>: RS.200/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included).<br/>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p><b>Direct numbers</b> : ClimbOn Prudhvi- 9908023223 , ClimbOn jaydev 8500691621</p> '),(546,'1461159380000','Into the lap of nature, trek to beaches in Gokarna and Sathodi Falls July 8 - 10','230515204','1468732441000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/230515204/','Contact Event Host:ClimbOn-Babu Reddy - 9966693964','2016-07-08 16:00:00.000000','past','KACHIGUDA RAILWAY STATION','Hyderabad','in','KACHIGUDA RAILWAY STATION',0,'2016-07-17 05:14:00.000000','<p>About: </p> <p><b>Gokarna: </b></p> <p>Gokarna is famous for its beautiful beaches and landscapes. The main beaches in Gokarna are the Gokarna beach, Kudle Beach, Om Beach, Half moon Beach and Paradise Beach (also known as Full moon). The Gokarna beach forms the coast of the town while the other four beaches lie to the south of Gokarna. Kudle and Om are around 6 km from Gokarna town along a muddy hill; they are accessible by rickshaw or foot. Half moon and Paradise are beyond Om beach and are accessible only by foot or boat. Om beach is named so because it is shaped like the auspicious ॐ [Om] symbol. Om beach is the only naturally Om shaped beach. Two other beaches - Paradise and Half Moon - are smaller and remote beaches. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/1/2/600_449499186.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Sathodi Falls:-</p> <p>The Sathodi Falls are formed by several streams near the Kallaramarane Ghat, 32 km from Yellapur. The falls are about 15 meters in height. After flowing from the waterfall the streams then flow into the backwaters of the Kodasalli Dam, into the Kali River. Owing to the picturesque view, the place is fondly called “Mini Niagara”. These falls form an integral part of the Ganeshgudi forest range.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/5/1/9/600_449301785.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Outline: </b></p> <p>Day 1 : Beach Trekking along the coastline from Gokarna Beach to Paradise Beach [ 12 km ]</p> <p>Day 2 : Sathodi Falls</p> <p><b>Iternary: </b></p> <p>Friday 4pm : Kacheguda train to Hubli </p> <p>Sat 8am : Hubli station to Gokarna. </p> <p>Sat 12pm : Lunch &amp; Beach Trek from Gokarna - Om beach - Half Moon - Paradise / Gokarna (12 km Approx) </p> <p>Sat 8pm : Stay in Gokarna [Accommodation is separate in tents for Men and woman] </p> <p> Sun 4am : Wakeup call </p> <p> Sun 5am : Gokarna to Sathodi Falls </p> <p> Sun 8am : Trekking in Sathodi falls and click some cool pics </p> <p>  Sun 4pm : Sathodi falls to Hubli. </p> <p> Sun 4pm: Catch train to Hyderabad. </p> <p> <b>Things to bring: - </b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts, at the beach, a pair of shorts would be a good. </p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. </p> <p>- Sleeping bag or thick blanket</p> <p> - Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p> - Torch light with extra set of batteries. </p> <p> - A proper rucksack (backpack) to keep all of the above things </p> <p> - Camera to capture awesome places.[Optional]</p> <p> - Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b></p> <p> Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p><b>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. </b>Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.<b> This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</b> </p> <p><b> Damages: 2900/-</b> Ball park figure [Transport + Accommodation] Will share  the cost if it is more or less. [ Food is excluded]</p> <p>Please pay 1000/- as an advance payment to confirm your slot.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/230515204/\">Click to Pay</a></p> '),(547,'1465881238000','Night camping Beside Lake @ Pocharam Forest 9th July','231879268','1468775634000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231879268/','ClimbOn Suman 9966002025','2016-07-09 13:00:00.000000','past','Balanagar','Hyderabad','in','Balanagar X Roads',0,'2016-07-17 17:13:00.000000','<p>Pocharam lake is located in Medak district in the Indian state of Telangana. It is adjacent to Pocharam Forest &amp; Wildlife Sanctuary.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/4/d/600_442416685.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/1/0/1/600_442533025.jpeg\" /></p> <p>15 KM from Medak is Pocharam Lake with a dam, and Pocharam Wildlife sanctuary which used to be a hunting ground for the Nizam.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/6/f/600_442416719.jpeg\" /></p> <p>We would also be exploring the Medak Fort which is a citadel built on a hillock that provided as a vantage point for the Kakatiyan rulers in ancient India.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/9/1/600_442416753.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Date:</b> On Sat 9th 1p.m to Sun 10th 11 a.m 1D/1N.</p> <p><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot and make the payment at meetup point.</p> <p><b>Distance: </b>110kms away from (3hrs drive)</p> <p><b>Meetup Point:</b> Balanagar X roads, Self transport.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences: </b>Night Camping, Star gazing,</p> <p>a. Night camping</p> <p>b. Trekking.</p> <p>c. Bon-fire.</p> <p>d. Stargazing</p> <p>e. Haunted stories</p> <p>f. Fort Visit</p> <p>Plus Nature &amp; fun things to do.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b><br/>A pair of extra clothes if you go for swim. (optional)<br/>Sports shoes.<br/>Torch with extra batteries,<br/>Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and 2 ltr water bottle.<br/>Caps/Raincoats(optional)<br/>A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b><br/>Day 1 After reaching by 5pm, Roam Around, bon-fire with camping, Dinner.<br/>Day 2 Morning we start the day lake trek enjoying the view and fun activities.</p> <p><b>Tariff: </b>Rs.400 per head - Limited seats only<br/>Includes:<br/>a. Camping gears (Tents etc..)<br/>b. Activities.</p> <p><b>Payment link:</b></p> <p>Please do <b><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231879268/\">100/- advance payment</a></b> to book your slot as we have limited tents , once payment transferred share your transaction ID so that we can we move you in yes list.</p> <p><b>Food and Transport Not included</b> in the club fund. We can share it accordingly.<br/>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care will be taken to make your trip comfortable.</p> <p><b>Note: </b><i>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b> ClimbOn Suman 9966002025</i></p> '),(548,'1468240094000','Climb On CRICKET - ChakDe','232534477','1468672298000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232534477/','ClimbOn Rohit 9676722155','2016-07-16 05:45:00.000000','past','Kismatpur','Hyderabad','in','Oxygen Sports Village',0,'2016-07-16 12:31:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/1/3/e/600_452052606.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/2/9/8/600_452052952.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Cost  :</b> Rs 250/per head  - this <b>doesn\'t</b> include transportation and food. Food will be shared equally. </p> <p><b>Important Instructions:  </b></p> <p>1) No smoking and no alcohol <br/>2) No littering, no pollution of water </p> <p><b>NOTE</b>: Please answer all the questions. </p> <p><b>Contact </b>:Rohit 9676722155</p> '),(549,'1468492553000','ClimbOn Fitness: Swimming in an Indoor Pool (For the Beginners also)','232610672','1468684648000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232610672/','Contact Event Organiser: ClimbOn-Arvind (9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1)','2016-07-16 18:00:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-07-16 15:57:00.000000','<p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood</p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(550,'1467041788000','One day..One River..Two Dams..Let\'s ride to Manjeera and Singur Dams on a Sunday','232198537','1468841645000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232198537/','Meeting Point: BHEL Gate, Hyderabad. Call your organizer Uday @ 9666531565','2016-07-17 05:30:00.000000','past','Medak','Andhra Pradesh','in','Singur',0,'2016-07-18 11:34:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/3/b/f/600_451749151.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>This Sunday is going to be soo good, because we are going to visit two dams on the same day.</b></p> <p><b>Where are we going:</b></p> <p><b>Manjeera Dam:</b><br/>This is the lifeline for Hyderabadis. This is a man made dam on Manjeera river, from which most of the areas in Hyderabad get drinking water supplied from. Visiting this place means  feeling thankful for what we have been getting from that dam as a life saver.</p> <p><b>Crocodile Breeding Center_Manjeera Dam:</b><br/>This is a small breeding center for crocodiles at the dam. We will visit this place and spend some time there, before moving on to the next place.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/2/b/a/600_451564794.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Singur Dam:</b></p> <p>This is another irrigation cum hydro-electricity production center constructed on Manjeera river again. We will spend a lot of time clicking pictures at this place and also visit a childrens park near the dam. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/2/c/8/600_451564808.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/3/0/9/600_451564873.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What do we do:</b><br/>We will start to Manjeera dam at 06:00 AM sharp.<br/>Later we will stop for breakfast at Sangareddy.<br/>From there, it is going to be too damn good (Because we are visiting two dams ;-)).<br/>We will ride through remote villages, along side the Manjeera river.<br/>Pics and pics and pics on the way. <br/>That is what we will do until we reach Singur Dam.<br/>We will make sure to reach back Hyderabad by 06:00 PM the same day.</p> <p><b>Can I join and How can I come:</b><br/>* Everyone above the age of 18 can join.<br/>* You can get your motorbikes and scooter, which are above 100 CC respectively. <br/><b>Update: Allowing Cars too<br/></b> <br/>*<b> If you want to be a pillion on a bike it is the rider\'s discretion to allow you on their vehicles.<br/>*Watsapp group will be created to discuss the ride share and important updates.<br/>* In case a person coming you have pooled up with drops out, the organizer can not guarantee you a ride share, because it is the vehicle owner\'s discretion. <br/>Please consider all these elements before doing RSVP.</b></p> <p><b>How long are we going to ride/drive:</b><br/>75 Kms+75 Kms</p> <p><b>Safety Instructions: </b> <br/>This travelling part in this event happens at a professional level, unlike any events you may have attended before. This is going to be a wonderful experience to you, fellow riders and a visual treat for the onlookers on the roads, provided we all stick to the expectations as described below: </p> <p>Monsoon folks! It might rain. Bring in your rain wear. Event happens despite of rain. We will definitely stop and wait if it is a downpour. If it just drizzles, you don\'t know how funtastic it will be to ride.</p> <p>* Since we will be riding our bikes, being cautious on the road is vital. Please ensure that your bike is in good condition (Head light, Brake Light, Indicators and Horn are in working condition and both Mirrors are to be on the bike.) <br/>* Carry your Driver’s License, Vehicle Registration card, the Insurance certificate and the pollution certificate. In case you are not carrying them, ClimbOn Hyderabad is not liable for any consequences you may have to face, as described in the motor vehicle Act. All you need to do is carry them with you and the ride will be seamless.  <br/>* Helmet (Full Faced/ Half Faced), A full sleeved jacket of any kind or a hoodie and Shoes are mandatory for all the riders. (It is highly recommended for a pillion too, to wear a helmet). <br/>* Every rider will follow the hand signs and safety instructions as instructed by the Host. <br/>*No stunting, racing or any activities those are hazardous to the rider and other vehicles on the high way. <br/>* Consuming Alcohol and Smoking tobacco and products related to it in any form are restricted, from the time of assembling at the meeting point, until dispersing at the closing point <br/>* Your host will carry the First-Aid kit throughout the event (Just in case). </p> <p><b>Update: Allowing Cars too</b></p> <p><b>How much do I pay:</b><br/>150/-  (Includes Clubfee, Basic First Aid, Expertise Tea/Coffee). Fuel, Food, water and all other personal expenses are excluded.</p> <p><b>Disclaimer:</b> The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.  </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/7/6/9/600_451565993.jpeg\" /></p> '),(551,'1468980933000','Indoor  Climbing with ClimbOn (For the beginners also)','232742596','1469286870000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232742596/','Climb-On Arvind (9640431351)','2016-07-23 17:30:00.000000','past','Gachibowli Miyapur Road','Hyderabad','in','Crag Studio',0,'2016-07-23 15:14:00.000000','<p>Indoor climbing is an increasingly popular form of rock climbing performed on artificial structures that attempt to mimic the experience of outdoor rock. Indoor rock climbing is one of the most adrenaline-pumping sports you can do.</p> <p>Let\'s climb to indoor artificial walls at Kondapur and train your body for outdoor climbing adventures.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/2/2/4/600_449197412.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This is a fun and safe sport for all ages in controlled environment. First timers are also welcome and encouraged to come and climb with ClimbOn! You don\'t need to come with a friend, you would make many climber friends at the end of event.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/2/4/b/600_449197451.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Place and meet-up point</b></p> <p>CRAG Studio: Plot No 198, Opposite Harsha Toyota Show room, Gachibowli Miyapur Rd, Prashanth Nagar Colony, Kondapur.</p> <p><b>Please be there 15 minutes before the event.</b></p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 350 </b>(this includes climbing basics by instructors, club fee, trekking shoes, climbing gears,and emergency first-aid kit support).</p> <p><b>Attire: </b>Shorts or tracks that stretch well.</p> <p><b>Basic Fundamentals of Indoor Rock Climbing | Rock Climbing</b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=30y8Uy0B_uk</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gLfvk2SSj1c</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs\"><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=A7hrePm3OUs</a></a><br/></b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>FAQ: </b></p> <p><b><i>Can I come if I\'ve never climbed before?<br/></i></b></p> <p>Yes of course. Studio have climbers of all different skill levels, and there\'s usually at least one person at each meetup who hasn\'t climbed before. It\'s not a problem.</p> <p><b><i>Do I have to bring gear?<br/></i></b>No, you can hire gear at the climbing studio. If you have your own gear, feel free to bring it along. Note that you don\'t need to bring any rope, carabiners or the like.</p> <p><b>Do I need strong arms for climbing?</b></p> <p>The most common myth about indoor climbing! Climbing and bouldering is all about getting your legs to do all the hard work. Going climbing does make you stronger however as you do have to use your arms, but that happens over time! These climbing sessions are designed to help you learn the basics of footwork and progress faster and smoother.</p> <p>Any questions, please comment below, or call/whatsApp Arvind at 9640431351</p> <p><b>Disclaimer</b>: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times. By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.</p> '),(552,'1467364745000','Rappelling,Rock climbing and hiking at Khajaguda','232299729','1469371029000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232299729/','Contact Event Organiser:  prudhvi- 9908023223, Ankur- 9039011200','2016-07-24 06:00:00.000000','past',' near Raidurgam Bus stop Mumbai Highway Road ','Hyderabad','in','Khajaguda',0,'2016-07-24 14:37:00.000000','<p>Khajaguda is quality outdoor climbing locations all varying in scenery, rock quality and texture. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/f/0/e/600_435483854.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/5/1/d/600_436790461.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Spend the day with our certified guide learning the basics of rock climbing and improving your top-roping skills and techniques.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/9/3/2/600_436762834.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor rock climbing experiences. </p> <p><b>Basic Rappelling and Scrambling:</b></p> <p>Time : 6am  - 11:30 am</p> <p>Tee shirt</p> <p>Tracks - No shorts please. </p> <p>Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>Cap advised</p> <p>Water 2 liter</p> <p>Snacks to Fill On to Climb On.</p> <p>Cost breakup: Rs. 100/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], Equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included) <br/><b>Gear Provided.</b>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p>Meet up at Raidurgam bus-stop  near Wells Fargo at 6:00 AM. </p> '),(553,'1468980592000','Fitness: Swimming in an Indoor Pool (For the Beginners also)','232742478','1469352395000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232742478/','Contact Event Organiser: ClimbOn-Arvind (9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1)','2016-07-24 13:30:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-07-24 09:26:00.000000','<p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood</p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(554,'1463977186000','Trek to Tadiandamol - Highest peak in Coorg','231329771','1470287504000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231329771/','ClimbOn - Babu Reddy -9966693964  Rohith-9676722155','2016-07-29 19:00:00.000000','past','KACHEGUDA RAILWAY STATION','Hyderabad','in','KACHEGUDA RAILWAY STATION',0,'2016-08-04 05:11:00.000000','<p>Tadiandamol trek is one of the most beautiful, though less known, treks in Karnataka. The trail takes you through the vast expanse of the Shola forests, through endless lush green grasslands and streams.</p> <p>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- </p> <p><b>Difficulty level:</b> Easy - Medium</p> <p><b>Risks:</b> Leeches</p> <p>For: Aged 18+yrs and fit trekkers only, If you are interested, add yourself to WL, and once payment is received you will be moved into going list.</p> <p>---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p> <p>Tadiandamol is the highest peak in Coorg/Kodagu district with an elevation of 5740 ft. It is the third highest peak in Karnataka It is a place of interest for <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiking\">&lt;/a&gt;trekkers and naturalists. The mountain has patches  of shola forests in the valleys.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/7/4/600_450300372.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/9/d/4/600_450306612.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/9/d/d/600_450306621.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p>(Friday) :</p> <p> Start from Kachiguda</p> <p>(Saturday):</p> <p>08:00 AM : Reach Bangalore majestic</p> <p>09:00 AM : Travel to Kakkabe</p> <p>2:00 PM : Reach Kakkabe and start trek to the Peak</p> <p>06:00 PM : Reach peak and pitch tents</p> <p>08:00 PM : Dinner , chit chat and sleep</p> <p>(Sunday) :</p> <p>05:00 AM : Wakeup call</p> <p>06:00 AM : Enjoy breathtaking view of sunrise and capture those moments</p> <p>09:00AM : Trek down</p> <p>12:00PM: Reach base village and have some lunch</p> <p>02:00 PM : Start to Bangalore</p> <p>08:00 PM : Reach Bangalore</p> <p>10:00 PM : Catch Train from Bangalore</p> <p>(Monday)</p> <p>8:00 AM : Reach Secunderabad</p> <p><b>Advisory :</b></p> <p>* As we are traversing through pristine and untamed nature, do not expect luxury      trip</p> <p>* Please carry some food</p> <p>* Basic level of fitness is compulsory to undertake this trek</p> <p>* Do pay heed to the guidelines given by the instructor</p> <p>* Avoid consumption of alcohol or any other intoxicating products during the            entire trip</p> <p>* Do not carry valuables or expensive jewelleries during the trip</p> <p>* Do not leave the campsite during the night</p> <p>*  Avoid using earphones during the trek as they might hinder your audibility</p> <p><b>Things to Bring:</b></p> <p>1. Rucksack/ Backpack to keep all things with nice support. <br/>2. Sleeping Bag or couple of blankets. <br/>3. Shoes with good grip used before &amp; two pairs of socks <br/>4. Dress change for 2 days (Light Colors preferable, Avoid jeans) &amp; few plastic covers to keep wet cloths.</p> <p>5.Rain Coat, Wind cheater</p> <p>6. Torch with extra batteries. </p> <p>7. Water Bottle min (2 litres) <br/>8. Camera to click  moments- OPTIONAL <br/>09. First – Aid kit, any specific medicines you need. (That anyway organizer will carry) <br/>10. Carry Identification card.- Govt recognized one <br/>11. Snacks like energy bars, ready to eat food etc.</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event.</p> <p>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm. This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p><b>Cost :</b> Rs: 3000/- per person including food (Does not include food in train). Any excess money will be shared and remaining money will be refunded before the trek ends.</p> <p>Pay 1000/- + taxes as advance to confirm your slot.. Please find payment link below</p> <p>&lt;a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231329771/\"&gt;Click here to pay</a></p> '),(555,'1469085685000','Let\'s zooom to Mallelaterdham falls','232773374','1470118313000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232773374/','Meeting point is Aaramghar X roads, where PVN Road Express way to the airport ends. Call your Host Uday @ 9666531565','2016-07-31 05:30:00.000000','past','Srisailam Highway','Andhra Pradesh','in','Mallela theertham',0,'2016-08-02 06:11:00.000000','<p>Let us visit Mallelateerdham falls this weekend. </p> <p>This waterfall is close to Srisailam. Mallela Theertham is in the middle of the dense Nallamalla forest. A walk down 350 steps is required to access the waterfall and the view is exhilarating as we get closer to the falls.</p> <p>Now that monsoon already started, the route that we take is absolutely scenic and if it rains, it gets even better.</p> <p>The water in this falls come from a small rivulet and from this area and it flows through the dense jungle where it merges into  the Krishna River.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/f/c/7/600_452356327.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/2/d/1/600_452361201.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Can I join and How can I come: <br/><i>Personal Transport</i></b><br/>* Everyone above the age of 18 can join. <br/>* You can get your vehicles which are 150 CC and above. All kinds of vehicles are allowed.<br/>* Share fuel expenses, if you are sharing a pillion seat with a biker or pooling into a car.<br/>* If you want to be a pillion on a bike it is the rider\'s discretion to allow you on their vehicles. <br/>*Watsapp group will be created to discuss the ride share and important updates. <br/>* In case a person coming you have pooled up with drops out, the organizer can not guarantee you a ride share, because it is the vehicle owner\'s discretion. <br/>Please consider all these elements before doing RSVP. </p> <p><b>How long are we going to ride/drive: <br/></b> 160 Kms + 160 Kms = 320 Kms</p> <p><b>Important things to consider:</b><br/>* We will have breakfast on the way and take some packed food also with us, because this place is very remote and food is not easily available there.<br/>* Please carry at least 2 liters of water with you. Since we will get in to the valley, it becomes difficult to get back to the entrance and get the water. We will get down 350 steps, to get to the water falls.</p> <p><b>Safety Instructions:  </b><br/>This travelling part in this event happens at a professional level, unlike any events you may have attended before. This is going to be a wonderful experience to you, fellow riders and a visual treat for the onlookers on the roads, provided we all stick to the expectations as described below: </p> <p>Monsoon folks! It might rain. Bring in your rain wear. Event happens despite of rain. We will definitely stop and wait if it is a downpour. If it just drizzles, you don\'t know how funtastic it will be to ride. </p> <p>* Since we will be riding our bikes and driving the cars, being cautious on the road is vital. Please ensure that your bike and car is in good condition (Head light, Brake Light, Indicators and Horn are in working condition and both Mirrors are to be on the bike.) <br/>* Carry your Driver’s License, Vehicle Registration card, the Insurance certificate and the pollution certificate. In case you are not carrying them, ClimbOn Hyderabad is not liable for any consequences you may have to face, as described in the motor vehicle Act. All you need to do is carry them with you and the ride will be seamless. <br/>* Helmet (Full Faced/ Half Faced), A full sleeved jacket of any kind or a hoodie and Shoes are mandatory for all the riders. (It is highly recommended for a pillion too, to wear a helmet). <br/>* Every rider will follow the hand signs and safety instructions as instructed by the Host. <br/>* Person driving the car should have the seat belt strapped, during the drive.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/f/e/1/600_452356353.jpeg\" /></p> <p>*No stunting, racing or any activities those are hazardous to the rider/driver and other vehicles on the high way. <br/>* Consuming Alcohol and Smoking tobacco and products related to it in any form are restricted, from the time of assembling at the meeting point, until dispersing at the closing point <br/>* Your host will carry the First-Aid kit throughout the event (Just in case). </p> <p><b>How much do I pay: </b><br/>200/-  (Includes Breakfast, Entry fee, Clubfee, Basic First Aid, Expertise, Tea/Coffee).<br/>Fuel, Lunch, Dinner, water and all other personal expenses are excluded. </p> <p><b>What could be the expenses I have to incur?<br/>Bikes </b>@ 35 KMPL avg. mileage-Fuel-640/-<br/><b>Cars </b>@ 18 KMPL avg. Mileage-Fuel-1240/-<br/>Lunch and Dinner &amp; Water=100+100</p> <p><b>Disclaimer: </b>The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.  </p> '),(556,'1464021775000','Trekking to Ahobilam (Eastern Ghats) in monsoon: Nature at its best','231340293','1470671059000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231340293/','Arvind Climb-On 9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1','2016-08-05 21:00:00.000000','past','Opp : MY Home Jewel','Hyderabad','in','chandanagar/Deepthi sri nagar',0,'2016-08-08 15:44:00.000000','<p>Ahobilam is located in Karnool district of Andhra Pradesh in the hills of the eastern ghats. It is appx 380 kms from Hyderabad.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/9/b/0/600_451630672.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Ahobilam is one of the most sacred temples in South India with history beyond the records of time. It is the holy abode of Lord Narasimha, having nine Narasimha temples spread across <b>lower </b>and <b>upper Ahobilam</b> within a radius of 8 kms. It is said that Lord killed Hiranyakasipu and saved Prahalada here. Though the initial temples were built by Chalukyas in 8th century, most of the current structures were rebuilt by Vijayanagara kings around 15th century.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/3/b/c/600_450325532.jpeg\" /></p> <p> Situated amidst dense Nallamala Forest, visiting Ahobilam is a very enriching experience. Millions of people have trekked here and is considered safe. It requires a lot of endurance to cover the lower and upper Ahobilam. <b><i>Total trek is approximated to be of 20 Kms.</i></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/5/a/1/600_451410113.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/4/0/3/600_450325603.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</b></p> <p><b>Trekking Grade:</b> Moderate <b>Route:</b><i> <b>Hyderabad – Kurnool  (220 Km)– Nandyal  (75 Km)– Allagadda (50 km – Ahobilam (35 km)</b></i></p> <p><b>Best Time to Visit Ahobilam:</b><i>The months between June and September see a good amount of rainfall. During the monsoon season, Ahobilam looks even more beautiful as the trees are dressed in shades of green.</i></p> <p>Itinerary(*<i>We may have a little variation the plan depending upon the situations)</i></p> <p><b>Day 0 - Friday (</b>Night after 9:00 PM<b>):</b> Leave to Allagadda by APSRTC bus and then by another bus to Ahobilam (35 km).  We will be travelling to Allagadda by Bus that  goes via ChandaNagar,  KPHB colony, SR Nagar,Ameerpet  etc. You are free to choose any of these Boarding points as per your convenience. Please inform your decision before the bus departure for co-ordination.</p> <p><b>Day 1 - Saturday :</b> Reach Upper Ahobilam, book a room only for luggage &amp; fresh-up, Cover temples of Upper Ahobilam till evening. Sleep in tents near one of the temples in the night.</p> <p><b>Day 2- Sunday:</b> Fresh-up, Visit temple, Breakfast and go to Lower Ahobilam; Cover the temples by 2.00 (have lunch at satram). We could cover Mahanandi  (another place near to Nandyal ) if time allows.  11.00 PM: Catch bus to Hyderabad.</p> <p><b>Day 3-Monday:</b> Reach Hyd in the morning and say tata bye bye. We expect to return by 04:30AM @ MGBS/Imliban &amp; 05:30 AM at KPHB of  (expect a delay of 1-2 hrs).</p> <p><i><b> With the details and </b>itinerary given<b> above, we are sure that you have made up your mind to rock on this event.</b></i></p> <p><b><i>--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</i></b></p> <p><b>Cost:  </b>Appx Rs. 2200, which includes Hyd-Ahobilam -Hyd bus fair (~1100) +  Club fee (~300; covers tent stay, medical kit, stationary, etc), Organizer\'s reimbursement (~150), Food at Ahobilam (Sat and Sunday- B/F, lunch, and dinner, appx Rs. 600), miscellaneous expenses (Rs. 50). </p> <p><b>IMP:YOU SHOULD BE PREPARED TO EAT AT THE SATRAMS AS THAT IS WHERE WE WILL BE EATING SOME OF OUR MEALS WHEN WE PASS FROM PLACE TO PLACE. </b></p> <p><i><b>Advance payment to block your seat: </b>You will be in waiting list unless you make the payment. Please make a payment of Rs. 1025 to confirm your seat. We would need this advance to book bus tickets and making other arrangements. </i></p> <p><b>Payment Link:</b> <a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231340293/\"><a href=\"https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231340293/\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.instamojo.com/climbon/231340293/</a></a></p> <p><i>*  Please note that this is not a luxury trip, please be prepared for  everything. Although arrangements are made to make it comfortable please  be ready to adjust for any unexpected twists &amp;carry a little extra  money in case the event cost is increased.</i></p> <p><i>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</i></p> <p><b>General Instructions:</b></p> <p>Here are a few important things that you need to know about Ahobilam Trek in advance:</p> <p>1.  The terrain is rough with bushes and thorny trees, Search and  rescue becomes difficult due to vegetation and vastness of the area. </p> <p>2.  Though the current water levels at our bath point might not be on a high, but we can expect some water Kund to dive in. Please don\'t enter into water if you don\'t know swimming &amp; without informing your Buddy. Always have a Buddy informed.</p> <p>3.  We will be camping in the night near a temple, Please exercise religious respect.</p> <p>4.  We might have company-  We all have equal responsibility to keep the Dignity of the club. </p> <p>5.  All are requested to exercise sanctity throughout the trek.</p> <p>6- Drink plenty of water a Day (3-4L) before to fill the body tissue would be  required (this will really help)...</p> <p><i><b>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</b></i></p> <p><b><i>Trekking outfit and things to bring: </i><br/></b></p> <p><b>·1- Light colored/stretchable tracks. </b>Carry only 2 excess pair  (Night wear + a pair for swimming ) anything additional will increase your Dead Load.</p> <p>2- <b>Sleeping Bag:</b> Please buy/borrow//beg if you don\'t have one. Basic model will be enough. In case you intend to suffer- Bring 2 blankets at least to wrap Yourself comfortably.</p> <p>3.  <b>Rucksack </b>.....  Make sure you pack all the things into one Backpack[including sleeping bag] + pack all your clothes in polythene covers so that they won’t get wet even when it drowns. ... YOU will have to carry 3 liters water.</p> <p>4- <b>Torch: </b>This is must ... please buy a good one, which gives you a sharp beam.</p> <p>5- <b>Shoes</b>: NEVER wear a new shoe on a hike, carry extra pair of<br/>socks.  Prefer Hiking Shoes over sport shoe which have strong-light rubber<br/>soles &amp; good ankle support+ 1 pair of slippers.</p> <p>6-Medicines: Bring personal medicines if you have any. The organizer will bring First Aid Kit.</p> <p>7-Identity &amp; Address proof\'s; Preferably issued by GOI/GO Telangana  with <i>a xerox copy of it.</i></p> <p>7-<b>Energy Food</b>: Dates, Electrol /glucose/energy bars/chocolates etc... any snack for your new friends .. Must ..Must.. Must...;)</p> <p>8 Other things(<b>Optional</b>) Knife, Mirror, Towel, Brush &amp; Match box/lighter,..........You never know when u will have to stand against odds</p> <p>9- Two emergency notes with your name, address, emergency contact number.</p> <p>10: A camera for KODAK moments (<b>optional</b>), DSLR\'s welcome</p> <p><b><i>PLEASE CARRY A SLING BAG, WILL BE DROPPING THE LUGGAGE IN A ROOM AND HIKE WITH A SMALLER BACKPACK</i></b></p> <p><b><i>For any more questions, please reach out to the organizer of the event <br/></i></b></p> <p><b><i>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</i></b></p> <p><b>Disclaimer: </b>The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times. By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms. </p> '),(557,'1467365247000','Rachakonda - Rappelling & Exploration into the Hills-Sunday 7th Aug.','232299784','1471143521000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232299784/','Orange Hospitals  https://goo.gl/maps/wgFAgtQVwZJ2','2016-08-07 06:00:00.000000','past','L B Nagar','Hyderabad','in','Orange Hospitals',0,'2016-08-14 02:58:00.000000','<p>Rachakonda Fort is a place of tourist importance. The \'Dasavatara\' sculptures in a cave near Pattabhigutta and the five temples in the town are excellent specimens of Kakatiya art and architecture.</p> <p>Situated among hill ranges, Rachakonda is a place of considerable archaeological interest.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/0/c/6/600_439828870.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Who can take part in:</b> The whole world :D. One who is fit mentally.</p> <p><b>Level of difficulty:</b> Chill folks, we\'ll make sure U \'just do it\'.</p> <p>Based on climatic conditions one can experience bouldering, rock climbing,<b> Rappelling</b>, chimney climbing and basic knots training.</p> <p><b>Intent: </b>Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor climbing and make you experience the true nature of physical and mental strength in you.</p> <p><b>Itinerary</b><b>: </b><br/>6:00 AM : Assemble at LB nagar X Roads near Orange Hospitals<br/>8:00 AM: Reach Rachakonda . On our way let\'s pause at a hotel, eat and pack some for afternoon.<br/>8:15 AM : Lo, here it begins.<br/>*[Fun]**<br/>*[Adventure]***<br/>*[Fun]**<br/>5: 00 PM : Tired?? let\'s get back to our town. Hasta la vista.<br/>6:30 PM : Reached Hyderabad!!!</p> <p><b>Mode of Commute:</b> Personal transport. Get your vehicles or we can share with others. It\'s not too far, just 60 K.M from Hyderabad so not to worry much about transport.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/1/1/9/600_439828953.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/1/3/e/600_439828990.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/1/5/e/600_439829022.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Instructions: </b></p> <p><b>• </b>Bag to carry with raincoat, it may rain.<br/>•Tee shirt, Tracks - No shorts,<br/>•Shoes are a MUST, Cap advised.<br/>• Some fruits, juices, Snacks to Fill On while \'Climb On\'.<br/>• 2-3 Liters of water is must and lunch.</p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><i>Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you.</i></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/c/5/b/600_439831835.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i><br/></i></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/1/a/0/600_439829088.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Cost breakup: </b>Rs. 300/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included)<br/>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p><i><b>RSVP Rules:</b> We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case, just its a humble request to please inform the Organiser a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i></p> <p>For any more questions, our phone lines are open.</p> <p><i>Direct numbers : Climb-On Prudhvi-9908023223</i><i>,</i>, Rohit- 9676722155</p> '),(558,'1470734247000','Yoga for internal strength','233228041','1471144529000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233228041/','ClimbOn Arvind (9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1)','2016-08-13 06:00:00.000000','past','Banjara Hills','HYDERABAD','in','KBR National Park- Main Entrance Gate',0,'2016-08-14 03:15:00.000000','<p>Join us for a yoga session for calming the mind and connecting to our inner happiness. We will explore Ayurveda and practice pranayama and meditation.</p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b>What we are going to do ?</b></p> <p>• Warm up with basic exercises and Sun Salutation (surya namaskaras)</p> <p>• Front bending aasanas<br/>• Back bending aasana <br/>• Balancing</p> <p><b>What you need to bring?</b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat. Alternatives are large sheet or towel</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p>Session is open to all so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours!</p> <p><b>What is the club fund?</b></p> <p>Its <b>free</b>. No club fund. You only need to pay KBR park entry fee, which is Rs 20/person.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/7/f/e/600_452999390.jpeg\" /></p> <p>So, lets enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p>We event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> '),(559,'1470805350000','Fitness through swimming (Learn basics of swimming)','233250733','1471072411000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233250733/','Contact Event Organiser: ClimbOn-Arvind (9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1)','2016-08-13 10:00:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-08-13 07:13:00.000000','<p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood</p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(560,'1465792207000','Let\'s Zaaaap to Exotic Laknavaram Lake on 14 Aug\'16, One Day Ride.','231853079','1471438402000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/231853079/','Asian cine square multiplex, Uppal-Meeting point- Call Uday @ 9666531565','2016-08-14 05:30:00.000000','past','Near Warangal','Hyderabad','in','Laknavaram Lake',0,'2016-08-17 12:53:00.000000','<p><b>Long weekend folks..! Let us go and ride..!<br/></b><br/>It can\'t get any better than taking your bikes out and riding in the gush of early morning wind blowing on your face through the helmets. The moment of truth when you and your machine becomes one and leaps forward towards a calm and quiet destination..</p> <p>Where are we going:<br/><b><br/>Laknavaram Lake</b> is located in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Govindaraopet\">Govindaraopet mandal</a>, about 80km from <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warangal\">Warangal</a>,<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telangana\">Telangana</a>. It is spread over an area of 10,000 acres and holds about 2.135 tmcft of water. It irrigates over 3,500 acres of land. It was build by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kakatiya\">Kakatiya</a> kings. It has about 13 islands in it and has a 160 metres long hanging bridge, which connects three islands. It is surrounded by a thick deciduous forest and it is a very popular tourist spot.</p> <p>The beauty of this lake is inexplicable and the cable bridge is the best of all.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/f/0/e/600_446308430.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/6/6/600_446103430.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/6/9/600_446103433.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Can I join and How can I come: </b></p> <p><b><i>Personal Transport</i> </b><br/>* Everyone above the age of 18 can join. <br/>* You can get your vehicles which are 150 CC and above. All kinds of vehicles are allowed. <br/>* Share fuel expenses, if you are sharing a pillion seat with a biker or pooling into a car. <br/>* If you want to be a pillion on a bike it is the rider\'s discretion to allow you on their vehicles. <br/>*Watsapp group will be created to discuss the ride share and important updates. <br/>* In case a person coming you have pooled up with drops out, the organizer can not guarantee you a ride share, because it is the vehicle owner\'s discretion. <br/>Please consider all these elements before doing RSVP. </p> <p><b>How long are we going to ride: </b><br/> 210 Kms + 210 Kms = 420 Kms </p> <p><b>Skill level: Easy-Moderate<br/></b></p> <p><b>What do we have to carry:<br/></b><br/>* We will have breakfast on the way and the lunch at the destination.<br/>* Please carry at least 2 liters of water with you.<br/>* Backpack, rainwear, shades, cap, toiletries, extra pair of clothes, towel, napkins.<br/>* Enough cash<br/>* <b>LOOOOTTT OF ENERGY</p> <p>What are we going to do:</p> <p>What! You need a time table! <br/>Come on! We are going to break free and spend some time relaxing. No time table. Let the time decide.<br/></b><b><br/>Safety Instructions:  </b><b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/e/a/9/600_452792425.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This travelling part in this event happens at a professional level, unlike any events you may have attended before. This is going to be a wonderful experience to you, fellow riders and a visual treat for the onlookers on the roads, provided we all stick to the expectations as described below: </p> <p>Monsoon folks! It might rain. Bring in your rain wear. Event happens despite of rain. We will definitely stop and wait if it is a downpour. If it just drizzles, you don\'t know how funtastic it will be to ride. </p> <p>* Since we will be riding our bikes, being cautious on the road is vital. Please ensure that your bike is in good condition (Head light, Brake Light, Indicators and Horn are in working condition and both Mirrors are to be on the bike.) <br/>* Carry your Driver’s License, Vehicle Registration card, the Insurance certificate and the pollution certificate. In case you are not carrying them, ClimbOn Hyderabad is not liable for any consequences you may have to face, as described in the motor vehicle Act. All you need to do is carry them with you and the ride will be seamless. <br/>* Helmet (Full Faced/ Half Faced), A full sleeved jacket of any kind or a hoodie and Shoes are mandatory for all the riders. (It is highly recommended for a pillion too, to wear a helmet). <br/>* Every rider will follow the hand signs and safety instructions as instructed by the Host. <br/>*No stunting, racing or any activities those are hazardous to the rider and other vehicles on the high way. <br/>* Consuming Alcohol and Smoking tobacco and products related to it in any form are restricted, from the time of assembling at the meeting point, until dispersing at the closing point <br/>* Your host will carry the First-Aid kit throughout the event (Just in case). </p> <p><b>How much do I pay:  </b><br/>200/-  (Clubfee, Basic First Aid, Expertise, Tea/Coffee). <br/>Fuel, Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner, water and all other personal expenses are excluded. </p> <p><b>What could be the expenses I have to incur? </b><br/>Bikes @ 35 KMPL avg. mileage-Fuel-840/-  <br/>Cuts down by half if you are getting a pillion.<br/>Breakfast, Lunch and Dinner &amp; Water=30+100+100 </p> <p><b>Disclaimer</b>: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.  </p> '),(561,'1470671580000','Morning Cycling ride to Gandipet Lake and Games','233209018','1471283527000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233209018/','ClimbOn Sandeep - 8008004360','2016-08-14 05:30:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-08-15 17:52:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride to Gandipet Lake. We will start from HBC bike station Gachibowli. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p>[Gandipet Lake]</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/5/d/4/600_449142452.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Weather is just awesome in Hyderabad - We might get a chance to enjoy the mist on our way </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/f/8/9/600_451292649.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>!!!Important - those who plan to rent - </b></p> <p><b>Please carry an original ID card</b> like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station 10-20 minute before to rent the cycles. </p> <p><b>Cost - </b>Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit etc.)</p> <p> [ Please bring exact change ] </p> <p><b>Own Bicycle Rent Cost</b> - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly -  Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee  Rs 100/-</p> <p><i>Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event,</i></p> '),(562,'1470805056000','Fitness through swimming in an Indoor Pool (For the Beginners also)','233250675','1471159832000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233250675/','Contact Event Organiser: ClimbOn-Arvind (9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1)','2016-08-14 11:30:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-08-14 07:30:00.000000','<p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood</p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(563,'1469652817000','Backpacking to Kasol and Kheerganga in Himachal Pradesh','232928123','1472097198000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232928123/','ClimbOn Arvind 9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1','2016-08-18 20:00:00.000000','past','Kashmiri Gate Delhi','Delhi','in','ISBT ',0,'2016-08-25 03:53:00.000000','<p>We are organising a 3 days solo backpacking trip from Delhi to Kasol and nearby beautiful places in Himachal, which deserve to be in your bucket list this year. This trekking would be of moderate level with a total of ~30 kms in 3 days (~10-12 km each day).</p> <p><b><i>Important Instruction:  </i></b><i><b>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Here we plan to provide you a solo travel experience. After reaching Kasol only, we will plan which nearby places to be covered. For this event, club is mainly </b>bringing like minded people together for a trek. We will share the cost as and when we spend. </i><i><b>Please note that </b></i><i>we strictly follow no smoking, no alcohol, no littering, and no water pollution policy. </i><b><i>We request  participants to </i><i> be considerate and responsible and just enjoying each moment.</i><i> Participation would be </i></b><i><b>revoked at any time for any reason including (but not limited to) unsocial behaviour, misconduct, or participation in illegal activities during the event.  You are solely responsible for your </b>behaviour/conduct during the event. <b>B</b></i><b><i>y clicking RSVP you agree to these terms. </i></b></p> <p><b>Below are a few places that we plan to cover in these 3 days:</b></p> <p><b>Kasol:</b> Away from your boss, away from your office, far in end of Parvati valley in the Himalayas, there lies a village town called Kasol, also known as mini Amsterdam in India. It’s located in Himachal Pradesh, just 500 km from National capital Delhi. In recent years, it has become a hub for backpack travellers. It’s a base for Himalayan trekking.  It’s famous for River side spots, foreigners (We could see lots of Israelis and other foreign nationals roaming around) and base camp to many important trek routes in the region. Great place to enjoy local and Israeli cuisines. </p> <p><a href=\"http://www.drifterplanet.com/kasol/\"><a href=\"http://www.drifterplanet.com/kasol/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.drifterplanet.com/kasol/</a></a></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/8/d/e/600_452559134.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/b/3/f/600_452559743.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Kheerganga Meadows:</b> From Kasol, as you move on a refreshing trek for an exhilarating scenic views you reach a place none other than to Kheerganga.  It is open seven months a year and maximum height you gain is 9700 ft. The place is well-connected by road till Barshaini and it take 5 to 7 hrs to trek. The distance covered is 12-14 Km on foot. Best time to go to kheerganga is April to November. One just can’t get enough of the natural hot water spring experience this place offers. For Stay and lodging, Kheerganga offers basic accommodation in village. There are numerous options for guest house available to stay overnight. Camping can also be done with own tents in Kheerganga. Once you reach main Kheerganga area explore the meadows on to your right Far away from the claws of technology, this little place has the potential to melt your heart in the first visit itself. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/8/6/5/600_452559013.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Manikaran (Optional in plan): </b>Manikaran is located in the Parvati Valley on river Parvati, northeast of Bhuntar in the Kullu District of Himachal Pradesh. It is at an altitude of 1760 m and is located about 45 km from Kullu and 5 kms from Kasol.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/8/7/4/600_452559028.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Malana (First Democracy of the world; Optional in Plan):</b> Malana is a small village in Himachal Pradesh, India said to be the first democracy of world.  A hidden magic at the foothills of Himalayas lies a hamlet. Malana is a perfect for a weekend gateway from the hustles and bustles of a normal monotonous city life.  Some call it \'The Village of Taboos’, some story tellers claim that Malana is \'The World\'s Oldest Democracy\' although the village gained a lot of popularity in recent year. Its 2 hours trek to reach village from motor head.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/8/c/9/600_452559113.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Rasol trek (Optional in Plan):</b></p> <p>Amazing view 4 hours of trekking from kasol will lead you to this beautiful village called Rasol.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/0/3/600_452559171.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/8/f/f/600_452559167.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Tentative Plan:</b></p> <p><b>18th Aug, Day 0 (Thursday):</b>  From your place to Delhi; and from Delhi to Kasol (520 Kms) by night bus (HRTC bus are cheap and safe)</p> <p><i>Night bus from Delhi  at 9:50 PM  (Kashmiri Gate; Tata AC Bus) for Bhuntar. Buses from Delhi to Kullu/Manali</i><i> generally have a stop at Bhuntar (8:00 AM). Bhuntar is the entry to Parvati valley. Its only 32 kms from Kasol.</i></p> <p><b>19th Aug, Day 1 (Friday):</b>  Morning, Reach Kasol (~10:00 AM). Kasol Local Bazaar + Manikaran+ Malana/rasol trek (2-3 hrs trek). Stay at Kasol.</p> <p><b>20th Aug, Day 2 (Saturday):</b> Post breakfast we will start to Manikaran and barsaini: 40 Kms, and then Barsaini to Kheerganga*: 12 Kms trek (5 hours trek) . Entire evening at Kheerganga and take bath at Hot water springs and enjoy the nature. Sleeping in the tent/home stay. </p> <p><b>21st Aug;</b> Day 3 (<b>Sunday</b>):  KheerGanga to Barsaini (4 hours trek) + Visit to Manikaran Gurudwara + Kasol (we will spend time near parvati river till evening).</p> <p><b>21st Aug, Evening: End of the event. You may choose coming back to Delhi by night bus.</b></p> <p><b>22nd Aug;</b> Day 4 (Monday): Delhi in the morning at 6:00 AM and then go back to your place by flight/train.</p> <p><b>THINGS TO PACK:</b></p> <p>·  Rucksack bag</p> <p>·  Sleeping bag</p> <p>·  Good thick woolens</p> <p>·  Woolen socks</p> <p>·   Good walking / trekking shoes</p> <p>·   Water bottle</p> <p>·   Sun screen lotion would be good (if needed)</p> <p>·   Sunglasses</p> <p>·   Towel</p> <p>·  Torch</p> <p>·  basic medicines</p> <p>Cost:  <b>Rs. 300 Club fee (tents, stationary, medical kit support etc) + </b>Rest all, whatever it is, will be shared on spot.  Ballpark figure from Delhi is appx Rs. 5500.</p> <p>Delhi to Bhuntar and Kullu to Delhi: ~Rs 2400 (Himgaurva Tata AC bus; onwards journey 9:50 PM and return journey Kullu to Delhi 7:00 PM Bus; <b>book it  though HRTC or ask organiser to book it for you)</b></p> <p>Other travel: Kasol, Manikaran, Malana ~ Rs 1000 (<b>we will share the cost at the spot</b>)</p> <p>Stay for 3 days: ~ Rs. 900 (Sharing basis; <b>we will share the cost on the spot</b>)</p> <p>Food for 3 days: ~ Rs.900 (<b>we will share the cost on the spot</b>)</p> <p><b>Hyderabad to Delhi,</b> you could either fly or go by train. Flight cost for one side is ~Rs 3500 (<b>Book your own</b>)</p> '),(564,'1471242405000','Yoga for internal strength','233363934','1471661611000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233363934/','ClimbOn Sandeep (8-0-0-8-0-0-4-3-6-0); ClimbOn Shritej (7-8-4-2-5-2-1-4-8-4)','2016-08-20 06:00:00.000000','past','Banjara Hills','HYDERABAD','in','KBR National Park- Main Entrance Gate',0,'2016-08-20 02:53:00.000000','<p>Join us for yoga sessions for calming the mind and connecting to our inner happiness. We will explore  various aasanas and practice pranayama and meditation. </p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practiced with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b>Well known facts: </b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b>What we are going to do in  ClimbOn yoga sessions ?</b></p> <p>• Warm up with basic exercises and Sun Salutation (surya namaskaras)</p> <p>• Front bending aasanas</p> <p>• Back bending aasanas </p> <p>• Balancing</p> <p>• Pranayama</p> <p>• Meditation</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/6/3/d/600_453146173.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What you need to bring?</b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat. Alternatives are large bedsheet or towel</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b>What is the club fund?</b></p> <p>Its <b>free</b>. No club fund. You only need to pay KBR park entry fee, which is Rs 20/person.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/7/f/e/600_452999390.jpeg\" /></p> <p>So, lets enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> '),(565,'1468313599000','Lets ClimbOn to Koil Konda Fort','232557427','1471793130000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232557427/','ClimbOn Prudhvi- 9908023223 , ClimbOn Sandeep 8008004360','2016-08-21 06:00:00.000000','past','Attapur','Hyderbad','in','Pillar No 65 ',0,'2016-08-21 15:25:00.000000','<p>Koil Konda in mahboobnagar district has numerous hills and lakes. The location is 125 KM from Hyderabad. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/d/7/600_452796823.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Koilkonda Fort:</b> the erstwhile outpost of the Qutab Shahi dynasty, is perched on a hilltop, To reach the top, one needs to trudge across a deep canyon on the west or a series of streams if coming through east before reaching a flight of steps that leads to the fort.</p> <p>To enter the Koilkonda Fort, seven gates have to be crossed. The first one spots an inscription of Ibrahim Qutab Shah that dates back to 1550. Fourth gate leads to a dilapidated palace. Along with the fort, which itself is a magnificent structure, there is also a mosque, an Idgah and a pond. The Fort also has an old ashurkhana/Masjid dedicated to Bibi Fatima and is revered by both Hindus and Muslims.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/e/6/600_452796838.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Who can take part in</b>: The whole world :D. One who is fit mentally.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/f/2/600_452796850.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/f/a/600_452796858.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Level of difficulty: Chill folks, we\'ll make sure U \'just do it\'. Based on climatic conditions one can experience bouldering, rock climbing, rappelling,  chimney and basic knots training.</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/0/b/2/600_452797042.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Intent</b> : Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor climbing and make you experience the true nature of physical and mental strength in you.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/0/3/5/600_452796917.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary</b>:</p> <p>6:00 AM Assemble at Meeting Point <br/>9:00 AM Reach Koil Konda. On our way let\'s pause at a hotel eat and pack some for afternoon.<br/>9:15 AM Lo, here it begins.<br/>[Fun]<br/>[Adventure]<br/>[Fun]<br/>4:30 PM Tired?? let\'s start moving back to Hyderabad. Hasta la vista.<br/>8:00 PM Reached Hyderabad!!!</p> <p><b>Mode of Commute</b>: Personal transport. Get your vehicles or we can share with others. It\'s not too far so not to worry much about transport.</p> <p><b>Instructions</b>:<br/>• Tee shirt, Tracks - No shorts,<br/>• Shoes are a MUST, Cap advised.<br/>• Some fruits, juices, Snacks to Fill On to \'ClimbOn\'.<br/>• 2-3 Liters of water is mandatory and lunch.</p> <p><b>Cost breakup</b>: RS.300/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise [Know-how], equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included).<br/>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p><b>Direct numbers</b> : ClimbOn Prudhvi- 9908023223 , ClimbOn Sandeep 8008004360</p> <p><b>Disclaimer</b>: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms.  </p> '),(566,'1471801678000','Breakfast, chit-chat and a sweet 65k leisure cycling ride to shamshabad airport','233514640','1472794337000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233514640/',NULL,'2016-08-27 05:30:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-09-02 05:32:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride to Shamshabad airport. We will start from HBC bike station Gachibowli. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p><b>When </b>: Saturday, 5:00 AM<br/><b>Distance</b>: 65- 70 Kms<br/><b>Duration</b>: 4 to 5 hours</p> <p><b>Important!!! </b>- those who plan to rent - Please carry an original ID card like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station 10-20 minute before to rent the cycles.</p> <p><b>Cost - </b>Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit etc.)</p> <p>[ Please bring exact change ] Own Bicycle Rent Cost - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly - Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee Rs 100/-</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event</p> '),(567,'1471348025000','Rappelling,Rock climbing and hiking at Khajaguda','233392277','1472365457000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233392277/','Contact Event Organiser:  Rohith ClimbOn-9676722155','2016-08-27 06:00:00.000000','past',' near Raidurgam Bus stop Mumbai Highway Road ','Hyderabad','in','Khajaguda',0,'2016-08-28 06:24:00.000000','<p>Khajaguda is quality outdoor climbing locations all varying in scenery, rock quality and texture. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/2/c/9/600_453184809.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/3/0/9/600_453184873.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/5/1/d/600_436790461.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Spend the day with our certified guide learning the basics of rock climbing and improving your top-roping skills and techniques.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/9/3/2/600_436762834.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor rock climbing experiences. </p> <p><b>Basic Rappelling and Scrambling:</b></p> <p>Time : 6am  - 11:30 am</p> <p>Tee shirt</p> <p>Tracks - No shorts please. </p> <p>Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>Cap advised</p> <p>Water 2 liter</p> <p>Snacks to Fill On to Climb On.</p> <p>Cost breakup: Rs. 100/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], Equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included) <br/><b>Gear Provided.</b>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p>Meet up at Raidurgam bus-stop  near Wells Fargo at 6:00 AM. </p> '),(568,'1472045613000','Fitness through swimming in an Indoor Pool (For the Beginners also)','233585929','1472306452000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233585929/','Contact Event Host: ClimbOn Shritej (7-8-4-2-5-2-1-4-8-4)','2016-08-27 18:00:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-08-27 14:00:00.000000','<p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood</p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(569,'1470305657000','Royal Enfield Exclusive. Let\'s dug dug dug to Ananthgiri Hills ! Royal style!','233112705','1472392353000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233112705/','Meeting point: Morine Bakery, Call your host Sandeep @ 800-800-4360','2016-08-28 05:30:00.000000','past','Vikarabad','Vikarabad','in','Ananthgiri Hills',0,'2016-08-28 13:52:00.000000','<p>Don\'t get so busy making a living that you forget to make a life. Motorcycle riding gives you a sense of freedom, so we are getting there folks. Riding with ClimbOn Motorbiking adventure Touring is just getting better and better and better. This time we are going to make so much noise, that we become head turners and while all the attention is on our convoy, we make a Royal move on the road to Ananthgiri Hills on the Royal Enfields.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/3/5/600_452796661.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This is an exclusive event for Riding enthusiasts, owning a Royal Enfield and also our fabulous ClimbOn riding team, who wants to join this event, by renting one of the favorite Enfields.</p> <p><b>Let the leaking oil of our bikes mark their territory.</b></p> <p>                                                                                 <b> - <i>ClimbOn COMBAT.</i></b></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/b/0/5/600_452795589.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Where are we going on our bikes?</b>  </p> <p><b>Ananthagiri </b></p> <p>Ananthagiri Hills are located at Vikarabad, Ranga Reddy district, TG, India. It is 5 kms from Vikarabad and 80 Kms from Hyderabad. The water flows from these hills to Osman Sagar and Himayat Sagar. It is one of the dense forests in Telangana. Ananthagiri Temple is located in this forested area. It is the Birthplace of Musi river, which flows through Hyderabad.<br/><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>What do we visit at Anantagiri Hills?</b></p> <p><b>Anantha Padmanabhaswamy Temple:</b></p> <p>It is one of the earliest habitat areas. Ancient caves, medieval fort structures and temple show the antiquity of this area.</p> <p><b>Kotpalli Reservoir:</b></p> <p>This is a reservoir located 28 Kms from Ananthagiri hills. Very often, Kayaking is also available at this place.</p> <p> <b>Haritha Resort:</b></p> <p>Harita resort operated by Govt. of Telangana has a swimming pool in it and serves buffet lunch as well. (If a dhaba is preferred, we shall have lunch at a Dhaba). </p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/5/d/5/600_452814741.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Who can come: </b></p> <p><b>* You should be above the age of 18, holding a valid 2 wheeler Driving License. <br/>* This is exclusive event for Royal Enfield owners and riders, who could rent a RE, to join us.</b></p> <p><b>* Contact your organizers for bike renting options. </p> <p>* Pillions: It is the riders choice to get his own pillion or rent one (Haha Kidding!) You can ask for one and if there is a need, organizer will let you know. Fuel cost has to be shared with the rider. </b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p>Schedule:</p> <p><b>5:30AM-Meeting at Morine Bakery, Nanal Nagar (2nd signal after Mehandipatnam bus stop, Land Mark: Big Hand sign statue at the intersection of the road.) </p> <p>5:30-6:00AM-Briefing of Hand signs and orientation on safe riding habits. </p> <p>06:00 AM-Start towards Ananthagiri Hills </p> <p>07:30 AM-Stop for Breakfast &amp; Chai at Chevella </p> <p>08:30 AM-Arrive at Anantapadmanabha Swamy temple </p> <p>09:00 AM-Go to the fantastic view point at the hills. Spend time clicking pictures and a lot of selfies for sure </b></p> <p><b><br/>10:00 AM- Start to Kotpalli Reservoir </p> <p>10:40 AM- Reach the reservoir &amp; If available, we shall do Kayaking or chill out until we get back to our scooters. </p> <p>12:00 PM- Start back to Anantagiri hills, to visit Harita Resort and swim if the pool is open. <br/>(We can refresh at this place. Washrooms are available and they are clean) </p> <p>01:00 PM- Have lunch at the resort itself or we can go to a dhaba on the way back. </p> <p>05:00 PM- Back at Morine bakery, Hyd and disperse. </b></p> <p><b>Safety Instructions:   </b></p> <p><b>This ride happens at a professional level, unlike any rides you may have attended before. This is going to be a wonderful experience to you, fellow riders and a visual treat for the onlookers on the roads, provided we all stick to the expectations as described below: </p> <p>Monsoon folks! It might rain. Bring in your rain wear. Event happens despite of rain. We will definitely stop and wait if it is a downpour. If it just drizzles, you don\'t know how fantastic it will be to ride. </b></p> <p>Get extra pair of clothes and toiletries, if you want to get wet in the reservoir</p> <p>* Since we will be riding our bikes, being cautious on the road is vital. Please ensure that your bike is in good condition (Headlight, Brake Light, Indicators and Horn are in working condition and both Mirrors are to be on the bike.) <br/>* Carry your Driver’s License, Vehicle Registration card, the Insurance certificate and the pollution certificate. In case you are not carrying them, ClimbOn Hyderabad is not liable for any consequences you may have to face, as described in the motor vehicle Act. All you need to do is carry them with you and the ride will be seamless.  <br/>* Helmet (Full Faced/ Half Faced), a Full Sleeved Jacket or a Hoodie and Shoes are mandatory for all the riders. (It is highly recommended for a pillion too, to wear a helmet).  <br/>* Every rider will follow the hand signs and safety instructions as instructed by the Host. <br/>*No stunting, racing or any activities those are hazardous to the rider and other vehicles on the highway. <br/>* Consuming Alcohol and Smoking tobacco and products related to it in any form are restricted, from the time of assembling at the meeting point, until dispersing at the closing point <br/>* Your host will carry the First-Aid kit throughout the event (Just in case). </p> <p><b>Convenience Instructions: </b></p> <p><b><i>* Since we may do kayaking at Kotpalli Reservoir, get a pair of slippers, as you cannot sit with the shoes on. As swimming is also an option at Harita resort, get an extra pair of clothes. For boys, swimming shorts are provided. Remember folks.. If you are getting your clothes, make sure they are of Sportswear type(Changing rooms and showers are available there, for men and women separately). Cotton shorts are not allowed in the pool. For kayaking they might charge close to 400/- and for swimming it is less than 150/-. </i><br/></b></p> <p><b>How much do you pay: </b></p> <p>Post the event, each participant has to pay 150/- (Includes Tea/Coffee, Organizer’s Reimbursement and the Club Fee &amp; Expertise). </p> <p><b>Disclaimer</b>: The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times, including when coming to/going from the event (need to follow traffic and road safety instructions such as wearing helmet, using car seat belt etc.). By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms. </p> '),(570,'1472044715000','Yoga for internal strength','233585613','1472352177000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233585613/','ClimbOn Shritej (7-8-4-2-5-2-1-4-8-4)','2016-08-28 06:00:00.000000','past','Banjara Hills','HYDERABAD','in','KBR National Park- Main Entrance Gate',0,'2016-08-28 02:42:00.000000','<p>Join us for yoga sessions for calming the mind and connecting to our inner happiness. We will explore  various aasanas and practice pranayama and meditation. </p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practiced with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b>Well known facts: </b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b>What we are going to do in  ClimbOn yoga sessions ?</b></p> <p>• Warm up with basic exercises and Sun Salutation (surya namaskaras)</p> <p>• Front bending aasanas</p> <p>• Back bending aasanas </p> <p>• Balancing</p> <p>• Pranayama</p> <p>• Meditation</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/6/3/d/600_453146173.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What you need to bring?</b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat. Alternatives are large bedsheet or towel</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b>What is the club fund?</b></p> <p>Its <b>free</b>. No club fund. You only need to pay KBR park entry fee, which is Rs 20/person.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/7/f/e/600_452999390.jpeg\" /></p> <p>So, lets enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> '),(571,'1469213407000','Let\'s trek to Untouched Nature in Shayadri mountains-THE RAJMACHI TREK','232809186','1473044185000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/232809186/','Rohithdeekshith CLIMBON - 9676722155','2016-09-02 20:00:00.000000','past','Nampally','Hyderabad','in','Hyderabad Railway Station at Nampally',0,'2016-09-05 02:56:00.000000','<p>Important Instructions: </p> <p>1) No smoking and no alcohol </p> <p>2) No littering, no pollution of water </p> <p>3) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable </p> <p>4) Ladies and gents accommodation is separate in tents. </p> <p>5) Food will be mostly vegetarian </p> <p>6) We carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers </p> <p>7) If you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately. </p> <p>8) If you can\'t swim don\'t go deep into the water</p> <p>If u want an unique trekking experience then come and join CLIMBON in this monsoon will explore and find the hidden falls and forts of  RAJMACHI......</p> <p>• <b>IMPORTANT NOTE:- Do RSVP</b>, Join the waiting list, make the payment, once we receive your payment you will be moved into going list.</p> <p><b>Trek Notes </b>: Only for Ages 18+ and who are physically fit.</p> <p>• Where                   :     Rajmachi Hills,Maharastra</p> <p>• Category              :    Trekking &amp; exploration</p> <p>• Difficulty level     :    Medium</p> <p>• Trek Duration      :   2 Days (We will start on Friday and back by Monday)</p> <p><b>Trek details:-</b></p> <p><b>Rajmachi (Udhewadi)</b> is a small village in the rugged mountains of in Sahyadri,India The fortification at Rajmachi consists of two forts,namely Shrivardhan fort and manaranjan fort. Rajmachi Fort is a popular trekking destination. It is a very famous fort located near two famous hills of Maharastra, Lonavala and Khanadala.</p> <p>•   It is about 15 km treking distance from Lonavala.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/c/e/c/600_452388364.jpeg\" /></p> <p>• Rajmachi is one of the famous trek in Shayadri mountains and one of the favorite destination for every trekker and beginners . The height of this fort 2710 Feet . This fort built by Shivaji in 17th century.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/c/f/4/600_452388372.jpeg\" /></p> <p>• At the base of the Mountain is the serene Tungarli Lake surrounded by waterfalls while Kondhavi Caves can be found on top of the fort. There is a beautiful temple of Kal-Bhairavi between the twin forts. The view from top of the Fort is panoramic comprising Ulhās River, Duke’s Nose.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/f/5/f/600_452388991.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/f/a/a/600_452389066.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Lonavala and descend from Karjat . Trek route for both side surrounded by dense forest so you can get opportunity to see different species of birds and animals . </p> <p><b>Tentative Plan::</b></p> <p>• Day 1:</p> <p>• Start to Pune by evening 8:00 PM by Mumbai Express(17032) </p> <p>• Day 2:</p> <p>• 11:00 -  Reach Karjat and take public transport to base.</p> <p>• 12:00 - Start trek to Rajmachi Fort </p> <p>• 19:00 - Reach the Fort and look for place to camp.</p> <p>• Day 3:</p> <p>• 05:00 Wake-Up and get ready</p> <p>• 06:00 to 11:30 Explore Summit - Sheevardhan and Manaranjan forts.Trek trough      the most scenic Route -Ulhas valley and reach Lonavala. </p> <p>• 03:00 Start from Lonavala to Hyderabad</p> <p>Day 4:</p> <p>• reach hyd early in the morning and then sayonara !!! :)</p> <p><b>Cost :</b></p> <p>INR.Rs 2200/- approx. ball park figure per head which includes transport /camping/first aid/club fund/organiser\'s expences</p> <p>pls transfer the above mentioned costs for confirmation of slots </p> <p>Name : rohith eravalli <br/>Bank :kotak mahendra bank <br/>Branch : somagiguda <br/>Acc/no :9211678893 <br/>IFSC code : KKBK0000552</p> <p>Mention trek name for easy identification thank you....</p> <p><i><b>------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</b></i></p> <p><b><i>Trekking outfit and things to bring: </i><br/></b></p> <p><b>·1- Light colored/stretchable tracks. </b>Carry only 2 excess pair  (Night wear + a pair for swimming ) anything additional will increase your Dead Load.</p> <p>2- <b>Sleeping Bag:</b> Please buy/borrow//beg if you don\'t have one. Basic model will be enough. In case you intend to suffer- Bring 2 blankets at least to wrap Yourself comfortably.</p> <p>3.  <b>Rucksack </b>.....  Make sure you pack all the things into one Backpack[including sleeping bag] + pack all your clothes in polythene covers so that they won’t get wet even when it drowns. ... YOU will have to carry 3 liters water.</p> <p>4- <b>Torch: </b>This is must ... please buy a good one, which gives you a sharp beam.</p> <p>5- <b>Shoes</b>: NEVER wear a new shoe on a hike, carry extra pair of<br/>socks.  Prefer Hiking Shoes over sport shoe which have strong-light rubber<br/>soles &amp; good ankle support+ 1 pair of slippers.</p> <p>6-Medicines: Bring personal medicines if you have any. The organizer will bring First Aid Kit.</p> <p>7-Identity &amp; Address proof\'s; Preferably issued by GOI/GO Telangana  with <i>a xerox copy of it.</i></p> <p>7-<b>Energy Food</b>: Dates, Electrol /glucose/energy bars/chocolates etc... any snack for your new friends .. Must ..Must.. Must...;)</p> <p>8 Other things(<b>Optional</b>) Knife, Mirror, Towel, Brush &amp; Match box/lighter,..........You never know when u will have to stand against odds</p> <p>9- Two emergency notes with your name, address, emergency contact number.</p> <p>10: A camera for KODAK moments (<b>optional</b>), DSLR\'s welcome</p> <p>===&gt; Few things in between are not planned and these things are must in an adventure trek.</p> <p>Note : Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. CLIMBON earnestly requests all its members to be socially responsible whilst the treks and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology. Try to avoid plastics as much as possible, especially plastic smiles.</p> <p>Important Instructions: <br/>1) No smoking and no alcohol <br/>2) No littering, no pollution of water <br/>3) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable <br/>4) Ladies and gents accommodation is separate in tents. <br/>5) Food will be mostly vegetarian <br/>6) We carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers <br/>7) If you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately. <br/>8) If you can\'t swim don\'t go deep into the water.</p> <p><b>Important</b> : Answers all the questions otherwise your RSVP will not be considered</p> <p><b>NOTE:</b> Event Hosts have all the rights to add or remove any member and do necessary changes in route, activity, time, duration depending on the situations and climate conditions. ORGANIZER\'S DECISION IS FINAL (ITS ALL ABOUT SAFETY, PLEASE CO-OPERATE)</p> <p><b><i>For any more questions, please reach out to the organizer of the event <br/></i></b></p> <p><b><i>-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</i></b></p> <p><b>Disclaimer: </b>The organizer(s) of this meetup is/are not responsible for any loss or accidents to participants of this event. All participants must conduct themselves in a safe and appropriate manner and comply with the event safety standards, organizers\' instructions and procedure at all times. By clicking RSVP you agree to these terms. </p> <p>Contact:-</p> <p>Rohith-9676722155 (Whats app preferred)</p> '),(572,'1472532496000','Yoga for internal strength','233730159','1472871580000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233730159/','ClimbOn Shritej (7-8-4-2-5-2-1-4-8-4)','2016-09-03 06:00:00.000000','past','Banjara Hills','HYDERABAD','in','KBR National Park- Main Entrance Gate',0,'2016-09-03 02:59:00.000000','<p>Join us for yoga sessions for calming the mind and connecting to our inner happiness. We will explore  various aasanas and practice pranayama and meditation.   </p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practiced with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b>Well known facts: </b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b>What we are going to do in  ClimbOn yoga sessions ?</b></p> <p>• Warm up with basic exercises and Sun Salutation (surya namaskaras)</p> <p>• Front bending aasanas</p> <p>• Back bending aasanas </p> <p>• Balancing</p> <p>• Pranayama</p> <p>• Meditation</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/6/3/d/600_453146173.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What you need to bring?</b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat. Alternatives are large bedsheet or towel</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b>What is the club fund?</b></p> <p>Its <b>free</b>. No club fund. You only need to pay KBR park entry fee, which is Rs 20/person.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/7/f/e/600_452999390.jpeg\" /></p> <p>So, lets enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> '),(573,'1472571838000','Fitness through swimming in an Indoor Pool (For the Beginners also)','233739144','1472881670000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233739144/','Contact Event Host: ClimbOn Arvind (9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1)','2016-09-03 10:00:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-09-03 05:47:00.000000','<p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood</p> <p><b>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </b> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</p> <p><b>Cost: Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges</b>, which includes <b>swimming costumes (for Boys). Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes. </b>As we would be repeating this event every week, you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO</b></p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(574,'1472561337000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','233735519','1473093065000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233735519/','ClimbOn Prudhvi 9908023223, Climb On shiva - 9866984814','2016-09-03 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-09-05 16:31:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 3 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 9:30PM-12:00 AM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/0/600_448372560.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/5/d/600_448372573.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/6/600_448372582.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/d/6/d/600_448372589.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>6.00: Game shuru</p> <p>8.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>8.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 150 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Prudhvi 9908023223, climb 