p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/c/b/3/600_449388307.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Moving around in Matheran</b></p> <p>The only modes of transport, on the red soiled roads, are on horseback or by man-pulled rickshaw or on foot. It is one of the few places in the world where all motorised vehicles are banned which makes the place unique. That calls for trekking all the way.</p> <p><b>Height</b> </p> <p>At an elevation of about 800m (2,625 ft) above Mean Sea Level.</p> <p><b>Area</b></p> <p>5000 acres or eight sq miles</p> <p><b>Climate </b><br/>Matheran has cool and moderate climate. During monsoon rainfall is heavy and it provides a different charm. The climate after the rains is very pleasant.</p> <p><b>Topography</b></p> <p>Level with sparse undulations. The topmost layer of rock is of soft porous iron-clay with abundant small black boulders. The surface is covered by red soil with less humus.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/c/9/3/600_449435987.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>About our trek</b></p> <p>We will stay in a booked Guest House </p> <p><b>Difficulty Level</b>: Medium (Approx 15-20 kms in 2 days)</p> <p><b>09th September 2016 (Friday)</b></p> <p>Leave by Train No 17032 Mumbai Express which will depart from Nampally / Begumpet station at 8.40 pm</p> <p><b>10th September 2016 (Saturday)</b></p> <p>11:00 am:  Reach Karjat <br/>11:30 am: Local train to Nerul <br/>12.30 pm : Trek to Matheran /Board Toy train to Metheran which is an awesome journey<br/> 2.30 pm: Reach Matheran and<a href=\"http://s.igmhb.com/click?v=SU46MTE2NTI1OjEzOTk6Y2hlY2s6OTViNjUzMGFlYjllNjFlNGNlMGNmMzU4ZTczNmY1Mjk6ei0yNDkyLTg3NzM0NjUzOnd3dy5tZWV0dXAuY29tOjMzNjU0MzpiMjZmYTQ0NmY4MjkyNTMzYzgxODkyZmY1NzI4OTY3NTplNDY0NGU1Zjg1NjA0NTgyOTg2NDRiN2Y3ZDQwMDdjNzoxOmRhdGFfc3MsMTA5OXgxOTIwO2RhdGFfcmMsMztkYXRhX2ZiLG5vOzo0NDIxMjk3OnZ3b3B0LDA&amp;subid=g-87734653-52128aaa073e42e88d2929b7cb4d0c87-&amp;data_ss=1099x1920&amp;data_rc=3&amp;data_fb=no&amp;data_tagname=A&amp;data_ct=image_only&amp;data_clickel=link&amp;data_sid=490ff72c6c75738f781ab15382791b21\"> check</a> into Guest House and we will cover few places like Sunset point and Chaorlete Lake after a break.  <br/>10 pm: Dinner, Chat up and Sleep</p> <p><b>11th September (Sunday)</b></p> <p>4:30 am: Wake Up Call <br/>5 am - 2pm : We will cover some awesome places like Sunrise point,Alexandar Point,One tree point and do shopping in Matheran Market <br/> 2pm - Pack luggage and start to Karjat</p> <p>4.50 pm - Catch Train no:11019 Konark Express from Karjat</p> <p>12th September (Monday):</p> <p>7:00 am / 7.50 am: Reach  Begumpet /Secunderabad Station.</p> <p><b>Itinerary </b>may change depending on situations</p> <p><b>Things to bring : </b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts[Comfortable]</p> <p>- Raincoat</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. </p> <p>- Sleeping bag or thick blanket</p> <p> - Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p> - Torch light with extra set of batteries. </p> <p> - A proper rucksack (backpack) to keep all of the above things </p> <p> - Camera to capture awesome places.[Optional] </p> <p> - Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Important Instructions:  </b></p> <p> <b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm. This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p><b> Damages: 2900/- Ball park figure</b> [Transport + Accommodation] Will share  the cost if it is more or less. [ Food is excluded]</p> '),(579,'1471934187000','Night camping Beside Lake @ Pocharam Forest 10th sep','233554308','1473708828000','https://www.meetup.