upstatic.com/photos/event/8/7/7/9/600_443014681.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Instructions</b></p> <p>1) No smoking/alcohol and No littering <br/>2) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable <br/>3) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention. <br/>4) If you need any, bring it to the organizers notice. </p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b> Wear Full track pants (avoid jeans). T-shirts(half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>Wear sport/trekking shoes only </p> <p>sun cap</p> <p><b> Mandatory things </b></p> <p>Water bottles - 2x1 lit MUST</p> <p>Get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch MUST  to climb on after and during the trek.<br/>Get your camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p><i>RSVP Rules: We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP  \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case,  just its a humble request to please inform the Organiser a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i> </p> <p><b>Meeting Place:</b> Balanagar X roads bus stop towards Jeedimetla. </p> <p><b>Transport: </b>We will be traveling on our vehicles (bikes and cars),on fuel contribution basis. This is a half day trip and we shall be back by 1 PM.</p> <p><b>Cost:</b> Rs 100 towards club. </p> <p><b>Contact Details: ClimbOn Rohith-9676722155</b></p> <p><b>Difficulty </b>- Moderate.</p> <p>Please Be On time.</p> '),(586,'1474474262000','Time To Embrace Cycling In Rain !!!','234296889','1474815590000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234296889/',NULL,'2016-09-25 17:00:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-09-25 14:59:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride to Gandipet Lake. We will start from HBC bike station Gachibowli. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat. [Gandipet Lake]</p> <p>Weather is just awesome in Hyderabad - We might get a chance to enjoy the mist on our way !!!Important - those who plan to rent - Please carry an original ID card like your valid Driving license, PAN card etc. The ID card will be kept as deposit at HBC and will be returned back after the ride on returning the bike. Please be at bike station 10-20 minute before to rent the cycles. Cost - Club Fee - 50/- (includes stationary, first aid kit, patch kit etc.)</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/c/3/6/2/600_454370018.jpeg\" /></p> <p>[ Please bring exact change ] Own Bicycle Rent Cost - Zero if you are bringing you own bicycle. Those who are renting bicycle will need to pay rent to HBC counter directly - Rs 50/- for 3 hours. One time Registration Fee Rs 100/-</p> <p><b>Note: </b>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event,</p> '),(587,'1470286170000','Talakona Waterfalls Trek and Horsely Hills','233109517','1475462699000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/233109517/','ClimbOn Babu Reddy - +91 9966693964','2016-09-30 19:00:00.000000','past','KACHEGUDA RAILWAY STATION','Hyderabad','in','KACHEGUDA RAILWAY STATION',0,'2016-10-03 02:44:00.000000','<p><b>Trek to Talakona Waterfalls  </b></p> <p>Trek  Grade : Easy  </p> <p><b>Talakona waterfalls</b></p> <p>Talakona means head hill in Telugu (tala - head and kona - hill). However, Thalakona allegorically means “the head of the Seshachalam hills” as these mountains are believed to be the starting point of the Tirumala mountain ranges.</p> <p>The Talakona forests host rare and endangered species of animals like Slender Loris, Indian Giant Squirrel, Mouse Deer, Golden Gecko, Panther, Porcupine, Chital and Sambar. Endemic species like Red Sander, Cycas beddomeii and Enteda like giant plants are also found in this region. The forest is mostly covered with sandalwood trees with some medicinal plants. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/a/d/a/600_452791450.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Gushing streams, cutting through the steep rocks, cascade from a height of 270 feet. The birds in the jungle chirp along to add to the harmonious rhythm which reverberates in the air. Apart from this, about 36 to 40 feet height, there is a 240 meter long canopy rope walk. This walk is a nerve tingling experience. This is the ambience created by the Talakona waterfall, the highest waterfall in the state. Nestled in the forests of Sri Venkateswara Park in Chittoor district, this perennial waterfall attracts picnickers, trekkers and travellers.</p> <p>The sandalwood trees cover most of the forest area leave a pleasant, lingering fragrance. The forest is also rich with valuable herbs and medicinal plants, which gave it the status of a Bio-sphere reserve in 1989. As the stream passes through these plants, it carries their curative powers and grows to be rich with minerals. The falls attract several ailing tourists to a swim to increase the human body’s immune resistance. Wide variety of rare and endangered species of animals such as Slender Loris, Indian Giant Squirrel, Mouse Deer, Golden Gecko, Panther, Porcupine, Chital and Sambar are also found in the Talakona forests.</p> <p>There are few steep climb up and climb down, a bit adventure.  </p> <p><b>Horsely Hills</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/4/c/e/600_452793998.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Horsely Hills is known for its scenic beauty and the narrow uphill roads. Surrounded by the dense growth of trees, the major tourist attractions around Horsely hills are Lake Gangotri, Highview seeing place, Gaalibanda, Environmental park and the Horsley Hills Museum. Horsley Hills is also one of the few places to offer Zorbing in India. Other adventure sports conducted are Rappelling and Trekking.</p> <p>30th September 2016 (Friday) </p> <p>Leave by Train No 12797 Venkatadri Express which will depart from Kacheguda station at 8.05 pm</p> <p><b>01st  October 2016 (Saturday)</b></p> <p>07:30 am:  Reach Tirupati<br/>11:00 am: Reach Bakarapet and start trek to falls<br/>12.30 pm : Reach falls , spend time there and forest canopy<br/>03.00 pm: Start back to Bakarapet</p> <p>04:30PM: Start to Horsely hills</p> <p>07:00PM: Reach Horsely hills. Check in at Haritha Resort  </p> <p>10 pm: Dinner, Chat up and Sleep</p> <p><b>02nd October (Sunday)</b></p> <p>05:00 am: Wake Up Call <br/>6 am - 6pm : We will cover all places in Horsely hills, do some adventure activities like zorbing, rapelling etc. depending on avialability. <br/>06pm - Start to Mulacalacheruvu</p> <p>07:30 pm - Catch Train no:12731 Padmavati Express from Mulacalacheruvu</p> <p><b>03rd October (Monday): </b></p> <p>7:05 am : Reach Secunderabad Station.</p> <p>Itinerary may change depending on situations </p> <p><b>Things to bring : </b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts[Comfortable]</p> <p>- Raincoat</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. </p> <p>- Sleeping bag or thick blanket</p> <p> - Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p> - Torch light with extra set of batteries. </p> <p> - A proper rucksack (backpack) to keep all of the above things </p> <p> - Camera to capture awesome places.[Optional] </p> <p> - Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b></p> <p><b> Note: </b>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm. This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p> <b>Damages</b>: 2500/- Ball park figure [Transport + Accommodation] Will share  the cost if it is more or less. [ Food is excluded]</p> <p>Pay 1000/- in advance to confirm your slot.. Please find details below</p> <p>Nangi Babu Reddy</p> <p>036001542305</p> <p>ICICI BANK - ICIC0000360</p> <p>Electronic City Bangalore</p> <p>How to reach us</p> <p>ClimbOn Babu Reddy - +91-9966693964</p> '),(588,'1475032639000','Yoga for internal strength','234459188','1475291110000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234459188/','ClimbOn Shritej (7-8-4-2-5-2-1-4-8-4)','2016-10-01 06:00:00.000000','past','Banjara Hills','HYDERABAD','in','KBR National Park- Main Entrance Gate',0,'2016-10-01 03:05:00.000000','<p>Join us for yoga sessions for calming the mind and connecting to our inner happiness. We will explore  various aasanas and practice pranayama and meditation.   </p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practiced with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b>Well known facts: </b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b>What we are going to do in  ClimbOn yoga sessions ?</b></p> <p>• Warm up with basic exercises and Sun Salutation (surya namaskaras)</p> <p>• Front bending aasanas</p> <p>• Back bending aasanas </p> <p>• Balancing</p> <p>• Pranayama</p> <p>• Meditation</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/6/3/d/600_453146173.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>What you need to bring?</b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat. Alternatives are large bedsheet or towel</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b>What is the club fund?</b></p> <p>Its <b>free</b>. No club fund. You only need to pay KBR park entry fee, which is Rs 20/person.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/7/f/e/600_452999390.jpeg\" /></p> <p>So, lets enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> '),(589,'1474489579000','Let\'s climb the rocks of Peerancheru with Basic Rappling 9th October','234303153','1476033325000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234303153/','Contact Event Organiser:ClimbOn-Shiva 9866984814','2016-10-09 06:00:00.000000','past','Nanal nagar X roads','Hyderabad','in','Morine bakery',0,'2016-10-09 17:15:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/b/e/9/600_445635337.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Peeran Cheruvu is on the road to Gandipet and is an awesome location for rock climbing and bouldering.</p> <p>Itinerary: Exploratory trek so nothing is planned. Responsible Bouldering: Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved nature. We request all members to be socially responsible and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology.</p> <p>6:00AM : Assemble at meetup point at Morine bakery, nanal nagar X roads (Hand Symbol)<br/>6:15 AM : Start to Peerancheru<br/>6:30AM : Reach the place and event begins<br/>****** Rock climbing*****<br/>********Bouldering******­**<br/>******Rappelling*******<br/>12:00 PM : Tired?? Let’s get back to our town. TaTa, Bubye :)</p> <p>Important Instructions:<br/>1) No smoking/alcohol and No littering<br/>2) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable<br/>3) We carry Basic First Aid, please do inform us if you need any special attention.<br/>4) If you need any, bring it to the organizers notice.</p> <p>Things to bring: Wear Full track pants (avoid jeans). T-shirts(half sleeve or full sleeve)</p> <p>Wear sport/trekking shoes only<br/>cap<br/>water bottles - 2x1 lit<br/>get fruits/juices/energy bar / something to munch on to climb on after and during the trek.<br/>Get your camera if u want to take snaps</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/2/5/e/600_445713374.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/5/4/f/600_435969551.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/8/0/e/600_435595310.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>RSVP Rules: We have some members who just RSVP \"Yes\" for the meetup and never show up at the event. Such members who do not turn up are blocking a slot for another active member a good opportunity to participate. Please respect the organizers time and efforts and cooperate with us. Do not go for RSVP \" Yes\" if you are not sure about attending the event. We do understand just-in-time situation and might go at zero-hour and might miss us, in such case, just its a humble request to please inform the Organizer a day hours before the commencement of the trek and move to Not Attending list. Thanks.</i></p> <p>Meeting Place: Mehdipatnam/Reti bowli @ Morine Bakery<br/>Transport: By personal Transport<br/>Cost: Rs 100 towards club.</p> <p>Contact Details: Shiva 9866984814</p> <p>Difficulty - Moderate.</p> <p>Please Be On time.</p> '),(590,'1473845273000','Ride to Gandikota “The Hidden Grand Canyon of India”: 15th and 16th oct 2016...','234115774','1476593969000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234115774/','Call Rohith: 9676722155','2016-10-15 04:30:00.000000','past','pillar no:-60','hyderabad','in','mehdipatnam',0,'2016-10-16 04:59:00.000000','<p>• IMPORTANT NOTE:- Do RSVP, Join the waiting list, make the payment, once we receive your payment you will be moved into going list.</p> <p>If you have ever visited America’s famous Grand Canyon in Colorado River, Gandikota, the Grand Canyon of India would remind you of that again. It is no lesser than “The Grand Canyon” in providing you the excitement of nature’s beauty. It is situated near Jammalamagudu in Erramalai hills on the right bank of the river Pennar in Kadapa district of Andhra Pradesh.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/a/8/b/4/600_445483188.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><i><br/></i></b></p> <p>GANDIKOTA:-</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/d/0/a/600_454120202.jpeg\" /></p> <p>It is appx 350 Kms from Hyderabad. To most of the travelers, it is still a hidden and unexplored place. Gandikota gets its name from the word ‘Gandi’ which means gorge and kota means fort in Telugu. There is a fort located right at the edge of this gorge. The gorge formation is such that the Pennar River flows about 90 metres below on the western and northern sides. The Valley has a beautiful landscape and lush forests, and is blessed with many natural resources. Trekking in the valley and experience the wild beauty of nature is very mesmerizing.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/2/7/4/600_445197972.jpeg\" /></p> <p>BELUM CAVES:-</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/d/4/0/600_454120256.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Belum Caves is the largest tourist cave in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_subcontinent\">Indian subcontinent</a> and the longestcaves in plains of Indian Subcontinent, known for its <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stalactite\">stalactite</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stalagmite\">stalagmite</a> formations. Belum Caves have long passages, spacious chambers, fresh water galleries and siphons. It is a natural underground cave formed by the constant flow of underground water. The caves reach its deepest point (150 feet from entrance level) at the point known as <i>Pataalaganga</i> In <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telugu_language\">Telugu language</a>, it is called బెల్లము గుహలు <i>Belum Guhalu</i></p> <p>. Belum Caves has a length of 3229 metres, making it the second largest natural caves in Indian Subcontinent after <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krem_Liat_Prah\">Krem Liat Prah</a> caves in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meghalaya\">Meghalay</a>.</p> <p><b><i># Guys, please share your mobile number with us either through an option in the answer section inside the RSVP link (preferred) or messages it to the organizers (Rohith: 9676722155; Your contact details will be visible to the organizers only.</i></b></p> <p><b>Meet-up point: 4</b>:30 AM on Saturday 15th october at Mehdipatnam pillar no:- 60</p> <p><b>Mode of transport: </b>Bike/car. Please coordinate with other members for Bike/Car pooling, if required.</p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p><b>Day 1 (Saturday): </b></p> <p>04:30AM : At meet Up point.</p> <p>05:00AM sharp -Start from Hyderabad<br/>01:00 PM -Reach Yaganti and have lunch</p> <p>05:30 PM -Reach Gandikota and food supplies<br/>06:00 PM -explore the place </p> <p>07:00 pm -Halt and pitch tents for overnight camping at suitable place having amazing landscape.<br/>08:00 PM- 12:00 AM – Night <i>campfire cooking(if possible) and dinner.</i></p> <p><b>Day 2 (Sunday)*</b><br/>05:00 AM – Good morning</p> <p>06:00 AM - 12 PM - Visit the Gandikota fort, Belum caves, Gorges, and explore the Penna River. We may also do <i>climbing/scrambling, if time allows. </i></p> <p>12:00 PM - Lunch and vote of thanks<br/>01:00 PM - Back to Hyderabad</p> <p>9:00 PM – Hello Hyderabad</p> <p><i> *We may have a little variation in the plan, based on the situations.</i></p> <p><b><i>Trekking outfit and a few things to bring: </i></b></p> <p>· Two full length track pants or loose trouser (avoid Jeans); Two T-shirts - No bright colored, one short for swimming.</p> <p>· A rucksack or a hiking bag to keep all the things with a sleeping bag or a bed-sheet/ blanket.</p> <p>· Trekking or sport shoes used at least ones with 2 pairs of socks.</p> <p>· Toiletries (Brush, tooth paste, soap, shampoo etc).</p> <p>· Hat or cap, sun screen/sun glasses.</p> <p>· At-least 3 water bottles.</p> <p>· Electrol /glucose/energy bars/chocolates etc.</p> <p>· Torch or headlight with extra spare batteries.</p> <p>· Any medications physician prescribed.</p> <p>· Two emergency notes with your name, address, emergency contact number.</p> <p>· Your photo Id with a xerox copy of it.</p> <p>· And, of-course a good and positive mood.</p> <p><b>Instructions</b></p> <p>· No smoking, alcohol, littering, and no pollution of water.</p> <p>· This is not a luxury trip, but out most care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</p> <p>· Girls and boys accommodation in separate tents</p> <p>· Food will be mostly vegetarian</p> <p>· We carry basic First Aid; if you need anything you can ask the organizers.</p> <p>· If you can\'t swim please avoid going deep into the water</p> <p>· This trip is organized only for climbers also, the one who have done few treks before.</p> <p>· This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care will be taken to make your trip comfortable</p> <p><b>Tariff: </b>Rs.400 per head, which includes Rs.300 as club fund for camping tents, trekking activities, first-Aid etc. and Rs 100 as miscellaneous charges.</p> <p><b>Food and Transport </b>(car/bike pooling in case we all have sufficient cars) not included in the club fund.We can share it accordingly. <b>In case, we do not have sufficient cars with participants, we will hire a Bus and will share the charges.</b></p> <p><b>Payment Details</b>:</p> <p>Name : rohith eravalli <br/>Bank :kotak mahendra bank <br/>Branch : somagiguda <br/>Acc/no :9211678893 <br/>IFSC code : KKBK0000552</p> <p>Mention trek name for easy identification thank you....</p> <p>We look forward to having fun!</p> <p>For any more questions, please reach out to the organizers of the event.</p> <p><b>Rohith:</b> 9676722155.</p> '),(591,'1476429054000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','234851363','1476547307000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234851363/','ClimbOn Shiva 9866984814','2016-10-15 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-10-15 16:01:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 05:30PM - 9:00PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/7/d/2/600_453858386.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/8/600_455051160.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/d/600_455051165.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/e/2/7/600_450876391.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/3/8/600_450999224.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>6.00: Game shuru</p> <p>9.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>9.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 200 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Shiva 9866984814</p> '),(592,'1474819152000','Let\'s ClimbOn to Kavadipally Hills','234393604','1476618472000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234393604/','ClimbOn Prudhvi- 9908023223 , ClimbOn ashim-9000567089','2016-10-16 06:00:00.000000','past','L B Nagar','Hyderabad','in','Orange Hospitals',0,'2016-10-16 11:47:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/f/f/b/600_439257339.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Kavadipally is on way to Ramoji Film city. A huge chain of boulders yet untouched and unexplored.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/f/7/5/600_439257205.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Who can take part in</b>: The whole world :D. One who is fit mentally.</p> <p><b>Level of difficulty</b>: Chill folks, we\'ll make sure U \'just do it\'. Based on climatic conditions one can experience bouldering, rock climbing,   chimney and basic knots training.</p> <p><b>Intent</b> : Our goal is to facilitate fun, informative, inspirational and recreational outdoor climbing and make you experience the true nature of physical and mental strength in you.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/5/6/3/600_451101859.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary</b>:</p> <p>6:00 AM : Assemble at LB nagar X Roads near Orange Hospitals<br/>6:45 AM Reach Kavadipally. On our way lets pause at a hotel eat and pack some for afternoon.<br/>7:30 AM : Lo, here it begins.<br/>[Fun]<br/>[Adventure]<br/>[Fun]<br/>5: 30 PM : Tired?? lets get back to our town. Hasta la vista.<br/>6:00 PM : Reached Hyderabad!!!</p> <p><b>Mode of Commute</b>: Personal transport. Get your vehicles or we can share with others. It\'s not too far so not to worry much about transport.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.google.co.in/maps/@17.3074222,78.7139979,388a,20y,81.96t/data=!3m1!1e3!5m1!1e4?hl=en\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.google.co.in/maps/@17.3074222,78.7139979,388a,20y,81.96t/data=!3m1!1e3!5m1!1e4?hl=en</a></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>:<br/>• Tee shirt, Tracks - No shorts,<br/>• Shoes are a MUST, Cap advised.<br/>• Some fruits, juices, Snacks to Fill On to \'ClimbOn\'.<br/>• 2-3 Liters of water is mandatory and lunch.</p> <p><b>Cost breakup</b>: RS.200/- towards Club Fund Includes Expertise[Know-how], equipment, stationary and first-Aid.(Fuel, food, water is not included).<br/>Ropes, Carabiners, Harness and necessary equipment for climbing will be provided by our club, so leave on us.</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p><b>Direct numbers</b> : ClimbOn Prudhvi- 9908023223 , ClimbOn Rohit- 9676722155</p> '),(593,'1474176590000','Trip to Hamra Hampi','234210832','1477377366000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234210832/','ClimbOn Babu Reddy - 9966693964','2016-10-21 21:00:00.000000','past','JNTU KUKATPALLY ','HYDERABAD ','IN','NEAR JNTU COLLEGE, KUKATPALLY',0,'2016-10-25 06:36:00.000000','<p><b>Organisers Experience: </b><br/>A backpacker\'s Paradise. A place worth filling few pages on your travel diary.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/4/9/2/600_446129842.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>About: </b></p> <p>Hampi, once the capital of the Vijayanagar Empire and a UNESCO World Heritage Site today,lies scattered over a landscape that leaves you spellbound: heaps of giant boulders perch precariously over miles of undulating terrain, their rusty hues offset by jade-green palm groves, banana plantations and paddy fields, while the azure sky painted with fluffy white cirrus adds to the magical atmosphere. </p> <p>               Vast stretches of boulder-strewn hills make the backdrop of Hampi unique. Dotted around the hills and valleys are 500 plus monuments. Among them are beautiful temples, basements of palaces, remains of aquatic structures, ancient market streets, royal pavilions, bastions, royal platforms, treasury buildings.., the list is practically endless. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/9/a/1/600_454231137.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/9/b/1/600_454231153.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/9/c/6/600_454231174.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/9/c/f/600_454231183.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/9/d/f/600_454231199.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Pic Credits: Sravan Kumar Dokka</p> <p><b>Indepth:</b><br/>Day 0 : Friday evening.<br/>Leave from Hyd to Hoospet.</p> <p>ITINERARY [Subject to change]:</p> <p>DAY 0 : start from HYD , catch Bus to HOSPET at 9:00 PM</p> <p>DAY 1 :</p> <p>05:30AM: Reach HAMPI , check in at Hotel</p> <p>07:00AM: Hike to Mathunga hill, Sunrise, Hampi Bazaar, Krishna Temple, Virupaksha Temple,</p> <p>Natural Archway, Zenana Enclosure, Watch Towers, Guard\'s Quarters, Hazara Rama Temple, Elephant\'s Stables, King\'s Audience Hall, King\'s Palace, Throne Platform, Octagonal Water Pavillion, Octagonal Bath, Chandrasekhara Temple .. etc</p> <p>DAY 2 : </p> <p>6AM: Wakeup Call</p> <p>7AM: We will cover VIttala Temple, Lotus Mahal, Achyutaraya Temple, Soolai Bazaar, Coraocle Ride, Rishyamuka and Anjaneya Hill via Chakratirtha and continue towards Anegondi, Pampapati temple.....</p> <p>7 PM Vacate Rooms and Start for HOSPET</p> <p>8PM Get into BUS to Hyderabad</p> <p>DAY 3: Reach Hyderabad by 06AM.  </p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts.</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. - Sleeping bag or thick blanket and a proper rucksack (backpack) (both are must) and some plastic covers.</p> <p>- Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p>- Some snacks to climb on.</p> <p>- Torch light is must.</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b><br/><i>Note:</i> No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun.</p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.<br/>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</p> <p><b>Damages: </b><br/>2400/- Will share the cost if it is more or less.<br/>[ Food is excluded]</p> <p>Pay 1000/- in advance to confirm your slot.. Please find details below</p> <p>Nangi Babu Reddy</p> <p>036001542305</p> <p>ICICI BANK - ICIC0000360</p> <p>Electronic City Bangalore</p> <p>How to reach us</p> <p>ClimbOn Babu Reddy - +91-9966693964</p> '),(594,'1476598401000','Cycling to Gandipet lake and breakfast.','234889900','1477194787000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234889900/','Call Uday @ 9666531565_Hyderabad Bicycle Station_Opp. to Bio Diversity Park','2016-10-23 05:30:00.000000','past','Gandipet','Hyderabad','in','Gandipet lake',0,'2016-10-23 03:53:00.000000','<p>Winter is already kicking in. Temperatures have dropped so much after the recent rainfall. Mornings have become fantastic. </p> <p>Gandipet lake, which has been an eye sore lately has full of water now and has become one of the best spots to visit early in the morning.</p> <p>So, how do we go there!!!</p> <p>Let us get there on the bicycles. </p> <p>En route, we can have a look at the fantastic sunrise, while we are heading towards the lake, on the Outer ring road.</p> <p>The amount of euphoria after reaching the lake, after a good amount of riding time is inexplicable.</p> <p>The fresh cold breeze on your face is a priceless experience. We all know how the roads have turned out to be lately.</p> <p><b>So where are we going?</b><br/>Gandipet Lake</p> <p><b>How are we going?</b><br/>Bicycles</p> <p><b>How long are we going to ride?</b><br/>To and Fro: 25-30 Kms</p> <p><b>Is it going to be difficult?</b><br/>Not at all. We will not push you to the limits. We will ensure that there are adequate stops and breaks.</p> <p><b>Things to know:</b></p> <p><b>What to wear?</b><br/>Anything comfortable to ride a bicycle. Preferably T shirt and a short or a jogger.</p> <p><b>Accessories:</b><br/>Shades<br/>Cycling Helmet will be provided<br/>Shoe, preferably sports or Canvas type</p> <p><b>What else should I get?</b><br/>Water Water Water<br/>2 Liters. <br/>Back pack or a pouch to carry your phone, money wallet and other stuff.</p> <p><b>When do we start and when do we come back?</b></p> <p>We shall start at 530 AM and return at 9 AM</p> <p><b>Meeting point:</b><br/>Hyderabad Bicycling Club_Opp. Bio Diversity Park,</p> <p><b>We will have breakfast on the way back.</b></p> <p><b>End point:</b><br/>Hyderabad Bicycling Club_Opp. Bio Diversity Park,</p> <p><b>Event Charges:</b><br/>25/- Only</p> <p><b>Other Charges:</b><br/>Hyderabad Bicycling Club Charges 100/- for first time registration.<br/>If you are already registered and have the slip or the card, you don\'t have to pay this.<br/><b>For those who want to rent a bicycle:</b><br/>50/- is the rental charge.<br/>* Get a govt. photo ID card, because HBC will retain it and give it back after the cycle is handed over after the ride.</p> <p><b>That\'s it. Ready to roll??</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/9/f/d/600_455110749.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/9/b/d/600_455110685.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/a/5/4/600_455110836.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/a/8/1/600_455110881.jpeg\" /></p> '),(595,'1477020588000','ClimbOn Aqua Fitness - Swimming to tone up your body (For the Beginners also)','235010751','1477202116000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235010751/','Contact Event Host: ClimbOn Arvind (9-6-4-0-4-3-1-3-5-1)','2016-10-23 10:00:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-10-23 05:55:00.000000','<p><b><i>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood.</i></b></p> <p>Benefits of Swimming</p> <p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p><b><i>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </i></b><i> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</i></p> <p><i><b>What you need to bring along?</b></i></p> <p>1- Small bag (to keep your cloths and stuff)</p> <p>2- Towel</p> <p>3- Swimming costume (for boys swimming pool guys provide a shorts, but it is good to bring your own shorts; Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes)</p> <p>4- Swimming cap (optional)</p> <p>5- Swimming goggle (optional)</p> <p><b><i>Cost:</i></b></p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO; </b><b>Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges paid to swimming pool guys</b>, which includes swimming costumes (for Boys).  As we would have been repeating this event very frequently (almost every week), you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(596,'1476947770000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','234987467','1477238453000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234987467/','Event Host: Shiva 9866984814, Prudhvi: 9908023223','2016-10-23 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-10-23 16:00:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 05:30PM - 9:00PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/7/d/2/600_453858386.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/8/600_455051160.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/d/600_455051165.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/e/2/7/600_450876391.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/3/8/600_450999224.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>6.00: Game shuru</p> <p>9.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>9.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 200 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Shiva 9866984814, Prudhvi 9908023223</p> '),(597,'1474389033000','Trek to Bhimashankar via Shidi Ghat (best trek in Sahyadri ranges)','234269952','1478511020000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234269952/','CLIMBON ROHITH - 9676722155','2016-11-04 20:00:00.000000','past','Nampally','Hyderabad','in','Hyderabad Railway Station at Nampally',0,'2016-11-07 09:30:00.000000','<p><b>IMPORTANT NOTE:</b><i> Please don\'t expect luxury in the trek, </i>Do RSVP, Join the waiting list, make the payment, once we receive your payment you will be moved into going list.</p> <p><b>Trek Notes :</b> Only for Ages 18+ and who are physically fit(not for beginners) </p> <p>• Where                   :     Bhimshanker Hills,Maharastra</p> <p>• Category              :    Trekking &amp; exploration</p> <p>• Difficulty level    :    Medium </p> <p>• Trek Duration      :   2 Days (We will start on Friday and back by Monday)</p> <p><b>Bhimshanker Hills:</b></p> <p> Trek to Bhimashankar is considered as one the best treks in Sahyadri ranges and this time, you will be ascending via Shidi Ghat and descending via Ganesh Ghat to make it more interesting. The forest of Bhimashankar is a paradise for nature lovers, as it hosts several exotic species of wildlife and especially the rust-coloured giant squirrel  — the state animal of Maharashtra.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/3/e/c/600_454341484.jpeg\" /></p> <p>The area is surrounded by lofty peaks, dense forests and is also the source of River Bhima. There is also Bhimashankar Sanctuary where variety of birds, flowers and animals can be seen. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/4/c/d/600_454341709.jpeg\" /></p> <p>***  There are two established trekking trails between Khandas and Bhimashankar. The first of these trails is called \"Sidhi Ghat\". This route is named after the three ladders or Sidhi (in Hindi) that have been placed along some tricky sections on this trail.</p> <p>*** The second trail is known as \"Ganesh Ghat\", named after a temple dedicated to the Hindu deity Ganesha which falls on this route. Among the two alternative trekking trails, Ganesh Ghat is a longer yet less challenging route. However, what this trail lacks in difficulty, it makes up in some magnificent views of Bhimashankar\'s walls.</p> <p><b>Trek Via Khandas - SIDI GHAT:</b></p> <p>The route going to the left from the bridge goes to the village. The route to the left of the well in the village leads to the Shidi Ghat. This is one of the difficult routes to Bhimashankar. This route becomes very treacherous and slippery during the monsoon. There are three ladders in this route within the first two hours of climbing. One reaches a settlement after half an hour of the third ladder. This route is called \"Sidhi\" ghat because of ladder (Sidhi) placed on the routes.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/4/a/0/600_454341664.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/4/b/4/600_454341684.jpeg\" /></p> <p> Bhimashankar temple:-</p> <p><b>Bhimashankar Temple</b> is a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jyotirlinga\">Jyotirlinga</a> shrine located 50 km northwest of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khed_taluka\">Khed</a>, near <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pune\">Pune</a>, in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a>. It is located 127 km from Shivaji Nagar (Pune) in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ghats\">Ghat region</a> of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Ghats\">Sahyadri hills</a>. Bhimashankar is also the source of the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bhima_river\">river Bhima</a>, which flows southeast and merges with the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krishna_river\">Krishna river</a> near <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raichur\">Raichur</a>. </p> <p>                                             The Bhimashankara temple (one of 12 Jyotirlingas) is a composite of the old and the new structures, and is built using the Nagara style of architecture. It is a modest yet graceful temple and it dates back to mid-18th century. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/5/7/d/600_454341885.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/5/8/e/600_454341902.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Tentative Plan:</b></p> <p>• Day 1:</p> <p>• Start from Hyderabad to Pune - start to pune by 8:30 PM by Mumbai Express (17032) </p> <p>• Day 2:</p> <p>•  Reach Karjat by 11:30 and take public transport to base.</p> <p>•  Start trek to bhimshankar temple route via sidi ghat </p> <p>•  Reach the top and look for place to camp.</p> <p>• Day 3:</p> <p>•  Wake-Up early in the morning and get ready</p> <p>•  Visit the places and temple surroundings  </p> <p>• Pack up and then back to pune by bus and board a return train to hyd</p> <p>Day 4:</p> <p>• Reach back hyd early in the morning......</p> <p><b>COST: </b></p> <p>INR.Rs 2100/- approx. ball park figure per head which includes transport /camping/first aid/club fund/organiser\'s expense</p> <p>Please transfer the initial amount 1000/- to the below mentioned account details for confirmation of slot.</p> <p>Name : rohith eravalli <br/>Bank :kotak mahendra bank <br/>Branch : somagiguda <br/>Acc/no :9211678893 <br/>IFSC code : KKBK0000552</p> <p>Mention trek name for easy identification thank you....</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b></p> <p>1) No smoking and no alcohol </p> <p>2) No littering, no pollution of water </p> <p>3) This is not a luxury trip, but all care has been taken to make your trip comfortable.</p> <p>4) Ladies and gents accommodation is separate in tents. </p> <p>5) Food will be mostly vegetarian </p> <p>6) We carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers </p> <p>7) If you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately. </p> <p>8) If you can\'t swim don\'t go deep into the water </p> <p><b><i>Trekking outfit and things to bring: </i> </b></p> <p>1- Light colored/stretchable tracks. Carry only 2 excess pair  (Night wear + a pair for swimming ) anything additional will increase your Dead Load. </p> <p>2- Sleeping Bag: Please buy/borrow//beg if you don\'t have one. Basic model will be enough. In case you intend to suffer- Bring 2 blankets at least to wrap Yourself comfortably. </p> <p>3.  Rucksack .....  Make sure you pack all the things into one Backpack[including sleeping bag] + pack all your clothes in polythene covers so that they won’t get wet even when it drowns. ... YOU will have to carry 3 liters water. </p> <p>4- Torch: This is must ... please buy a good one, which gives you a sharp beam.</p> <p>5- Shoes: NEVER wear a new shoe on a hike, carry extra pair of <br/>socks.  Prefer Hiking Shoes over sport shoe which have strong-light rubber <br/>soles &amp; good ankle support+ 1 pair of slippers.</p> <p>6-Medicines: Bring personal medicines if you have any. The organizer will bring First Aid Kit. </p> <p>7-Identity &amp; Address proof; Preferably issued by GOI/GO Telangana  with <i>a xerox copy of it.</i></p> <p>7-Energy Food: Dates, Electrol /glucose/energy bars/chocolates etc... any snack for your new friends .. Must ..Must.. Must...;)</p> <p>8 Other things(Optional) Knife, Mirror, Towel, Brush &amp; Match box/lighter,..........You never know when u will have to stand against odds </p> <p>9- Two emergency notes with your name, address, emergency contact number.</p> <p>10: A camera for KODAK moments (optional), DSLR\'s welcome</p> <p>===&gt; Few things in between are not planned and these things are must in an adventure trek.</p> <p><b>Note : </b>Most of us may not be serious trekkers but all of us have equal responsibility in protecting our beloved earth. CLIMBON earnestly requests all its members to be socially responsible whilst the treks and avoid any littering, shouting when in wild or causing anything that would disturb the normal ecology. Try to avoid plastics as much as possible, especially plastic smiles.</p> <p>*** If u want an unique trekking experience then come and join CLIMBON in this monsoon will explore and find the hidden falls and BHIMSHANKAR HILLS...... </p> '),(598,'1478250609000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','235346802','1478362916000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235346802/','Event Host: Shiva 9866984814','2016-11-05 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-11-05 16:21:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 05:30PM - 9:00PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy 