 time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p><b><i>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </i></b><i> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</i></p> <p><i><b>What you need to bring along?</b></i></p> <p>1- Small bag (to keep your cloths and stuff)</p> <p>2- Towel</p> <p>3- Swimming costume (for boys swimming pool guys provide a shorts, but it is good to bring your own shorts; Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes)</p> <p>4- Swimming cap (optional)</p> <p>5- Swimming goggle (optional)</p> <p>6- Plastic pouch/bag to keep wet cloths</p> <p><b><i>Cost:</i></b></p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO; </b><b>Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges  paid to swimming pool guys</b>, which includes swimming costumes (for Boys).  As we would have been repeating this event very frequently (almost every week), you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(600,'1478406929000','Happy birthday ClimbOn','235387886','1478441791000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235387886/',NULL,'2016-11-06 10:30:00.000000','past','','','','',0,'2016-11-06 14:16:00.000000','<p>HAPPY BIRTHDAY CLIMBON</p> <p>I’m happy to celebrate our 2nd club anniversary with all of you. We couldn’t make so far without tremendous effort and enthusiasm from our Club Organizers and inexhaustible inspiration from our club members. In these two years we have achieved few important milestones. ClimbOn, which started with 3 members, now constitutes 2336 active participants and still growing. The club is now registered as an NGO under Telangana govt. which will allow us to organize events even in some restricted areas.  Our trust has now its own bank account, making all transactions related to events much easier. We were able to conduct events in various places from Himalayas region to Kanyakumari.  </p> <p>This year we are looking forward to organize more events in other parts of India, not touched so far including other countries like Bhutan, Europe to name a few. For that we need your continuous support and motivation. Let’s Climb on!!!!!</p> '),(601,'1478844050000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','235505871','1478967076000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235505871/','Event Host: Prudhvi- 9908023223','2016-11-12 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-11-12 16:1