ber of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 250 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Prudhvi - 9908023223</p> '),(602,'1474179656000','Devils Circuit - Get Ready for the ultimate obstacle Viking Run.','234211266','1479012290000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234211266/','Suman Climb On - 9966002025','2016-11-13 07:00:00.000000','past','Chilukur Road','Hyderabad','in','Aziz Nagar Village, Near APPA (AP Police Academy) ',0,'2016-11-13 04:44:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/e/d/2/600_454232466.jpeg\" /></p> <p>After a fantastic response at our previous edition in October 2015, we are once again bringing our premier obstacle running property, the Devils Circuit to Hyderabad on the 13th of November, Venue : Peddamangalaram Village Moinabad, Ranga Reddy, Telangana.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UEtBoYASwRA\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UEtBoYASwRA</a></p> <p>For the uninitiated however, Obstacle Running, as a format is quite different from the traditional formats of distance running, i.e. marathons, half-marathons, etc. &amp; essentially involves running across a challenging, rugged, outdoor track littered with military training - styled obstacles. Devils Circuit, in this context, is an amazingly unique experience for all its participants were Jumping over high walls, wading through a freezing pool of ice, crawling through muddy trenches underneath barbed wire &amp; much more; all around a custom-developed 5 km track is quite the norm. While promoting general fitness &amp; well-being, DC is also a great platform to promote team bonding among large groups &amp; organizations. Across its 6 previous editions, DC has attracted close to 15000 participants across age groups &amp; nationalities.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/f/1/b/600_454232539.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/f/4/1/600_454232577.jpeg\" /></p> <p>What to expect:</p> <p>· A 5 kms long running track interspersed with 15 cool challenging obstacles that allow for a unique fun filled team building opportunity</p> <p>· A 3000 sq mtrs of Expo Zone playing host to beach volleyball and football, Zumba, live performances, in house DJ, flash mobs, reebok Crossfit zone, Tug-of-war, Maruti Suzuki Swift fun Zone and a variety of other entertainment absolutely free</p> <p>· A free Goody bag at the bib collection which would include a Reebok play dry T-shirt, a cool DC bag, a headwrap and a variety of other goodies and discount coupons worth more than INR 4000/-</p> <p>· One free beer on the house for each participant included in the package.</p> <p>· A Chunky Devils Circuit Medal and digital certificate to all the participants who succeed to beat the Devil by completing the Run.</p> <p>· A fantastic day out with friends, family and colleagues. One spectator pass given absolutely free to each participant.</p> <p>· A range of food and cool merchandise to pick from.</p> <p>· Cool prizes like Reebok Spartan kits, GoPro cameras, Led TVs, B-Twin Cycles, lots of other stuff &amp; the Grand Prize of a Maruti Suzuki Swift.</p> <p>· Some really cool and crazy photographs of you while trying out the different obstacles. We will have 30+ photographers stationed across the Circuit.</p> <p>· Last but not the least an experience of a lifetime.</p> <p>We have across the 7 editions hosted in the past, had very positive feedback from all corporates who have participated as a group. Some of these include Infosys, HSBC, Wipro, McKinsey, IGATE, PWC, Pepsi, Amazon, Snapdeal, Metlife and a host of Embassies and consulates.</p> <p>Reference links from earlier editions showcasing the amazing DC experience are attached here for your reference.</p> <p><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RmxdW-jmjuw\" class=\"embedded\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RmxdW-jmjuw</a></p> <p>A truly international event.</p> <p>Charges: Non-Competitive - 2000 INR and Competitive - 3500 INR.</p> <p>Avail great discount of 25% if you are Climb-On Hyderabad member (it becomes Rs.1500).</p> <p>Reach me @ Suman 9966002025</p> <p>Join us : www.meetup/Theclimbon/</p> '),(603,'1477893121000','I RIDE WITH INDIA | Cycling | An attempt for Limca Book of World Record','235234103','1479012307000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235234103/','Please provide your name and number, Swaraj and Uday will add you to the whatsApp group','2016-11-13 07:00:00.000000','past','GACHIBOWLI, HYDERABAD','Hyderabad','in','BIO DIVERSITY PARK, ',0,'2016-11-13 04:45:00.000000','<p>ClimbOn is co-hosting \"<b>I Ride With India</b>\" an annual Pan India cycling event for 2016 in Hyderabad.  Last year \"I Ride With India\" event witnessed over 10,000 cyclists participated from 120 locations across India and the event was well covered in <a href=\"http://cyclingindia.in/media-coverage/\">media</a>. This time, its planned to be even bigger. This is going to be an attempt for the biggest cycling event (multiple venue). The attempt will be presented to <b>Limca Book of World Records</b>. We invite you to be a part of this mega event. Anyone can participate in this event.</p> <p><b><i>All the participants will receive digital certificates on successful participation. </i></b></p> <p><b>About the event: </b></p> <p>\"<b>I Ride With India</b>\" is an annual Pan India cycling event by Cycling India. On 13th Nov, 2016, All over the India, various cycling groups will conduct the cycling ride at 7:00 am simultaneously. </p> <p><a href=\"http://cyclingindia.in/i-ride-with-india-2016/\"><a href=\"http://cyclingindia.in/i-ride-with-india-2016/\" class=\"linkified\">http://cyclingindia.in/i-ride-with-india-2016/</a></a></p> <p><b>Facebook page for Hyderabad event:</b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1819399068282170/\"><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/events/1819399068282170/\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.facebook.com/events/1819399068282170/</a></a></b></p> <p><b>Event Charges:</b>  <b>There is no registration fee. </b></p> <p>For those who want to rent a bicycle from HBC Bike station Gachibowli, you would be asked to pay Rs. 50/ for 3 hours (and 100/- for first time registration; If you are already registered and have the slip or the card, you don\'t have to pay this). * Get a govt. photo ID card, because HBC will retain it and give it back after the cycle is handed over after the ride.</p> '),(604,'1474397052000','GOECHA LA TREK - a classic trek in beautiful state of Sikkim (himalayan range)..','234273340','1480175825000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234273340/','CLIMBON ROHITH - 9676722155','2016-11-18 14:00:00.000000','past','SIKKIM','Hyderabad','in','YUKSOM',0,'2016-11-26 15:57:00.000000','<p>• IMPORTANT NOTE:- Do RSVP, Join the waiting list, make the payment, once we receive your payment you will be moved into going list.</p> <p>• Trek Notes : Only for Ages 18+ and who are physically very fit.</p> <p>• Region                   :  gocha la, sikkim</p> <p>• Difficulty level      :  Moderate To Difficult </p> <p>• Trek Duration       :   8 Days </p> <p>• Max Altitude        :   16,200 Ft.(4938 mts)</p> <p>• Approx Trekking  : 90 Kms. </p> <p><b>GOECHA LA:-</b></p> <p>Goecha La (el. 4940 mt or 16,207 ft) is a high <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mountain_pass\">mountain pass</a> in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sikkim\">Sikkim</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/India\">India</a>n the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Himalaya\">Himalaya</a> range.</p> <p>                                   The southeast face of Mt. <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kanchenjunga\">Kanchenjunga</a>, the world\'s third highest mountain, can be viewed from the pass, which is also a base camp for those aspiring to scale the mountain.</p> <p>Gocha la Situated in the state of Sikkim, Goechala is a popular Himalayan trekking route and a perfect trekking destination for all adventure seekers. The magnificent view of the Himalayan valleys along with its unrivalled collection of flora and fauna that you would get as you travel along the <a href=\"http://www.himalayadestination.in/blog/index.php/2015/09/30/goechala-trek-route-experiences-shared-by-6-trekkers/\">Goechala trek map</a> is something that would stay engraved in your memories forever. Some of the peaks that you see during your trek are the Ratong, Yokhun and Kabru and all these really look pretty.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/9/a/8/600_454342952.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/a/6/f/600_454343151.jpeg\" /></p> <p>ABOUT GOECHA LA TREK ROUTE:-</p> <p>The beautiful trail of Goechala Trek has some of the key highlights which make the trip so stunning and spectacular among the trekking community.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/a/5/e/600_454343134.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Rich in beauty, the Gochala trek route is a treat for your senses. Do not forget to carry your DSLRs as Goechala trek as a lot to offer for your lenses. The trek begins from a place named Yuksom which is about 6hrs drive from Gangtok. Goechala trek route encompasses the Sachen pass and follows the Dzongri Goechala trek map.</p> <p>         You cross lush green meadows and opaque forests as you move towards your destination located about 90 km away. The trek usually takes around 8 days leaving your travelling time to and from Yuksom.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/a/2/8/600_454343080.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/a/8/2/600_454343170.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Cost: 16000 </p> <p>which includes:-</p> <p>** Transportation (NJP to Yuskom to NJP) </p> <p>** Accommodation during the trek (camping)</p> <p>** All meals - vegetarian (starting from dinner at Yuksom on day 1 and ending with breakfast at Yuksom on the day 10)</p> <p>** Trekking permits and forest camping charges Trekking equipment (tents, sleeping bags, ice axes, ropes, etc.)</p> <p>** Safety equipment (first aid, medical kit, oxygen cylinders, stretcher, etc.)</p> <p>** Services of an expert trek leader and team  (guides, cooks, helpers, porters/mules)</p> <p>Payment:-</p> <p>Advance payment to be made for INR 5000 to book your slot with the Vendors (non refundable) Remaining 11000 should be paid by bank transfer or liquid cash on or before trek</p> <p>pls transfer the above mentioned costs for confirmation of slots </p> <p>Name        : rohith eravalli <br/>Bank          :kotak mahendra bank <br/>Branch      : somagiguda <br/>Acc/no      :9211678893 <br/>IFSC code : KKBK0000552</p> <p>Tentative Itinerary (may vary):-</p> <p><b>Day 1: New Jalpaiguri (NJP) to Yuksom</b></p> <p>Altitude:1,780 m.</p> <p>* 150 km drive, approx 8 hours</p> <p>** On this day you have to report in Yuksom. Stay will be in Yuksom (starting point of trek)</p> <p><b>Day 2: Yuksom to Tshokha </b></p> <p>Altitude: 3050 m.</p> <p>12 kms trek, approx 7 hrs</p> <p><b>Day 3: Tsokha to Dzongri </b></p> <p>Altitude: 3956 m.</p> <p>10 kms trek, approx 8 hours</p> <p><b>Day 4: Dzongari to Thansing</b></p> <p>Altitude: 3800 m.</p> <p>8 kms trek, approx 6 - 8 hrs</p> <p><b>Day 5: Thansing to Lamuney </b></p> <p>Altitude: 4298 m. </p> <p>4 kms trek, approx 2 hours</p> <p><b>Day 6: Lamuney to Goechala</b><br/>(Trek depending on the trekkers’ speed/weather)<br/>Altitude: 4,984 m.<br/>18 kms trek, 13 hours</p> <p><b>Day 7: Lamuney   to Tsokha via Phedang</b></p> <p>Altitude: 3800 m.  approx 7 hours </p> <p><b>Day 8: Tsokha to Yuksom</b></p> <p>Altitude: 5670 ft.</p> <p>15 km trek, approx 6 hours </p> <p>THINGS TO BRING:-</p> <p>Bare necessities:-</p> <p>BASIC GEARS:-</p> <p>** Back pack &amp; rain cover             (50 - 60 ltr) with comfortable shoulder straps</p> <p>** Day pack + rain cover                20 - 30 ltr (If hire a mule or porter)</p> <p>** Walking stick Advisable             (At least one)</p> <p>** Head torch 1 Nos.                       (Hand torch would be an alternative)</p> <p>** Water bottle/Hydration pack                        </p> <p>                                                           2 bottles of one liter each People who use                                                                          hydration pack 1 hydration pack and 1 bottle of                                                                  one liter</p> <p>** Snacks                                          Energy bars, dry fruits, electral/ors</p> <p>** Personal Medical Kit                  Consult your doctor</p> <p>CLOTHES:-</p> <p>Be comfort at trek</p> <p>Be comfy at the trek</p> <p>** Trek pants                                    2 Synthetic (avoid shorts, fitting denims, capris)</p> <p>** T-shirts                                          2 Full sleeves (Non-cotton)</p> <p>** Fleece                                           T-shirts 1 Nos.</p> <p>** Fleece jacket                               1 Nos. (Alternative: a woolen sweater)</p> <p>** Down feather / Hollofil jacket   1 Nos.</p> <p>** Wind &amp; waterproof jacket &amp; pant</p> <p>                                                           1 Pair</p> <p>** Thermal inner                             1 Pair</p> <p>** Poncho                                         1 Nos.</p> <p>PERSONAL UTILITIES:-</p> <p>** Sunscreen cream</p> <p>** Hand sanitizer</p> <p>** Moisturizer</p> <p>** Antibacterial powder</p> <p>** Lip balm</p> <p>** Toothbrush and toothpaste</p> <p>** Toilet Paper &amp; wipes,Quick dry towel</p> <p>THINK ABOUT YOUR HEAD:-</p> <p>** Sun cap                                        1 Nos. (One that covers the neck as well)</p> <p>** Woolen cap                                 1 Nos.</p> <p>** Sunglasses                                  Dark with side cover, it should be U/V protected.</p> <p>MIND YOUR STEP:-</p> <p>**Trekking shoes                            1 Pair </p> <p>                                                          (Waterproof, high ankle with good grip)</p> <p>** Floaters/flip-flops                      1 Pair (Optional)</p> <p>** Cotton socks                              4 pairs</p> <p>** Woollen socks                            2 pairs</p> <p> Strictly No littering, No Smoking and Drinking  please co-operate with the organiser......</p> <p>For any other queries contact </p> <p>ROHITH - 9676722155</p> <p>Mail- rohith.deekshith9@gmail.com</p> '),(605,'1476466609000','Yay!!HORSE RIDING with ClimbOn - enjoy the ride. Saddle Up and get ready@ Nov 19','234859528','1479620859000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234859528/','Contact Event Host: Shiva 9866984814','2016-11-19 05:30:00.000000','past','Gachibowli','Hyderabad','in','Wipro Gate',0,'2016-11-20 05:47:00.000000','<p>Hello All,</p> <p>Are you passionate to learn Horse riding or just to see how it feels like???</p> <p>Here is an opportunity for all of you. Come discover one of the best riding opportunities with us.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/5/f/0/600_455070192.jpeg\" /></p> <p>This event is starting place for anyone with an interest in horses and riding, who wants to learn and have fun in a safe and caring environment. So here is an opportunity for all of you. Join us to share your experience. Horses are more friendly. Horse riding gives you adventure, physical fitness and a lifetime experience. It seems very easy but it’s a bonding between rider and the horse. To feel this relation, we have planned this event specially for riding lovers.</p> <p>Do not be intimidated by the whole \'horse riding\' thing. None of us are professionals, we are just trying to have fun while learning to Ride.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/5/f/9/600_455070201.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table :</b></p> <p>5:30 AM: Meet at Wipro Circle, Financial District, Nanakramguda.</p> <p>5:45 AM: Start to NASR Polo Club, Janwada.</p> <p>6:30 AM: Reach the club.</p> <p>6:45 AM: Introduction and Horse Riding tips by the Horse Riding Team</p> <p>7:00 AM: Horse Riding Starts.</p> <p>8:00 AM: Horse Riding Ends.</p> <p>8:15 AM: Tata Bye bye.</p> <p><b>Instructions:</b></p> <p>1) Jeans and T-Shirt with Collor (must)</p> <p><b>2) Weight limit: &lt; 100KG</b></p> <p>3) Experience Level: Beginners </p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b></p> <p>1) Water : 1 liter</p> <p>2) Camera to capture pics.[Optional]</p> <p>3) Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Mode of transport:</b> Bike/car. Please coordinate with other members for Bike/Car pooling, if required.</p> <p>Instructions: No shows are not encouraged. We will be booking the slots based on the RSVP\'s. So please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Cost: INR 600 per head.<br/></b></p> <p>This is a limited member event. So book your slot at the earliest by paying INR 500 in advance rest you can pay on the day of the event. You can transfer your amount to the below account.</p> <p>Name: T. Shiva Prasad Rao</p> <p>Bank: HDFC</p> <p>Account Number: 05211050315420</p> <p>IFSC Code: HDFC0000521</p> <p>BANJARA HILLS</p> <p>Need more information then please <b>Contact:</b> Shiva 9866984814</p> '),(606,'1479363017000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','235642108','1479575926000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235642108/','Event Host: Shiva 9-8-6-6-9-8-4-8-1-4','2016-11-19 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-11-19 17:18:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 05:30PM - 10:15PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/7/d/2/600_453858386.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/8/600_455051160.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/d/600_455051165.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/e/2/7/600_450876391.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/3/8/600_450999224.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>6.00: Game shuru</p> <p>10.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>10.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b>- Rs 200 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Shiva- 9866984814</p> '),(607,'1477145366000','Outdoor Yoga: Boost the flow of energy in your body and mind and stay fit','235039061','1480096031000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235039061/','SP Singh (93-90-33-69-92); Arvind (96-40-43-13-51);','2016-11-20 06:00:00.000000','past','kondapur','Hyderabad','in','Botanical Garden',0,'2016-11-25 17:47:00.000000','<p>Come and join ClimbOn’s lovely morning outdoor yoga session. Enjoy the open air, smell of the trees, hear birds’ chirps, connect with yourself, and sweat off toxins by having lovely morning with holistic body and mind uplifting through yoga workouts!  What can we have better than this to start a day?</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/d/7/600_455293527.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>About the Event Host:</b></p> <p>Event host is a corporate yoga trainer for past six years and has learnt yoga from Mysore, Rishikesh and many other yoga schools. He is  very passionate about Yoga and meditation.</p> <p><b><i>Who should join this yoga?</i></b></p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practiced with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b><i>What we are going to practice?</i></b></p> <p>We will practice various yogasanas starting with <b>loosening, warming up, balancing, strengthening, stretching, bending and followed by relaxation, pranayama and meditation</b>; also, practicing <b>traditional and modern sun salutation</b> (Suryanamaskar). Traditional sun salutation helps to balance and improve the functioning of different system related with earth/water/fire/air/space element whereas modern sun salutation will check our stamina/strength/flexibility. </p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/1/2/600_455293586.jpeghttps://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/f/0/600_455293552.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><i>Well known facts about Yoga:</i> </b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b><i>What you need to bring along?</i></b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat (alternatives are large bedsheet or towel)</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b><i>What is the club fund?</i></b></p> <p>No club fee for first two yoga sessions (you only need to pay park entry fee, which is Rs 15 to 20/person); third session onwards, club fee of Rs 100 is applicable, which includes park entry fee (Rs. 20).</p> <p>So, lets enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/2/b/600_455293611.jpeg\" /></p> '),(608,'1474177051000','Into the lap of nature, trek to beaches in Gokarna and Sathodi Falls Nov25-27','234210895','1480297919000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/234210895/','Contact Event Host:ClimbOn-Babu Reddy - 9966693964','2016-11-25 16:00:00.000000','past','KACHIGUDA RAILWAY STATION','Hyderabad','in','KACHIGUDA RAILWAY STATION',0,'2016-11-28 01:51:00.000000','<p>About: </p> <p><b>Gokarna: </b></p> <p>Gokarna is famous for its beautiful beaches and landscapes. The main beaches in Gokarna are the Gokarna beach, Kudle Beach, Om Beach, Half moon Beach and Paradise Beach (also known as Full moon). The Gokarna beach forms the coast of the town while the other four beaches lie to the south of Gokarna. Kudle and Om are around 6 km from Gokarna town along a muddy hill; they are accessible by rickshaw or foot. Half moon and Paradise are beyond Om beach and are accessible only by foot or boat. Om beach is named so because it is shaped like the auspicious ॐ [Om] symbol. Om beach is the only naturally Om shaped beach. Two other beaches - Paradise and Half Moon - are smaller and remote beaches. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/1/2/600_449499186.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Sathodi Falls:-</p> <p>The Sathodi Falls are formed by several streams near the Kallaramarane Ghat, 32 km from Yellapur. The falls are about 15 meters in height. After flowing from the waterfall the streams then flow into the backwaters of the Kodasalli Dam, into the Kali River. Owing to the picturesque view, the place is fondly called “Mini Niagara”. These falls form an integral part of the Ganeshgudi forest range.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/5/1/9/600_449301785.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Outline: </b></p> <p>Day 1 : Beach Trekking along the coastline from Gokarna Beach to Paradise Beach [ 12 km ]</p> <p>Day 2 : Sathodi Falls</p> <p><b>Iternary: </b></p> <p>Friday 4pm : Kacheguda train to Hubli </p> <p>Sat 8am : Hubli station to Gokarna. </p> <p>Sat 12pm : Lunch &amp; Beach Trek from Gokarna - Om beach - Half Moon - Paradise / Gokarna (12 km Approx) </p> <p>Sat 8pm : Stay in Gokarna [Accommodation is separate in tents for Men and woman] </p> <p> Sun 4am : Wakeup call </p> <p> Sun 5am : Gokarna to Sathodi Falls </p> <p> Sun 8am : Trekking in Sathodi falls and click some cool pics </p> <p>  Sun 4pm : Sathodi falls to Hubli. </p> <p> Sun 4pm: Catch train to Hyderabad. </p> <p> <b>Things to bring: - </b></p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts, at the beach, a pair of shorts would be a good. </p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. </p> <p>- Sleeping bag or thick blanket</p> <p> - Water : 2 litres must. please use reusable bottles.</p> <p> - Torch light with extra set of batteries. </p> <p> - A proper rucksack (backpack) to keep all of the above things </p> <p> - Camera to capture awesome places.[Optional]</p> <p> - Energy bars &amp; snacks to ClimbOn</p> <p><b>Important Instructions: </b></p> <p> Note: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, </p> <p><b>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. </b>Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.<b> This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable.</b> </p> <p><b> Damages: 2900/-</b> Ball park figure [Transport + Accommodation] Will share  the cost if it is more or less. [ Food is excluded]</p> <p>Please pay 1000/- as an advance payment to confirm your slot.</p> <p>Pay 1000/- in advance to confirm your slot.. Please find details below</p> <p>Nangi Babu Reddy</p> <p>036001542305</p> <p>ICICI BANK - ICIC0000360</p> <p>Electronic City Bangalore</p> <p>How to reach us</p> <p>ClimbOn Babu Reddy - +91-9966693964</p> '),(609,'1479704032000','Breakfast, chit-chat and a sweet 65k leisure cycling ride to shamshabad airport','235726397','1480575681000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235726397/','Call Swaraj','2016-11-26 05:30:00.000000','past','Hitech City Bike Station','Hyderabad','in','HBC Bike station at Gachibowli.',0,'2016-12-01 07:01:00.000000','<p>Join us for a leisure ride to Shamshabad airport. We will start from HBC bike station Gachibowli. You can rent a bicycle from the bike station for 50/- with a government issued id card. It is recommended that you bring spare change, water bottle and some snacks to eat.</p> <p><b>When </b>: Saturday,