 trees, hear birds’ chirps, connect with yourself, and sweat off toxins by having lovely morning with holistic body and mind uplifting through yoga workouts!   Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/5/d/5/600_456257877.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/d/7/600_455293527.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b>About the Event Host:</b></p> <p>Event host is a corporate yoga trainer for past six years and has learnt yoga from Mysore, Rishikesh and many other yoga schools. He is  very passionate about Yoga and meditation.</p> <p><b><i>Who should join this yoga?</i></b></p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practised with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b><i>What we are going to practice?</i></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashtanga_vinyasa_yoga\">Ashtanga Vinyasa Yoga</a></b>: in its traditional form, as taught by the late <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Pattabhi_Jois\">Sri. K. Pattabhi Jois</a>. – Today this is the practice that is most common around the world. Widely practised for strength,  stamina and fitness. <b>Also known as Mysore style of yoga.  </b>In Ashtanga vinyasa there are sun salutation A &amp;  B series, primary, intermediate and advance series of Asnas. As a beginner we will practice sun salutation A &amp; B, primary series of Asnas and finishing Asnas to have feel of asthanga vinyasa yoga. </p> <p><b>Sun salutation:</b> The sun salutation (Sūrya Namaskāra) forms the foundation of Aṣṭāṅga vinyasa practice. Here you will establish the calm rhythm of breathing (Ujjāyī) direction of Energy (Bandha) and concentration (Ḍṛṣti). The powerful flow of a moving meditation is born.  Primary series (Āsana) helps us to expel toxins and prepare body for advance practice . The dynamic of the sun salutations transform to new forms of movement. (Vinyāsa).  Asnas of primary series require power, flexibility and endurance. The finishing sequence guides the practitioner in Aṣṭāṅga Yoga to an energetic culmination. The breathing (Ujjāyī) calms down, muscle contractions (Bandha) become subtle and concentration (Ḍṛṣti) turns inward.</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/1/2/600_455293586.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/6/c/c/600_456258124.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b><i>Well known facts about Yoga:</i></b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b><i>What you need to bring along?</i></b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat (alternatives are large bedsheet or towel)</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b><i>What is the club fund?</i></b></p> <p>No club fee for these two yoga sessions (you only need to pay park entry fee, which is Rs 15 to 20/person); next session onward, a club fee of Rs. 100/session is applicable, which includes park entry fee, club maintenance and stationary fee etc.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/2/b/600_455293611.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pic from earlier event</i></p> '),(612,'1479835887000','ClimbOn Aqua Fitness - Swimming to tone up your body (For the Beginners also)','235759085','1480229383000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235759085/','Contact Event Hosts: Arvind (96-40-43-13-51) and Sthitha (87-62-74-99-06)','2016-11-27 10:45:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-11-27 06:49:00.000000','<p><b><i>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood.</i></b></p> <p>Benefits of Swimming</p> <p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p><b><i>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </i></b><i> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</i></p> <p><i><b>What you need to bring along?</b></i></p> <p>1- Small bag (to keep your cloths and stuff)</p> <p>2- Towel</p> <p>3- Swimming costume (for boys swimming pool guys provide a shorts, but it is good to bring your own shorts; Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes)</p> <p>4- Swimming cap (optional)</p> <p>5- Swimming goggle (optional)</p> <p>6- Plastic pouch/bag to keep wet cloths</p> <p><b><i>Cost:</i></b></p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO; </b><b>Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges  paid to swimming pool guys</b>, which includes swimming costumes (for Boys).  As we would have been repeating this event very frequently (almost every week), you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(613,'1480505788000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','235927845','1480782008000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235927845/','Event Host: Swaraj 7799228575','2016-12-03 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-12-03 16:20:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements