past','Opposite GMR Aero Towers, Rajiv Gandhi international airport, Shamshabad','Hyderabad','in','Decathlon Store',0,'2016-12-04 15:07:00.000000','<p>CimbOn Hyderabad together with Decathlon invites all the Cyclone enthusiasts of Hyderabad to one of the much awaited Trail Cycling event of 2016 in Hyderabad.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/4/8/0/600_456369344.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/3/e/4/600_456369188.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Participate to cycle among the best cyclists in the city in one of the most beautiful Cycling Trails nearby.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/3/0/8/600_456368968.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Prize worth Rs.20000 to be own (Separate for Men &amp; Women). Participation Certificate of all the participants .</p> <p>Note- Participants can carry their own cycles. Road bikes will not be allowed.</p> <p>Registration cost: Rs. 300</p> <p>Registration link:<a href=\"http://bit.ly/2gAgZd9\"><a href=\"http://bit.ly/2gAgZd9\" class=\"linkified\">http://bit.ly/2gAgZd9</a></a>. Once register done, share your transection ID with organisers.</p> <p>Refreshments and Cycles to be provided for those who do not own a cycle.</p> <p>T&amp;C:</p> <p>Age Limit-10+.</p> <p>We recommend that you arrive at least 20 minutes prior at the venue to pick up your physical tickets.</p> <p>Management is not responsible for the belongings.</p> '),(615,'1480857916000','Ride for a cause \"Donate blankets to homeless community\".....','236021688','1481135183000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236021688/',NULL,'2016-12-07 20:30:00.000000','past','Indinaragar Gachibowli','Hyderabad','in','gachi bowli - CCD',0,'2016-12-07 18:26:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/5/d/d/600_456570173.jpeg\" /></p> <p>ForU Foundation has organised \"Ride for a cause\" in collaboration with corporate sponsors and individuals to ride and donate blankets to homeless and add a smiling streak on their faces. NowFloats and many more have come forward to support the initiative \" Ride for a Cause\" in Hyderabad.</p> <p>You can also support this noble cause and spread warmth of love this winter.</p> <p>Register here...</p> <p><a href=\"https://in.explara.com/e/rideforacause\" class=\"linkified\">https://in.explara.com/e/rideforacause</a></p> '),(616,'1479706084000','Ride To Ananthagiri Hills & Kayaking At Kotepalli Reservoir','235726767','1481376118000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235726767/','Call your host, Uday@ 9666531565. Meeting point: Morine Bakery, Nanal Nagar Cross roads.','2016-12-10 05:30:00.000000','past','Vikarabad','Hyderabad','in','Anantagiri',0,'2016-12-10 13:21:00.000000','<p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/e/9/d/600_456260125.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Let\'s experience the cold fresh morning breeze and visit the place most explored for its scenic beauty.</p> <p>Warm up your bikes\' engines and get set to ride.</p> <p>Where are we going?<br/>Ananthagiri Hills &amp; Kotepalli Reservoir</p> <p>Who can come?<br/>Anybody who is 18 Years or older could participate.</p> <p>What are we visiting?<br/>1. Anantha Padmanabha Swamy Temple and some exploration behind woods in the temple.</p> <p>2. View point on the hill top.</p> <p>3. View point on the Ghat section.</p> <p>4. Kotepalli Reservoir and Kayaking in the reservoir.</p> <p>5. Haritha Resort and Swimming pool.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/e/e/6/600_456260198.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/f/3/7/600_456260279.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/f/6/0/600_456260320.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/f/f/e/600_456260478.jpeg\" /></p> <p>How long are we going to ride?<br/>80+80=160 Kms Approx. Overall</p> <p>Schedule:<br/>Not Applicable. This is a no time table event. We will ensure that we start and be back on time though.</p> <p>Any Mandates:<br/>Riders safety is our utmost priority, followed by ensuring memorable moments throughout the event.</p> <p>So here are some mandates:</p> <p>1. Both rider and pillion should wear helmets. Full or half face, is your discretion.</p> <p>2. Shoe and any kind of jacket or hoodie for rider is must.</p> <p>3. Rider should have a valid 2 wheeler Driving license and should carry the vehicle\'s Registration certificate.</p> <p>Insurance and Pollution certificates should also be carried. If you don\'t, you could still join. However, you will be on your own, if the law enforcement authorities question.</p> <p>Which class of vehicles can we get?</p> <p>All scooters and motorbikes above 100 CC.<br/>No cars.</p> <p>What are some of the things I should get?</p> <p>1. Enough cash.<br/>2. Back pack<br/>3. Extra pair of clothes for Kayaking and swimming. Clothes will get wet during Kayaking.<br/>For swimming get only sports wear. No cotton clothes allowed. You could rent a short though, at Haritha resort.<br/>4. A towel<br/>5. Cap and Shades.<br/>6. Camera and power bank</p> <p>Ride Sharing:<br/>WatsApp group will be created a week before the ride, to discuss ride sharing.</p> <p>What are the event charges?</p> <p>150/- Includes Event fee and Basic first aid.</p> <p>Food, Water, Parking, Swimming pool, Kayaking and fuel are excluded.</p> <p>Overall Estimation:<br/>300/- For Fuel (Not part of Event Charges)<br/>150/- For food and water (Not part of Event Charges)<br/>150/- For Event charges<br/>About 200 for Kayaking (Not part of Event Charges)<br/>100/- for Swimming Pool (Not part of Event Charges)</p> <p>Disclaimer: No stunting and rash driving.<br/>You will be oriented on road safety and riding instructions before starting the ride and every rider will have to abide by those safety instructions.</p> <p>ClimbOn Hyderabad and its organizers are not going to be responsible if you involve in those activities and if they result in any kind of damages either to the person or their properties. Please RSVP only if you accept this disclaimer.</p> '),(617,'1481030550000','Camping at Ananthagiri by Decathlon Hyderabad','236065900','1481439171000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236065900/','Meeting point is: Decathlon Shamshabad, Opp.to GMR Aero Towers, Near Passenger Terminal. Call your Host Diwakar (Decathlon): 9441222658/ Swaraj (ClimbOn SPOC): 7799228575 & Uday (ClimbOn SPOC): 9666531565 @ Time 10 AM','2016-12-10 10:00:00.000000','past','Telangana','Telangana','in','Ananthagiri Hills, Vikarabad',0,'2016-12-11 06:52:00.000000','<p><b>Could it get any better than spending a weekend night, camping a shore a lake, with a lot many people like you spreading the euphoria?</b></p> <p><b>We could take you through this thrilling experience on this weekend @ Ananthagiri Hills &amp; Kotepalli Reservoir.</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/4/e/b/600_456646315.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/4/f/0/600_456646320.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/4/f/9/600_456646329.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/4/f/f/600_456646335.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/5/0/1/600_456646337.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/b/5/0/7/600_456646343.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>So this is the Plan:</b></p> <p><b>Where are we camping:</b> Kotepalli Reservoir, Near Ananthagiri Hills.</p> <p><b>How long it is from Hyderabad:</b> Just 80 Kms</p> <p><b>What is the mode of transport: </b><br/>Transport will be arranged, Mini Bus From Decathlon Shamshabad (Includes in the event charges)</p> <p><b>What are we going to do after getting there:</b><br/><b>Day 1 10th Dec\'16 Saturday</b></p> <p>1000 AM-Meeting at Decathlon Shamshabad<br/>1045 AM- Start to Ananthagiri Hills<br/>0100 PM- Lunch At Ananthagiri (Self Paid)</p> <p>03:00 PM- Reach the Camping Spot</p> <p><b>Activities: </b><br/>Exploration around Kotepalli reservoir<br/>Kayaking (Includes in the event charges)<br/>Fishing (Optional, if you have the equipment)</p> <p>0600 PM- Start pitching the tents (One of the things you would love to do)<br/>0800 PM- Dinner (Veg) (Includes in the event charges)<br/>1100 PM- Star gaze and fall asleep in the silence around the lake</p> <p><b>Day 2 11th Dec\'16 Sunday</b></p> <p>0500 AM- Waking up (One of the best mornings. Waking up in the midst of nowhere)<br/>0630 AM Hiking &amp; kayaking in the lake (Includes in the event charges)<br/>0800 AM Refreshments (Includes in the event charges)<br/>0930 AM Start back to Ananthagiri from the camping spot</p> <p>1100 AM Return to Hyderabad (Transportation includes in the event charges)</p> <p><b>What should I get:</b><br/>1. 2 Water Bottles<br/>2. Extra snacks to munch on<br/>3. Hiking Shoes or Sports Shoes<br/>4. Track Pants, T Shirts and Apparel to protect yourself from Cold weather<br/>5. Swim Shorts and Exra pair of undergarments<br/>6. Toiletries (Tooth Brush, Soap, Shampoo, Hand Wash, Sanitizers, Tissues etc)<br/>7. Sleeping Bag if you have or a Blanket thick enough.<br/>8. Sunglasses, Cap<br/>9. Power Bank<br/>10. Back Pack to store your stuff<br/>11. Medicines you might be using already.<br/>12. Some extra cash, just in case you would need</p> <p><b>Important Instructions:<br/></b>1. No Alcohol consumption and No Smoking from the time the event begins and until it ends.<br/>2. Organizer\'s will take a final call if there is an extremely important decision to be taken.<br/>3. No littering at all.<br/>4. Stay with the group and keep the organizer informed if you want to step out for a moment. Extremely remote and peaceful place. It is safe only if you have someone with you, who has the expertise.</p> <p><b>Event charges:</b><br/>Only 999/-</p> <p><b>Includes-Transportation from Hyd-Ananthagiri-Hyderabad<br/>Food- Dinner on Day 1 and Refreshments on Day 2 in the morning<br/>Kayaking Charges<br/>Camping equipment and expertise.</p> <p>Hurry up!!! Only a few Slots are available..</p> <p>Payment link will be updated shortly. Go ahead and book your slot. Get your friends and family too.</p> <p></b></p> '),(618,'1481092663000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','236086203','1481389910000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236086203/','Event Host: Shiva 9-8-6-6-9-8-4-8-1-4','2016-12-10 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2016-12-10 17:11:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 05:30PM - 10:15PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/7/d/2/600_453858386.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/8/600_455051160.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/d/600_455051165.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/e/2/7/600_450876391.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/3/8/600_450999224.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table : </b></p> <p>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>6.00: Game shuru</p> <p>10.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>10.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring: </b></p> <p><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b></p> <p>- Rs 200 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Shiva- 9866984814</p> '),(619,'1480088682000','ClimbOn Fitness: Ashtanga vinyasa yoga including various forms of Sun salutation','lghpgmyvqbmb','1481424529000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/lghpgmyvqbmb/','SP Singh (93-90-33-69-92); Arvind (96-40-43-13-51);','2016-12-11 06:00:00.000000','past','kondapur','Hyderabad','in','Botanical Garden',0,'2016-12-11 02:48:00.000000','<p>Come and join ClimbOn’s lovely morning outdoor yoga sessions. Enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Enjoy the open air, smell of the trees, hear birds’ chirps, connect with yourself, and sweat off toxins by having lovely morning with holistic body and mind uplifting through yoga workouts!   Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/5/d/5/600_456257877.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/d/7/600_455293527.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b>About the Event Host:</b></p> <p>Event host is a corporate yoga trainer for past six years and has learnt yoga from Mysore, Rishikesh and many other yoga schools. He is  very passionate about Yoga and meditation.</p> <p><b><i>Who should join this yoga?</i></b></p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practised with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b><i>What we are going to practice?</i></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashtanga_vinyasa_yoga\">Ashtanga Vinyasa Yoga</a></b>: in its traditional form, as taught by the late <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Pattabhi_Jois\">Sri. K. Pattabhi Jois</a>. – Today this is the practice that is most common around the world. Widely practised for strength,  stamina and fitness. <b>Also known as Mysore style of yoga.  </b>In Ashtanga vinyasa there are sun salutation A &amp;  B series, primary, intermediate and advance series of Asnas. As a beginner we will practice sun salutation A &amp; B, primary series of Asnas and finishing Asnas to have feel of asthanga vinyasa yoga. </p> <p><b>Sun salutation:</b> The sun salutation (Sūrya Namaskāra) forms the foundation of Aṣṭāṅga vinyasa practice. Here you will establish the calm rhythm of breathing (Ujjāyī) direction of Energy (Bandha) and concentration (Ḍṛṣti). The powerful flow of a moving meditation is born.  Primary series (Āsana) helps us to expel toxins and prepare body for advance practice . The dynamic of the sun salutations transform to new forms of movement. (Vinyāsa).  Asnas of primary series require power, flexibility and endurance. The finishing sequence guides the practitioner in Aṣṭāṅga Yoga to an energetic culmination. The breathing (Ujjāyī) calms down, muscle contractions (Bandha) become subtle and concentration (Ḍṛṣti) turns inward.</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/1/2/600_455293586.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/6/c/c/600_456258124.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b><i>Well known facts about Yoga:</i></b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b><i>What you need to bring along?</i></b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat (alternatives are large bedsheet or towel)</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b><i>What is the club fund?</i></b></p> <p>A club fee of Rs. 100/session is applicable, which includes participants\' park entry fee, and club maintenance, fuel charges, and stationary fee etc.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/2/b/600_455293611.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pic from earlier event</i></p> '),(620,'1480088965000','ClimbOn Aqua Fitness - Swimming to tone up your body (For the Beginners also)','235820669','1481439211000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235820669/','Contact Event Hosts: Arvind and Jagdish','2016-12-11 10:45:00.000000','past','Opposite RTO Office  Raghavendra Colony, Kondapur Beside Kritunga Restaurant','Kondapur','in','Seasons Swimming Pool ',0,'2016-12-11 06:53:00.000000','<p><b><i>You are just one swim away from a healthy life and  a good mood.</i></b></p> <p>Benefits of Swimming</p> <p>Did you know that even a gentle swim can burn over 200 Kcal in half an hour and a fast front crawl can burn as many calories as an 8mph run? </p> <p>Exercise at a slower pace for extended periods of time. You\'ll burn more fat if you slow your speed and swim for at least 30 minutes. When you exercise at lower intensities, you burn higher percentages of fat calories.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/4/600_447778452.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>7 Reasons for Swimming: </b>Heart Helper, Balance Your Build, increasing muscle strength, Increased Flexibility, Strengthen Your Core, Endurance, Weight Loss.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/e/4/5/f/600_447778463.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Swimming pools provide a great way to accomplish some aerobic exercise when it’s too hot to even think about jogging or playing a land sport. <b>Swimming provides a total body workout that exercises your arms, legs, and torso. If you’re new to exercise, swimming is a great choice because it’s low impact, fun, and a good way to get in a great workout without actually feeling like you’re working out – you’ll feel like you’re cooling down. </b></p> <p>Lets catch up for an hour long swimming meetup at Kondapur. </p> <p><b><i>People who are new to swimming can also join. We will provide you the basic training. </i></b><i> Depth of the pool ranges from 3 Ft to 7 Ft.</i></p> <p><i><b>What you need to bring along?</b></i></p> <p>1- Small bag (to keep your cloths and stuff)</p> <p>2- Towel</p> <p>3- Swimming costume (for boys swimming pool guys provide a shorts, but it is good to bring your own shorts; Girls need to bring their own swimming  costumes)</p> <p>4- Swimming cap (optional)</p> <p>5- Swimming goggle (optional)</p> <p>6- Plastic pouch/bag to keep wet cloths</p> <p><b><i>Cost:</i></b></p> <p><b>CLUB FUND: ZERO; </b><b>Rs. 150/hr Swimming Charges  paid to swimming pool guys</b>, which includes swimming costumes (for Boys).  As we would have been repeating this event very frequently (almost every week), you may go for weekend Registration to that indoor swimming pool (1200/month for weekends; including Holidays)</p> <p><b>Follow us on:  </b></p> <p>Meetup: <a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/Facebook:\"><a href=\"http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/</a></a></p> <p>Facebook: <a href=\"http://www.fb.com/climbonhikerYoutube:\">www.fb.com/climbonhiker</a></p> <p>youtube:  <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg\">www.youtube.com/channel/UCyC11AYYd3ZebzDWAqXVgHg</a></p> '),(621,'1477467736000','Experience unparalleled adventure of lifetime:Into Exhilarating world of Corals','235121790','1482520896000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235121790/','ClimbOn Babu Reddy 9966693964','2016-12-16 21:00:00.000000','past','Malvan','Maharastra','in','Tarkarli',0,'2016-12-23 19:21:00.000000','<p><b>About Place</b>:</p> <p><b>Tarkarli</b> is a village in <b>Malvan</b> taluka in Sindhudurg district, the southernmost district of Maharashtra State, India. It is well known for the historically important Sindhudurg Fort. It is tourist destination and a coral beach.</p> <p>Tarkarli beach has a long coastline and clear waters. Located at the confluence of the Karli River and the Arabian Sea, This place has gained prominence because of its long and narrow stretch of beach with pristine waters and water sports.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/2/b/6/600_449597078.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/2/9/e/600_449597054.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Scuba Diving</b>:</p> <p>Scuba diving is a form of underwater diving in which a diver uses a self contained underwater breathing apparatus (scuba) to breathe underwater.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/2/e/9/600_449597129.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Parasailing</b>:</p> <p>The harness attaches the pilot to the parasail, which is connected to the boat, or land vehicle, by the tow rope. The vehicle then drives off, carrying the parascender (or wing) and person into the air. The activity is primarily a fun ride, not to be confused with the sport of paragliding.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/2/8/600_449597192.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Jetski</b>:</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/8/0/600_449597280.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Other water sports</b>:</p> <p>• Banana ride</p> <p>• Bumper ride</p> <p>• Speed boat </p> <p>• Water scooter</p> <p><b>Itinerary :</b></p> <p><b>Day 0</b>:</p> <p><b>Friday</b> Board bus to Belgaum at 9pm</p> <p><b>Day 1</b>:</p> <p>07:00 : Reach Belgaum and board pre booked vehicle</p> <p>11:00: Reach Malvan</p> <p>12.00 : Start roamingand will cover attractions in Malvan</p> <p>18:00 : Spend time at beach</p> <p>21:00 : Dinner and Night Beach Camping</p> <p><b>Beach Camping</b>:</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/4/c/9/600_449597609.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Day 2</b>:</p> <p>06:00 : Wake up and get fresh</p> <p>07:00 : Breakfast</p> <p>09:00 : Scuba diving and watersports</p> <p>13:00 : Lunch </p> <p>15:00 : Start to Belgaum</p> <p>19:00 : Dinner and Start back to Hyderabad</p> <p><b>Day 3</b>:</p> <p>Reach Hyderabad by 7 A.M</p> <p>Tata, Bubye :)</p> <p><b>Things to bring</b>:</p> <p>- Couple of Track pants or shorts, T-shirts, at the beach, a pair of shorts would be a good.</p> <p>- Trekking shoes or sports shoes, 2 extra pair of socks. - Sleeping bag or thick blanket and a proper rucksack (backpack) (both are must) and some plastic covers</p> <p>- Some snacks to climb on.</p> <p>- Torch light is must.</p> <p>- Water 1-2 liters</p> <p><b>Cost :</b> Rs. 5500/-  includes <b>Scuba diving</b>, <b>Parasailing</b>, other water sports, <b>transportation</b> and club fee. (own expense for food )</p> <p><b>Bank Details</b>:</p> <p>Bank name              :    ICICI bank ltd.<br/>Account Name       :    Nangi Babu Reddy<br/>Account number   :    036001542305<br/>IFSC Code              :     ICIC0000360</p> <p><b>P.S: Please pay a minimum amount of Rs.1500/- to confirm your slot. If you are paying full amount, it is highly appreciated. </b></p> <p><b>Contact :</b></p> <p>ClimbOn Babu Reddy 9966693964</p> '),(622,'1481360497000','Parkour basics by an American Parkour Certified Coach Sreeramachandra','236154565','1481942879000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236154565/','ClimbOn Suman 9966002025','2016-12-17 05:30:00.000000','past','Lower Tankbund','Hyderabad','in','Indira Park',0,'2016-12-17 02:47:00.000000','<p>Parkour is the activity/sport of moving rapidly through an area, typically in an urban environment, negotiating obstacles by running, jumping, and climbing. The art which helps you to explore your mind, body and spirit and helps you become your best version.</p> <p>This meetup is for all the enthusiasts belonging to all age groups (5-50 years) who have been waiting to get started with the natural art of overcoming obstacles in the most creative and fun filled way. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/5/a/600_447966746.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/2/5/600_447966693.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Sreeramachandra Modukuru is an American Parkour Certified Coach, Professional Parkour Athlete, Official Trainer of the Paramilitary Forces (CISF) and a Fitness Freak. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/3/8/600_447966712.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Links to Sreeramachandra\'s Parkour/Freerunning: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Us_DODpziS0\">Video 1</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iXOUQR0Yuhw\">Video 2</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fiTCHoD0pLg\">Video 3</a></p> <p><b>Itinerary :</b></p> <p>05:30 : Assemble at Meeting Point - Indra Park<br/>05:45 : Little warm up <br/>06:00 : Start of the event <br/>08:00 : End of the event<br/>08:10  : Tata, bye bye</p> <p><b>What to Wear :</b> </p> <p>• Tee shirt - prefer full sleeves</p> <p>• Tracks / Shorts  ( No jeans please ) </p> <p>• Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>• Water 1-2 liters</p> <p><b>Cost :</b> Rs. 100/- as club fee.</p> <p><b>Contact :</b></p> <p>ClimbOn Suman 9966002025</p> '),(623,'1478514217000','Night camping Beside Lake @ Pocharam Forest 17th Dec','235411845','1482078731000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/235411845/','Event Host: Shiva 9-8-6-6-9-8-4-8-1-4','2016-12-17 13:00:00.000000','past','Balanagar','Hyderabad','in','Balanagar X Roads',0,'2016-12-18 16:32:00.000000','<p>Pocharam lake is located in Medak district in the Indian state of Telangana. It is adjacent to Pocharam Forest &amp; Wildlife Sanctuary.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/4/d/600_442416685.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/1/0/1/600_442533025.jpeg\" /></p> <p>15 KM from Medak is Pocharam Lake with a dam, and Pocharam Wildlife sanctuary which used to be a hunting ground for the Nizam.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/6/f/600_442416719.jpeg\" /></p> <p>We would also be exploring the Medak Fort which is a citadel built on a hillock that provided as a vantage point for the Kakatiyan rulers in ancient India.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/f/9/1/600_442416753.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Date:</b> On Sat 17th 1p.m to Sun 18th 11 a.m 1D/1N.</p> <p><b>Participate:</b> Book your slot and make the payment in adavance.</p> <p><b>Distance: </b>110kms away from (3hrs drive)</p> <p><b>Meetup Point:</b> Balanagar X roads, <b>Self transport</b>.</p> <p><b>Program Experiences: </b>Night Camping, Star gazing,</p> <p>a. Night camping</p> <p>b. Trekking.</p> <p>c. Bon-fire.</p> <p>d. Stargazing</p> <p>e. Haunted stories</p> <p>f. Fort Visit</p> <p>Plus Nature &amp; fun things to do.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b><br/>1. A pair of extra clothes if you go for swim. (optional)<br/>2. Sports shoes.<br/>3. Torch with extra batteries,<br/>4. Sleeping bag or just a blanket, and 2 ltr water bottle.<br/>5. Caps/Raincoats(optional)<br/>6. A bag to carry all the above.</p> <p><b>Itinerary: </b><br/>Day 1 After reaching by 5pm, Roam Around, bon-fire with camping, Dinner.<br/>Day 2 Morning we start the day lake trek enjoying the view and fun activities.</p> <p><b>Tariff: </b>Rs.<b>600(Dinner Included)</b> per head - Limited seats only<br/>Includes:<br/>a. Camping gears (Tents etc..)<br/>b. Activities.</p> <p>This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care will be taken to make your trip comfortable.</p> <p>You can make payments to the below Account:</p> <p>Name: T. Shiva Prasad Rao</p> <p>Bank: HDFC</p> <p>Account Number: 05211050315420</p> <p>IFSC Code: HDFC0000521</p> <p>BANJARA HILLS</p> <p><b>Note: </b></p> <p><i>No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from Start to end of the event, Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. Its just all about having fun.</i></p> <p>Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm.</p> <p><i><b>Direct numbers :</b>  Shiva: 9866984814<br/></i></p> '),(624,'1480088682000','ClimbOn Fitness: Ashtanga vinyasa yoga including various forms of Sun salutation','lghpgmyvqbhc','1482029333000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/lghpgmyvqbhc/','SP Singh (93-90-33-69-92); Arvind (96-40-43-13-51);','2016-12-18 06:00:00.000000','past','kondapur','Hyderabad','in','Botanical Garden',0,'2016-12-18 02:48:00.000000','<p>Come and join ClimbOn’s lovely morning outdoor yoga sessions. Enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Enjoy the open air, smell of the trees, hear birds’ chirps, connect with yourself, and sweat off toxins by having lovely morning with holistic body and mind uplifting through yoga workouts!   Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/5/d/5/600_456257877.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/d/7/600_455293527.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b>About the Event Host:</b></p> <p>Event host is a corporate yoga trainer for past six years and has learnt yoga from Mysore, Rishikesh and many other yoga schools. He is  very passionate about Yoga and meditation.</p> <p><b><i>Who should join this yoga?</i></b></p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practised with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b><i>What we are going to practice?</i></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashtanga_vinyasa_yoga\">Ashtanga Vinyasa Yoga</a></b>: in its traditional form, as taught by the late <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Pattabhi_Jois\">Sri. K. Pattabhi Jois</a>. – Today this is the practice that is most common around the world. Widely practised for strength,  stamina and fitness. <b>Also known as Mysore style of yoga.  </b>In Ashtanga vinyasa there are sun salutation A &amp;  B series, primary, intermediate and advance series of Asnas. As a beginner we will practice sun salutation A &amp; B, primary series of Asnas and finishing Asnas to have feel of asthanga vinyasa yoga. </p> <p><b>Sun salutation:</b> The sun salutation (Sūrya Namaskāra) forms the foundation of Aṣṭāṅga vinyasa practice. Here you will establish the calm rhythm of breathing (Ujjāyī) direction of Energy (Bandha) and concentration (Ḍṛṣti). The powerful flow of a moving meditation is born.  Primary series (Āsana) helps us to expel toxins and prepare body for advance practice . The dynamic of the sun salutations transform to new forms of movement. (Vinyāsa).  Asnas of primary series require power, flexibility and endurance. The finishing sequence guides the practitioner in Aṣṭāṅga Yoga to an energetic culmination. The breathing (Ujjāyī) calms down, muscle contractions (Bandha) become subtle and concentration (Ḍṛṣti) turns inward.</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/1/2/600_455293586.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/6/c/c/600_456258124.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b><i>Well known facts about Yoga:</i></b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b><i>What you need to bring along?</i></b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat (alternatives are large bedsheet or towel)</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b><i>What is the club fund?</i></b></p> <p>A club fee of Rs. 100/session is applicable, which includes participants\' park entry fee, and club maintenance, fuel charges, and stationary fee etc.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/2/b/600_455293611.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pic from earlier event</i></p> '),(625,'1481722853000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','236235153','1482080917000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236235153/','Event Host: Shiva 9-8-6-6-9-8-4-8-1-4','2016-12-18 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, A