tic.com/photos/event/8/e/2/7/600_450876391.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/3/8/600_450999224.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table :</b><br/>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>6.00: Game shuru</p> <p>10.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>10.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b><br/><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b></p> <p>- Rs 200 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Shiva- 9866984814</p> '),(632,'1480088682000','ClimbOn Fitness: Ashtanga vinyasa yoga including various forms of Sun salutation','lghpgmyvqbpb','1483844327000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/lghpgmyvqbpb/','SP Singh (93-90-33-69-92); Arvind (96-40-43-13-51);','2017-01-08 06:00:00.000000','past','kondapur','Hyderabad','in','Botanical Garden',0,'2017-01-08 02:58:00.000000','<p>Come and join ClimbOn’s lovely morning outdoor yoga sessions. Enjoy a morning under the rising sun and breath through the practice of yoga. Enjoy the open air, smell of the trees, hear birds’ chirps, connect with yourself, and sweat off toxins by having lovely morning with holistic body and mind uplifting through yoga workouts!   Let go off your stress and anxiety and discover your inner strength.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/5/d/5/600_456257877.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/4/d/7/600_455293527.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b>About the Event Host:</b></p> <p>Event host is a corporate yoga trainer for past six years and has learnt yoga from Mysore, Rishikesh and many other yoga schools. He is  very passionate about Yoga and meditation.</p> <p><b><i>Who should join this yoga?</i></b></p> <p><i>Sessions are open to all, so bring your spouse, kids, parents, friends, neighbours along and let them experience the benefits of Yoga practised with ClimbOn.</i> </p> <p><b><i>What we are going to practice?</i></b></p> <p><b><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ashtanga_vinyasa_yoga\">Ashtanga Vinyasa Yoga</a></b>: in its traditional form, as taught by the late <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Pattabhi_Jois\">Sri. K. Pattabhi Jois</a>. – Today this is the practice that is most common around the world. Widely practised for strength,  stamina and fitness. <b>Also known as Mysore style of yoga.  </b>In Ashtanga vinyasa there are sun salutation A &amp;  B series, primary, intermediate and advance series of Asnas. As a beginner we will practice sun salutation A &amp; B, primary series of Asnas and finishing Asnas to have feel of asthanga vinyasa yoga. </p> <p><b>Sun salutation:</b> The sun salutation (Sūrya Namaskāra) forms the foundation of Aṣṭāṅga vinyasa practice. Here you will establish the calm rhythm of breathing (Ujjāyī) direction of Energy (Bandha) and concentration (Ḍṛṣti). The powerful flow of a moving meditation is born.  Primary series (Āsana) helps us to expel toxins and prepare body for advance practice . The dynamic of the sun salutations transform to new forms of movement. (Vinyāsa).  Asnas of primary series require power, flexibility and endurance. The finishing sequence guides the practitioner in Aṣṭāṅga Yoga to an energetic culmination. The breathing (Ujjāyī) calms down, muscle contractions (Bandha) become subtle and concentration (Ḍṛṣti) turns inward.</p> <p><i>*Please note that there would be some variation to what is mentioned above and that depends on the level of practice, no of sessions, and time</i> .</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/1/2/600_455293586.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/6/c/c/600_456258124.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pics from earlier events</i></p> <p><b><i>Well known facts about Yoga:</i></b></p> <p><b>YOGA is one of the best ways to stay fit and physical benefits of yoga include:</b> </p> <p>• Increased flexibility.  </p> <p>• Increased muscle strength and tone.</p> <p>• Improved respiration, energy level and vitality. </p> <p>• Maintaining a balanced metabolism. </p> <p>• Weight reduction. </p> <p>• Cardio and circulatory health.</p> <p>• Improved eye sight.</p> <p><b><i>What you need to bring along?</i></b></p> <p>• Bring a yoga mat (alternatives are large bedsheet or towel)</p> <p>• Wear loose comfortable clothing</p> <p>• Suggest not to eat 2 hours prior to yoga event or 1 hour if it is a light snack.</p> <p><b><i>What is the club fund?</i></b></p> <p>A club fee of Rs. 100/session is applicable, which includes participants\' park entry fee, and club maintenance, fuel charges, and stationary fee etc.</p> <p>Event hosts are looking forward to meeting you soon!</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/3/5/2/b/600_455293611.jpeg\" /></p> <p><i>*Pic from earlier event</i></p> '),(633,'1482404013000','Exploration trip to Mysterious Island','236395199','1484412517000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236395199/','ClimbOn Sandeep - 800 800 4360','2017-01-14 05:00:00.000000','past','Gowliguda','Hyderabad','in','MGBS Bus station',0,'2017-01-14 16:48:00.000000','<p><b>Type  : </b>Exploration </p> <p><b>Team Size</b>  : 4 - 5 </p> <p><b>Who can register</b> : Only for members who have prior Exploration experience</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/b/8/4/600_457051620.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/b/8/8/600_457051624.jpeg\" /></p> <p>We will travel by our own vehicles.</p> <p><b>Damages</b>: We are going by own vehi