/b> <a href=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/DcC9W7qiik7BGIgpaLdETc\"><a href=\"https://chat.whatsapp.com/DcC9W7qiik7BGIgpaLdETc\" class=\"linkified\">https://chat.whatsapp.com/DcC9W7qiik7BGIgpaLdETc</a></a></p> '),(636,'1483583456000','Parkour basics by an American Parkour Certified Coach Sreeramachandra','236686302','1485015095000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236686302/','ClimbOn Suman 9966002025','2017-01-21 06:00:00.000000','past','Lower Tankbund','Hyderabad','in','Indira Park',0,'2017-01-21 16:11:00.000000','<p>Parkour is the activity/sport of moving rapidly through an area, typically in an urban environment, negotiating obstacles by running, jumping, and climbing. The art which helps you to explore your mind, body and spirit and helps you become your best version.</p> <p>This meetup is for all the enthusiasts belonging to all age groups (5-50 years) who have been waiting to get started with the natural art of overcoming obstacles in the most creative and fun filled way. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/5/a/600_447966746.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/2/5/600_447966693.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Sreeramachandra Modukuru is an American Parkour Certified Coach, Professional Parkour Athlete, Official Trainer of the Paramilitary Forces (CISF) and a Fitness Freak. </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/1/a/3/8/600_447966712.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Links to Sreeramachandra\'s Parkour/Freerunning: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Us_DODpziS0\">Video 1</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iXOUQR0Yuhw\">Video 2</a> <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fiTCHoD0pLg\">Video 3</a></p> <p><b>Itinerary :</b></p> <p>06:00 : Assemble at Meeting Point - Indra Park<br/>06:05 : Little warm up <br/>06:10 : Start of the event <br/>08:00 : End of the event<br/>08:10  : Tata, bye bye</p> <p><b>What to Wear :</b> </p> <p>• Tee shirt - prefer full sleeves</p> <p>• Tracks / Shorts  ( No jeans please ) </p> <p>• Shoes are a MUST</p> <p>• Water 1-2 liters</p> <p><b>Cost :</b> Rs. 100/- as club fee. <b><i>Please do not RSVP if you not sure to attend</i></b>.</p> <p><b>Contact :</b></p> <p>ClimbOn Suman 9966002025</p> '),(637,'1484227223000','Ride to Historical Bhongir Fort and Hike','236871925','1485056297000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236871925/','Contact Event Host: Shiva 9866984814','2017-01-21 06:00:00.000000','past','Uppal','Hyderabad','in','Uppal cross roads',0,'2017-01-22 03:38:00.000000','<p><b>About Place: </b>Bhongir or Bhongiri or Bhuvanagiri is a small town about 40km from uppal Hyderabad on the way to Warangal. The fort is on top of a small hill - in fact the hill is a monolith - a huge rock. The surrounding areas being flat, the hill affords a grand view of the vistas beyond.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/5/b/3/1/600_431903345.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/6/c/2/600_433110402.jpeg\" /></p> <p>What do we plan to do :Hiking, Fort climbing and collecting memories that will last a lifetime</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/7/0/7/600_433110471.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/f/5/b/600_446532123.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/7/7/1/5/600_433110485.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p>6:00am: Meetup at Uppal X Road (near Uppal Police Station) Start towards Bhongir</p> <p>7:00 Reach Bhongir and start climbing<br/>8:00 Reach hill top with an magnificent overview of horizon<br/>11:30 Start descending down.<br/>12:00 Start back to Hyderabad</p> <p><b>What to wear:</b></p> <p>Wear Shoes with \"lots\" of grip.</p> <p>• Wear anything comfortable, preferably tracks and tees.</p> <p>• As we will be starting early, wear something to keep you warm.</p> <p>• What to bring:</p> <p>• Water bottles - 2 x 1 litres</p> <p>• Hat or cap as it will be hot afternoons</p> <p>• Electrol or glucose</p> <p>• Camera</p> <p>• Any medications physician prescribed</p> <p>• Loads of energy.</p> <p><b>Costs </b>: Rs 120 Towards Club fund + Entrance Fee</p> <p><b>Guidelines</b>: This is a historical place . No venturing towards steep cliff drops .</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Shiva: 9-8-6-6-9-8-4-8-1-4</p> <p><b>Difficulty </b>: Easy</p> <p>Transport: Personal Vehicles If possible there will be pool and petrol cost will be shared</p> '),(638,'1484742548000','ClimbOn Fitness - Sand Volleyball - Boost Your Endurance this Weekend','237014433','1485019816000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/237014433/','Event Host: Shiva 9-8-6-6-9-8-4-8-1-4','2017-01-21 17:30:00.000000','past','1st Left after Meridian School, Opposite Tata Service Centre, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society, Madhapur','Hyderabad','in','The Street',0,'2017-01-21 17:30:00.000000','<p><b><i>1 court, 2 teams, 3 touches, 11 points, 1 winner team, a lot of energy, fitness, and a great team spirit, that we call \"sand volleyball\". </i></b>it is played by 2 teams on either side of the court divided by a net. Every team has 3 chances at max to send the to the other court, on this basis points are counted. Team which reaches 25 points first is declared as winner.</p> <p>Sand volleyball involves many quick and shifty movements, and jumps. It increases your <b>strength</b>, <b>performance endurance</b>, and <b>muscle balance</b>. Basically, <b>its </b><b>like an endurance drill. </b>Volleyball would make you want to play it non-stop. <b>Its a greatest stress reliever as well. </b>There is nothing better than feeling that you can spike the ball on your opponent team :)</p> <p><b>Lets meet up on Saturday 05:30PM - 10:15PM for a few sand volleyball matches to relieve your week\'s stress and to boost your endurance. </b>This will give you more energy to enjoy your weekend.</p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/7/d/2/600_453858386.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/8/600_455051160.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/b/9/d/600_455051165.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/8/e/2/7/600_450876391.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"https://a248.e.akamai.net/secure.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/9/9/3/8/600_450999224.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Time table :</b><br/>5.30: Meet at The Street, 100 feet Road, Ayyappa Society</p> <p>5.40: Introduction and game rules</p> <p>5.45: Warm up exercises</p> <p>6.00: Game shuru</p> <p>10.00: End game and feedback</p> <p>10.15: Tata bye bye.</p> <p><b>Things to bring:</b><br/><b><i>T-shirt, track, water, snacks, loads of energy and smiles. </i></b></p> <p><b>Instructions</b>: No shows are not encouraged as we are booking the court based on number of rsvp\'s so please RSVP NO if you are not sure of attending the meet.</p> <p><b>Note: Beginners are also happily welcomed.</b></p> <p><b>Cost </b></p> <p>- Rs 200 per head (ground rent ), may vary.</p> <p><b>Contact </b>: Shiva- 9866984814</p> '),(639,'1482333242000','It\'s time for beautiful Pondicherry & more','236375847','1485760882000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236375847/','ClimbOn Sandeep : 800 800 4360','2017-01-25 19:00:00.000000','past','Secunderabad','Hyderabad','in','Secunderabad Railway Station',0,'2017-01-30 07:21:00.000000','<p>Team Size : 10 to 12 including Organizer. </p> <p>Pondicherry is the capital city of Indian union territory of Puducherry. Pondicherry is situated in Puducherry district of the union territory and other districts situated in Tamil Nadu (Karaikal), Andhra (Yanam) &amp; Kerala (Mahe) majority of the people speaks Tamil. It is affectionately known as Pondy, and has been officially known by the alternative name Puducherry in Tamil (New Town) since 2006. Pondicherry is the regional capital and largest city in the territory. Away from the hustle and bustle of big city, Puducherry formerly Pondicherry is a quiet little town on the southern coast. </p> <p>The unmistakable French connection, the tree lined boulevards, the quaint colonial heritage buildings, the spiritual scene, the endless stretches of unspoiled virgin beaches, backwater, A surprising choice of restaurants serving a mélange of cuisines.  </p> <p><b>French boulevard:  </b></p> <p>A French colony until 1954, this coastal town retains a number of colonial buildings, churches, statues, and systematic town planning, as well as urban architecture, dubbed \"The Europe of India\" or the French Riviera of the East.    </p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/4/a/600_457037226.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>French War Memorial  </b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/4/1/600_457037217.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Churches of Pondicherry   </b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/3/6/600_457037206.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Back Waters of Pondicherry  </b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos2.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/3/c/600_457037212.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Auroville</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/4/3/2/f/600_457037199.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Mahabalipuram</b></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/6/8/d/3/600_457046835.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Day 1: (Wednesday): </b></p> <p>5.30 pm - Hyderabad to Pondicherry </p> <p><b>Day 2: (Thursday)  </b></p> <p>12.00 pm:  </p> <p>Reach Pondicherry check in rooms- refresh, Breakfast,</p> <p>Pondicherry sightseeing - Visit to Temples, Churches, and French war memorial </p> <p>Boat ride at back waters, Paradise beach and get to the beach Island. </p> <p>9:00 PM – back to rooms, Good night</p> <p><b>Day 3: (Friday)</b></p> <p>6:30 AM - Wake up, sunrise at beach Walk</p> <p>8.00 AM have breakfast and leave for Auroville.</p> <p>7.00 PM check into Hotel at Mahabalipuram </p> <p><b>Day 4: (Saturday)</b></p> <p>7.00 AM -  fresh up, have breakfast and go sightseeing</p> <p>2.00 PM after lunch start by local bus to Chennai railway station</p> <p>6.00 PM board train to Hyderabad </p> <p><b>Note</b>: This is a tentative itinerary subject to changes.</p> <p><b>Payment Details:</b> Rs. 6000/- (includes Travel - Shared Stay - Veg Food - Local Transport - Club Fund - Org Reimbursement).</p> <p>• All personal expenditures like camera fees, shopping etc. are to be borne by the individuals.</p> <p>• Entry Fees to some places and Boat fees is excluded </p> <p>• Add yourself to Waiting list and You will be moved to YES list after receiving the payment on First come First Serve basis.</p> <p><b>Account Name : </b>Climb on adventures society</p> <p><b>A/C No:</b> 916010056765291</p> <p><b>IFSC CODE:</b> UTIB0002960</p> <p><b>Branch </b>: NIZAMPET  HYDERABAD </p> <p>• Once payment is done comment your transaction ID or number below for confirmation.</p> <p><b>Important Instructions:  </b></p> <p>1) No smoking and no alcohol  </p> <p>2) No littering, no pollution of water  </p> <p>3) This is a budget trip but we will try to make it as comfortable as possible. </p> <p>4) Accommodation will be on triple sharing basis  </p> <p>5) No antisocial, deviant or unacceptable social behavior  Anybody not following this guidelines and rules will be asked to leave immediately and removed from the group.  </p> <p>6) We carry Basic First Aid and if you need anything you can ask the organizers </p> <p>7) If you feel unwell bring to the notice of the organizers immediately.  </p> <p>8) If you can\'t swim don\'t go deep into the water  </p> <p>9) You cannot go off trail or move about alone without informing the organizers </p> <p>10) Do not take unnecessary risks and always follow the organizers\' directions </p> <p><b>Contact</b>:</p> <p>ClimbOn Sandeep<b> : 800 800 4360</b></p> '),(640,'1482901117000','Trek to Meesapulimala - Third Highest peak in Kerala','236493346','1485742285000','https://www.meetup.com/Theclimbon/events/236493346/','ClimbOn - Shiva - 9-8-6-6-9-8-4-8-1-4, Rohit - 9-6-7-6-7-2-2-1-5-5','2017-01-26 11:00:00.000000','past','Nampally','Hyderabad','in','Hyderabad Railway Station at Nampally',0,'2017-01-30 02:11:00.000000','<p>Meesapulimala trek is one of the most beautiful and famous treks in Kerala. The trail takes you through the vast expanse of the tea estates, through endless lush green grasslands and streams.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos1.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/6/e/e/600_457135022.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Difficulty level:</b> Medium - High</p> <p>For: Aged 18+yrs and fit trekkers only, If you are interested, add yourself to WL, and once payment is received you will be moved into going list.</p> <p>---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p> <p>Meesapulimala is the third highest peak in the Western Ghats on the Indian subcontinent after Anamudi and Mannamalai in Idukki District Kerala. Its peak is 2,640 metres (8,661 ft) above sea level. You can experience spectacular views once you reach the top.</p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/0/0/600_457135040.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/a/8/8/600_457135944.jpeg\" /></p> <p><img src=\"http://photos4.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/d/7/2/9/600_457135081.jpeg\" /></p> <p><b>Itinerary:</b></p> <p>(Thursday):</p> <p>Start from Nampally @ 11:00 AM by train.</p> <p>(Friday):</p> <p>02:00 PM: Reach Ernakulam, Board the bus</p> <p>02:15 PM: Travel to Athirapally Waterfalls</p> <p>03:15 PM: Lunch</p> <p>03:45 PM: Visit Athirapally Waterfalls</p> <p>06:00 PM: Local Site Seeing.</p> <p>10:00 PM: Start to KFDC Office</p> <p>(Saturday)</p> <p>04:00 AM: Reach KFDC Office and enjoy the beautiful plantation set up by the forest department.</p> <p>05:00 AM: Start to base camp</p> <p>06:30 AM: Reach Base Camp and fresh up and have some snacks.</p> <p>07:30 AM: Start the trekking.</p> <p>05:00 PM: Reach Base Camp and rest for the day in the tents provided by the forest department.</p> <p>08:30 PM: Dinner.</p> <p>09:00: Camp Fire chit chat and sleep.</p> <p>(Sunday)</p> <p>6:00 AM: Wake Up call and fresh up.</p> <p>8:00 AM: Board bus and reach Aluva</p> <p>1:00 AM: Reach Aluva and catch bus to Hyderabad.</p> <p>(Monday)</p> <p>07:00 AM: Reach Hyderabad.</p> <p><b>Note</b>: Itinerary may change a bit based on the time we reach to the destinations.</p> <p><b>Advisory:</b></p> <p>* As we are traversing through pristine and untamed nature, do not expect luxury trip</p> <p>* Basic level of fitness is compulsory to undertake this trek</p> <p>* Do pay attention to the guidelines given by the instructor</p> <p>* Alcohol is strictly prohibited and will not be tolerated under any circumstances.</p> <p>* Do not carry valuables or expensive jewellery during the trip</p> <p>* Do not leave the campsite during the night</p> <p>* Avoid using earphones during the trek as they might hinder your audibility</p> <p><b>Things to Bring:</b></p> <p>1. Rucksack/ Backpack to keep all things with nice support.</p> <p>2. Blanket (Must). <br/>3. Shoes with good grip used before &amp; two pairs of socks <br/>4. Dress change for 2 days (Light Colors preferable, Avoid jeans) &amp; few plastic covers to keep wet cloths.<br/>5. Jackets to keep you safe from sold as it would be very cold in the night (Must).<br/>6. Torch with extra batteries (Must).<br/>7. Water Bottle min (2 litres) (Must)<br/>8. Camera to click moments- OPTIONAL <br/>9. Any specific medicines you need.<br/>10. Carry Identification card - Govt recognized one <br/>11. Snacks like energy bars, ready to eat food (Must)<br/>12. Odomos Cream.</p> <p><b>Note</b>: No booze, No intoxicants, No Strong drinks and No Smoking from start to end of the event.</p> <p>Please note that this is not a luxury trip. Just wear what you comfortable with, just relax as there is none to test you, Pull you, push you or to compete you. It\'s just all about having fun. Most important of all, A big smile, loads of energy and enthusiasm. This is not a luxury trip, but utmost care has been taken to make our trip comfortable. </p> <p><b>Cost :</b> Rs: 6000/- per person (Does include dinner and breakfast the next day at base camp (only one day)). Any excess money will be shared and remaining money will be refunded before the trek ends.</p> <p>Pay 3000 as advance to confirm your slot.. You can transfer your amount to the below account.</p> <p>Name: T. Shiva Prasad Rao</p> <p>Bank: HDFC </p> <p>Account Number: 05211050315420</p> <p>IFSC Code: HDFC0000521</p> <p>BANJARA HILLS</p> <p>Need more information do contact <b>Shiva:</b> 9866984814</p> <p>Note: Request you to only RSVP if you are sure about making it to the event as we need to book tickets in advance any drop outs in the middle would cause lot of problems. Hence request you to RSVP only if you are sure about making it to the event.</p> ');
